1702 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
1703 // Type Sizing and Analysis
1704 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
1705 
1706 /// getFloatTypeSemantics - Return the APFloat 'semantics' for the specified
1707 /// scalar floating point type.
1708 const llvm::fltSemantics &ASTContext::getFloatTypeSemantics(QualType T) const {
1709  switch (T->castAs<BuiltinType>()->getKind()) {
1710  default:
1711  llvm_unreachable("Not a floating point type!");
1712  case BuiltinType::BFloat16:
1713  return Target->getBFloat16Format();
1714  case BuiltinType::Float16:
1715  case BuiltinType::Half:
1716  return Target->getHalfFormat();
1717  case BuiltinType::Float: return Target->getFloatFormat();
1718  case BuiltinType::Double: return Target->getDoubleFormat();
1719  case BuiltinType::Ibm128:
1720  return Target->getIbm128Format();
1721  case BuiltinType::LongDouble:
1722  if (getLangOpts().OpenMP && getLangOpts().OpenMPIsDevice)
1723  return AuxTarget->getLongDoubleFormat();
1724  return Target->getLongDoubleFormat();
1725  case BuiltinType::Float128:
1726  if (getLangOpts().OpenMP && getLangOpts().OpenMPIsDevice)
1727  return AuxTarget->getFloat128Format();
1728  return Target->getFloat128Format();
1729  }
1730 }
1731 
1732 CharUnits ASTContext::getDeclAlign(const Decl *D, bool ForAlignof) const {
1733  unsigned Align = Target->getCharWidth();
1734 
1735  bool UseAlignAttrOnly = false;
1736  if (unsigned AlignFromAttr = D->getMaxAlignment()) {
1737  Align = AlignFromAttr;
1738 
1739  // __attribute__((aligned)) can increase or decrease alignment
1740  // *except* on a struct or struct member, where it only increases
1741  // alignment unless 'packed' is also specified.
1742  //
1743  // It is an error for alignas to decrease alignment, so we can
1744  // ignore that possibility; Sema should diagnose it.
1745  if (isa<FieldDecl>(D)) {
1746  UseAlignAttrOnly = D->hasAttr<PackedAttr>() ||
1747  cast<FieldDecl>(D)->getParent()->hasAttr<PackedAttr>();
1748  } else {
1749  UseAlignAttrOnly = true;
1750  }
1751  }
1752  else if (isa<FieldDecl>(D))
1753  UseAlignAttrOnly =
1754  D->hasAttr<PackedAttr>() ||
1755  cast<FieldDecl>(D)->getParent()->hasAttr<PackedAttr>();
1756 
1757  // If we're using the align attribute only, just ignore everything
1758  // else about the declaration and its type.
1759  if (UseAlignAttrOnly) {
1760  // do nothing
1761  } else if (const auto *VD = dyn_cast<ValueDecl>(D)) {
1762  QualType T = VD->getType();
1763  if (const auto *RT = T->getAs<ReferenceType>()) {
1764  if (ForAlignof)
1765  T = RT->getPointeeType();
1766  else
1767  T = getPointerType(RT->getPointeeType());
1768  }
1769  QualType BaseT = getBaseElementType(T);
1770  if (T->isFunctionType())
1771  Align = getTypeInfoImpl(T.getTypePtr()).Align;
1772  else if (!BaseT->isIncompleteType()) {
1773  // Adjust alignments of declarations with array type by the
1774  // large-array alignment on the target.
1775  if (const ArrayType *arrayType = getAsArrayType(T)) {
1776  unsigned MinWidth = Target->getLargeArrayMinWidth();
1777  if (!ForAlignof && MinWidth) {
1778  if (isa<VariableArrayType>(arrayType))
1779  Align = std::max(Align, Target->getLargeArrayAlign());
1780  else if (isa<ConstantArrayType>(arrayType) &&
1781  MinWidth <= getTypeSize(cast<ConstantArrayType>(arrayType)))
1782  Align = std::max(Align, Target->getLargeArrayAlign());
1783  }
1784  }
1785  Align = std::max(Align, getPreferredTypeAlign(T.getTypePtr()));
1786  if (BaseT.getQualifiers().hasUnaligned())
1787  Align = Target->getCharWidth();
1788  if (const auto *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(D)) {
1789  if (VD->hasGlobalStorage() && !ForAlignof) {
1790  uint64_t TypeSize = getTypeSize(T.getTypePtr());
1791  Align = std::max(Align, getTargetInfo().getMinGlobalAlign(TypeSize));
1792  }
1793  }
1794  }
1795 
1796  // Fields can be subject to extra alignment constraints, like if
1797  // the field is packed, the struct is packed, or the struct has a
1798  // a max-field-alignment constraint (#pragma pack). So calculate
1799  // the actual alignment of the field within the struct, and then
1800  // (as we're expected to) constrain that by the alignment of the type.
1801  if (const auto *Field = dyn_cast<FieldDecl>(VD)) {
1802  const RecordDecl *Parent = Field->getParent();
1803  // We can only produce a sensible answer if the record is valid.
1804  if (!Parent->isInvalidDecl()) {
1805  const ASTRecordLayout &Layout = getASTRecordLayout(Parent);
1806 
1807  // Start with the record's overall alignment.
1808  unsigned FieldAlign = toBits(Layout.getAlignment());
1809 
1810  // Use the GCD of that and the offset within the record.
1811  uint64_t Offset = Layout.getFieldOffset(Field->getFieldIndex());
1812  if (Offset > 0) {
1813  // Alignment is always a power of 2, so the GCD will be a power of 2,
1814  // which means we get to do this crazy thing instead of Euclid's.
1815  uint64_t LowBitOfOffset = Offset & (~Offset + 1);
1816  if (LowBitOfOffset < FieldAlign)
1817  FieldAlign = static_cast<unsigned>(LowBitOfOffset);
1818  }
1819 
1820  Align = std::min(Align, FieldAlign);
1821  }
1822  }
1823  }
1824 
1825  // Some targets have hard limitation on the maximum requestable alignment in
1826  // aligned attribute for static variables.
1827  const unsigned MaxAlignedAttr = getTargetInfo().getMaxAlignedAttribute();
1828  const auto *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(D);
1829  if (MaxAlignedAttr && VD && VD->getStorageClass() == SC_Static)
1830  Align = std::min(Align, MaxAlignedAttr);
1831 
1832  return toCharUnitsFromBits(Align);
1833 }
1834 
1835 CharUnits ASTContext::getExnObjectAlignment() const {
1836  return toCharUnitsFromBits(Target->getExnObjectAlignment());
1837 }
1838 
1839 // getTypeInfoDataSizeInChars - Return the size of a type, in
1840 // chars. If the type is a record, its data size is returned. This is
1841 // the size of the memcpy that's performed when assigning this type
1842 // using a trivial copy/move assignment operator.
1843 TypeInfoChars ASTContext::getTypeInfoDataSizeInChars(QualType T) const {
1844  TypeInfoChars Info = getTypeInfoInChars(T);
1845 
1846  // In C++, objects can sometimes be allocated into the tail padding
1847  // of a base-class subobject. We decide whether that's possible
1848  // during class layout, so here we can just trust the layout results.
1849  if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus) {
1850  if (const auto *RT = T->getAs<RecordType>()) {
1851  const ASTRecordLayout &layout = getASTRecordLayout(RT->getDecl());
1852  Info.Width = layout.getDataSize();
1853  }
1854  }
1855 
1856  return Info;
1857 }
1858 
1859 /// getConstantArrayInfoInChars - Performing the computation in CharUnits
1860 /// instead of in bits prevents overflowing the uint64_t for some large arrays.
1861 TypeInfoChars
1862 static getConstantArrayInfoInChars(const ASTContext &Context,
1863  const ConstantArrayType *CAT) {
1864  TypeInfoChars EltInfo = Context.getTypeInfoInChars(CAT->getElementType());
1865  uint64_t Size = CAT->getSize().getZExtValue();
1866  assert((Size == 0 || static_cast<uint64_t>(EltInfo.Width.getQuantity()) <=
1867  (uint64_t)(-1)/Size) &&
1868  "Overflow in array type char size evaluation");
1869  uint64_t Width = EltInfo.Width.getQuantity() * Size;
1870  unsigned Align = EltInfo.Align.getQuantity();
1871  if (!Context.getTargetInfo().getCXXABI().isMicrosoft() ||
1872  Context.getTargetInfo().getPointerWidth(0) == 64)
1873  Width = llvm::alignTo(Width, Align);
1874  return TypeInfoChars(CharUnits::fromQuantity(Width),
1875  CharUnits::fromQuantity(Align),
1876  EltInfo.AlignRequirement);
1877 }
1878 
1879 TypeInfoChars ASTContext::getTypeInfoInChars(const Type *T) const {
1880  if (const auto *CAT = dyn_cast<ConstantArrayType>(T))
1881  return getConstantArrayInfoInChars(*this, CAT);
1882  TypeInfo Info = getTypeInfo(T);
1883  return TypeInfoChars(toCharUnitsFromBits(Info.Width),
1884  toCharUnitsFromBits(Info.Align), Info.AlignRequirement);
1885 }
1886 
1887 TypeInfoChars ASTContext::getTypeInfoInChars(QualType T) const {
1888  return getTypeInfoInChars(T.getTypePtr());
1889 }
1890 
1891 bool ASTContext::isAlignmentRequired(const Type *T) const {
1892  return getTypeInfo(T).AlignRequirement != AlignRequirementKind::None;
1893 }
1894 
1895 bool ASTContext::isAlignmentRequired(QualType T) const {
1896  return isAlignmentRequired(T.getTypePtr());
1897 }
1898 
1899 unsigned ASTContext::getTypeAlignIfKnown(QualType T,
1900  bool NeedsPreferredAlignment) const {
1901  // An alignment on a typedef overrides anything else.
1902  if (const auto *TT = T->getAs<TypedefType>())
1903  if (unsigned Align = TT->getDecl()->getMaxAlignment())
1904  return Align;
1905 
1906  // If we have an (array of) complete type, we're done.
1907  T = getBaseElementType(T);
1908  if (!T->isIncompleteType())
1909  return NeedsPreferredAlignment ? getPreferredTypeAlign(T) : getTypeAlign(T);
1910 
1911  // If we had an array type, its element type might be a typedef
1912  // type with an alignment attribute.
1913  if (const auto *TT = T->getAs<TypedefType>())
1914  if (unsigned Align = TT->getDecl()->getMaxAlignment())
1915  return Align;
1916 
1917  // Otherwise, see if the declaration of the type had an attribute.
1918  if (const auto *TT = T->getAs<TagType>())
1919  return TT->getDecl()->getMaxAlignment();
1920 
1921  return 0;
1922 }
1923 
1924 TypeInfo ASTContext::getTypeInfo(const Type *T) const {
1925  TypeInfoMap::iterator I = MemoizedTypeInfo.find(T);
1926  if (I != MemoizedTypeInfo.end())
1927  return I->second;
1928 
1929  // This call can invalidate MemoizedTypeInfo[T], so we need a second lookup.
1930  TypeInfo TI = getTypeInfoImpl(T);
1931  MemoizedTypeInfo[T] = TI;
1932  return TI;
1933 }
1934 
1935 /// getTypeInfoImpl - Return the size of the specified type, in bits. This
1936 /// method does not work on incomplete types.
1937 ///
1938 /// FIXME: Pointers into different addr spaces could have different sizes and
1939 /// alignment requirements: getPointerInfo should take an AddrSpace, this
1940 /// should take a QualType, &c.
1941 TypeInfo ASTContext::getTypeInfoImpl(const Type *T) const {
1942  uint64_t Width = 0;
1943  unsigned Align = 8;
1944  AlignRequirementKind AlignRequirement = AlignRequirementKind::None;
1945  unsigned AS = 0;
1946  switch (T->getTypeClass()) {
1947 #define TYPE(Class, Base)
1948 #define ABSTRACT_TYPE(Class, Base)
1949 #define NON_CANONICAL_TYPE(Class, Base)
1950 #define DEPENDENT_TYPE(Class, Base) case Type::Class:
1951 #define NON_CANONICAL_UNLESS_DEPENDENT_TYPE(Class, Base) \
1952  case Type::Class: \
1953  assert(!T->isDependentType() && "should not see dependent types here"); \
1954  return getTypeInfo(cast<Class##Type>(T)->desugar().getTypePtr());
1955 #include "clang/AST/TypeNodes.inc"
1956  llvm_unreachable("Should not see dependent types");
1957 
1958  case Type::FunctionNoProto:
1959  case Type::FunctionProto:
1960  // GCC extension: alignof(function) = 32 bits
1961  Width = 0;
1962  Align = 32;
1963  break;
1964 
1965  case Type::IncompleteArray:
1966  case Type::VariableArray:
1967  case Type::ConstantArray: {
1968  // Model non-constant sized arrays as size zero, but track the alignment.
1969  uint64_t Size = 0;
1970  if (const auto *CAT = dyn_cast<ConstantArrayType>(T))
1971  Size = CAT->getSize().getZExtValue();
1972 
1973  TypeInfo EltInfo = getTypeInfo(cast<ArrayType>(T)->getElementType());
1974  assert((Size == 0 || EltInfo.Width <= (uint64_t)(-1) / Size) &&
1975  "Overflow in array type bit size evaluation");
1976  Width = EltInfo.Width * Size;
1977  Align = EltInfo.Align;
1978  AlignRequirement = EltInfo.AlignRequirement;
1979  if (!getTargetInfo().getCXXABI().isMicrosoft() ||
1980  getTargetInfo().getPointerWidth(0) == 64)
1981  Width = llvm::alignTo(Width, Align);
1982  break;
1983  }
1984 
1985  case Type::ExtVector:
1986  case Type::Vector: {
1987  const auto *VT = cast<VectorType>(T);
1988  TypeInfo EltInfo = getTypeInfo(VT->getElementType());
1989  Width = VT->isExtVectorBoolType() ? VT->getNumElements()
1990  : EltInfo.Width * VT->getNumElements();
1991  // Enforce at least byte alignment.
1992  Align = std::max<unsigned>(8, Width);
1993 
1994  // If the alignment is not a power of 2, round up to the next power of 2.
1995  // This happens for non-power-of-2 length vectors.
1996  if (Align & (Align-1)) {
1997  Align = llvm::NextPowerOf2(Align);
1998  Width = llvm::alignTo(Width, Align);
1999  }
2000  // Adjust the alignment based on the target max.
2001  uint64_t TargetVectorAlign = Target->getMaxVectorAlign();
2002  if (TargetVectorAlign && TargetVectorAlign < Align)
2003  Align = TargetVectorAlign;
2004  if (VT->getVectorKind() == VectorType::SveFixedLengthDataVector)
2005  // Adjust the alignment for fixed-length SVE vectors. This is important
2006  // for non-power-of-2 vector lengths.
2007  Align = 128;
2008  else if (VT->getVectorKind() == VectorType::SveFixedLengthPredicateVector)
2009  // Adjust the alignment for fixed-length SVE predicates.
2010  Align = 16;
2011  break;
2012  }
2013 
2014  case Type::ConstantMatrix: {
2015  const auto *MT = cast<ConstantMatrixType>(T);
2016  TypeInfo ElementInfo = getTypeInfo(MT->getElementType());
2017  // The internal layout of a matrix value is implementation defined.
2018  // Initially be ABI compatible with arrays with respect to alignment and
2019  // size.
2020  Width = ElementInfo.Width * MT->getNumRows() * MT->getNumColumns();
2021  Align = ElementInfo.Align;
2022  break;
2023  }
2024 
2025  case Type::Builtin:
2026  switch (cast<BuiltinType>(T)->getKind()) {
2027  default: llvm_unreachable("Unknown builtin type!");
2028  case BuiltinType::Void:
2029  // GCC extension: alignof(void) = 8 bits.
2030  Width = 0;
2031  Align = 8;
2032  break;
2033  case BuiltinType::Bool:
2034  Width = Target->getBoolWidth();
2035  Align = Target->getBoolAlign();
2036  break;
2037  case BuiltinType::Char_S:
2038  case BuiltinType::Char_U:
2039  case BuiltinType::UChar:
2040  case BuiltinType::SChar:
2041  case BuiltinType::Char8:
2042  Width = Target->getCharWidth();
2043  Align = Target->getCharAlign();
2044  break;
2045  case BuiltinType::WChar_S:
2046  case BuiltinType::WChar_U:
2047  Width = Target->getWCharWidth();
2048  Align = Target->getWCharAlign();
2049  break;
2050  case BuiltinType::Char16:
2051  Width = Target->getChar16Width();
2052  Align = Target->getChar16Align();
2053  break;
2054  case BuiltinType::Char32:
2055  Width = Target->getChar32Width();
2056  Align = Target->getChar32Align();
2057  break;
2058  case BuiltinType::UShort:
2059  case BuiltinType::Short:
2060  Width = Target->getShortWidth();
2061  Align = Target->getShortAlign();
2062  break;
2063  case BuiltinType::UInt:
2064  case BuiltinType::Int:
2065  Width = Target->getIntWidth();
2066  Align = Target->getIntAlign();
2067  break;
2068  case BuiltinType::ULong:
2069  case BuiltinType::Long:
2070  Width = Target->getLongWidth();
2071  Align = Target->getLongAlign();
2072  break;
2073  case BuiltinType::ULongLong:
2074  case BuiltinType::LongLong:
2075  Width = Target->getLongLongWidth();
2076  Align = Target->getLongLongAlign();
2077  break;
2078  case BuiltinType::Int128:
2079  case BuiltinType::UInt128:
2080  Width = 128;
2081  Align = 128; // int128_t is 128-bit aligned on all targets.
2082  break;
2083  case BuiltinType::ShortAccum:
2084  case BuiltinType::UShortAccum:
2085  case BuiltinType::SatShortAccum:
2086  case BuiltinType::SatUShortAccum:
2087  Width = Target->getShortAccumWidth();
2088  Align = Target->getShortAccumAlign();
2089  break;
2090  case BuiltinType::Accum:
2091  case BuiltinType::UAccum:
2092  case BuiltinType::SatAccum:
2093  case BuiltinType::SatUAccum:
2094  Width = Target->getAccumWidth();
2095  Align = Target->getAccumAlign();
2096  break;
2097  case BuiltinType::LongAccum:
2098  case BuiltinType::ULongAccum:
2099  case BuiltinType::SatLongAccum:
2100  case BuiltinType::SatULongAccum:
2101  Width = Target->getLongAccumWidth();
2102  Align = Target->getLongAccumAlign();
2103  break;
2104  case BuiltinType::ShortFract:
2105  case BuiltinType::UShortFract:
2106  case BuiltinType::SatShortFract:
2107  case BuiltinType::SatUShortFract:
2108  Width = Target->getShortFractWidth();
2109  Align = Target->getShortFractAlign();
2110  break;
2111  case BuiltinType::Fract:
2112  case BuiltinType::UFract:
2113  case BuiltinType::SatFract:
2114  case BuiltinType::SatUFract:
2115  Width = Target->getFractWidth();
2116  Align = Target->getFractAlign();
2117  break;
2118  case BuiltinType::LongFract:
2119  case BuiltinType::ULongFract:
2120  case BuiltinType::SatLongFract:
2121  case BuiltinType::SatULongFract:
2122  Width = Target->getLongFractWidth();
2123  Align = Target->getLongFractAlign();
2124  break;
2125  case BuiltinType::BFloat16:
2126  Width = Target->getBFloat16Width();
2127  Align = Target->getBFloat16Align();
2128  break;
2129  case BuiltinType::Float16:
2130  case BuiltinType::Half:
2131  if (Target->hasFloat16Type() || !getLangOpts().OpenMP ||
2132  !getLangOpts().OpenMPIsDevice) {
2133  Width = Target->getHalfWidth();
2134  Align = Target->getHalfAlign();
2135  } else {
2136  assert(getLangOpts().OpenMP && getLangOpts().OpenMPIsDevice &&
2137  "Expected OpenMP device compilation.");
2138  Width = AuxTarget->getHalfWidth();
2139  Align = AuxTarget->getHalfAlign();
2140  }
2141  break;
2142  case BuiltinType::Float:
2143  Width = Target->getFloatWidth();
2144  Align = Target->getFloatAlign();
2145  break;
2146  case BuiltinType::Double:
2147  Width = Target->getDoubleWidth();
2148  Align = Target->getDoubleAlign();
2149  break;
2150  case BuiltinType::Ibm128:
2151  Width = Target->getIbm128Width();
2152  Align = Target->getIbm128Align();
2153  break;
2154  case BuiltinType::LongDouble:
2155  if ((getLangOpts().SYCLIsDevice ||
2156  (getLangOpts().OpenMP && getLangOpts().OpenMPIsDevice)) &&
2157  AuxTarget != nullptr &&
2158  (Target->getLongDoubleWidth() != AuxTarget->getLongDoubleWidth() ||
2159  Target->getLongDoubleAlign() != AuxTarget->getLongDoubleAlign())) {
2160  Width = AuxTarget->getLongDoubleWidth();
2161  Align = AuxTarget->getLongDoubleAlign();
2162  } else {
2163  Width = Target->getLongDoubleWidth();
2164  Align = Target->getLongDoubleAlign();
2165  }
2166  break;
2167  case BuiltinType::Float128:
2168  if (Target->hasFloat128Type() || !getLangOpts().OpenMP ||
2169  !getLangOpts().OpenMPIsDevice) {
2170  Width = Target->getFloat128Width();
2171  Align = Target->getFloat128Align();
2172  } else {
2173  assert(getLangOpts().OpenMP && getLangOpts().OpenMPIsDevice &&
2174  "Expected OpenMP device compilation.");
2175  Width = AuxTarget->getFloat128Width();
2176  Align = AuxTarget->getFloat128Align();
2177  }
2178  break;
2179  case BuiltinType::NullPtr:
2180  Width = Target->getPointerWidth(0); // C++ 3.9.1p11: sizeof(nullptr_t)
2181  Align = Target->getPointerAlign(0); // == sizeof(void*)
2182  break;
2183  case BuiltinType::ObjCId:
2184  case BuiltinType::ObjCClass:
2185  case BuiltinType::ObjCSel:
2186  Width = Target->getPointerWidth(0);
2187  Align = Target->getPointerAlign(0);
2188  break;
2189  case BuiltinType::OCLSampler:
2190  case BuiltinType::OCLEvent:
2191  case BuiltinType::OCLClkEvent:
2192  case BuiltinType::OCLQueue:
2193  case BuiltinType::OCLReserveID:
2194 #define IMAGE_TYPE(ImgType, Id, SingletonId, Access, Suffix) \
2195  case BuiltinType::Id:
2196 #include "clang/Basic/OpenCLImageTypes.def"
2197 #define IMAGE_TYPE(ImgType, Id, SingletonId, Access, Suffix) \
2198  case BuiltinType::Sampled##Id:
2199 #define IMAGE_WRITE_TYPE(Type, Id, Ext)
2200 #define IMAGE_READ_WRITE_TYPE(Type, Id, Ext)
2201 #include "clang/Basic/OpenCLImageTypes.def"
2202 #define EXT_OPAQUE_TYPE(ExtType, Id, Ext) \
2203  case BuiltinType::Id:
2204 #include "clang/Basic/OpenCLExtensionTypes.def"
2205  AS = getTargetAddressSpace(
2206  Target->getOpenCLTypeAddrSpace(getOpenCLTypeKind(T)));
2207  Width = Target->getPointerWidth(AS);
2208  Align = Target->getPointerAlign(AS);
2209  break;
2210  // The SVE types are effectively target-specific. The length of an
2211  // SVE_VECTOR_TYPE is only known at runtime, but it is always a multiple
2212  // of 128 bits. There is one predicate bit for each vector byte, so the
2213  // length of an SVE_PREDICATE_TYPE is always a multiple of 16 bits.
2214  //
2215  // Because the length is only known at runtime, we use a dummy value
2216  // of 0 for the static length. The alignment values are those defined
2217  // by the Procedure Call Standard for the Arm Architecture.
2218 #define SVE_VECTOR_TYPE(Name, MangledName, Id, SingletonId, NumEls, ElBits, \
2219  IsSigned, IsFP, IsBF) \
2220  case BuiltinType::Id: \
2221  Width = 0; \
2222  Align = 128; \
2223  break;
2224 #define SVE_PREDICATE_TYPE(Name, MangledName, Id, SingletonId, NumEls) \
2225  case BuiltinType::Id: \
2226  Width = 0; \
2227  Align = 16; \
2228  break;
2229 #include "clang/Basic/AArch64SVEACLETypes.def"
2230 #define PPC_VECTOR_TYPE(Name, Id, Size) \
2231  case BuiltinType::Id: \
2232  Width = Size; \
2233  Align = Size; \
2234  break;
2235 #include "clang/Basic/PPCTypes.def"
2236 #define RVV_VECTOR_TYPE(Name, Id, SingletonId, ElKind, ElBits, NF, IsSigned, \
2237  IsFP) \
2238  case BuiltinType::Id: \
2239  Width = 0; \
2240  Align = ElBits; \
2241  break;
2242 #define RVV_PREDICATE_TYPE(Name, Id, SingletonId, ElKind) \
2243  case BuiltinType::Id: \
2244  Width = 0; \
2245  Align = 8; \
2246  break;
2247 #include "clang/Basic/RISCVVTypes.def"
2248  }
2249  break;
2250  case Type::ObjCObjectPointer:
2251  Width = Target->getPointerWidth(0);
2252  Align = Target->getPointerAlign(0);
2253  break;
2254  case Type::BlockPointer:
2255  AS = getTargetAddressSpace(cast<BlockPointerType>(T)->getPointeeType());
2256  Width = Target->getPointerWidth(AS);
2257  Align = Target->getPointerAlign(AS);
2258  break;
2259  case Type::LValueReference:
2260  case Type::RValueReference:
2261  // alignof and sizeof should never enter this code path here, so we go
2262  // the pointer route.
2263  AS = getTargetAddressSpace(cast<ReferenceType>(T)->getPointeeType());
2264  Width = Target->getPointerWidth(AS);
2265  Align = Target->getPointerAlign(AS);
2266  break;
2267  case Type::Pointer:
2268  AS = getTargetAddressSpace(cast<PointerType>(T)->getPointeeType());
2269  Width = Target->getPointerWidth(AS);
2270  Align = Target->getPointerAlign(AS);
2271  break;
2272  case Type::MemberPointer: {
2273  const auto *MPT = cast<MemberPointerType>(T);
2274  CXXABI::MemberPointerInfo MPI = ABI->getMemberPointerInfo(MPT);
2275  Width = MPI.Width;
2276  Align = MPI.Align;
2277  break;
2278  }
2279  case Type::Complex: {
2280  // Complex types have the same alignment as their elements, but twice the
2281  // size.
2282  TypeInfo EltInfo = getTypeInfo(cast<ComplexType>(T)->getElementType());
2283  Width = EltInfo.Width * 2;
2284  Align = EltInfo.Align;
2285  break;
2286  }
2287  case Type::ObjCObject:
2288  return getTypeInfo(cast<ObjCObjectType>(T)->getBaseType().getTypePtr());
2289  case Type::Adjusted:
2290  case Type::Decayed:
2291  return getTypeInfo(cast<AdjustedType>(T)->getAdjustedType().getTypePtr());
2292  case Type::ObjCInterface: {
2293  const auto *ObjCI = cast<ObjCInterfaceType>(T);
2294  if (ObjCI->getDecl()->isInvalidDecl()) {
2295  Width = 8;
2296  Align = 8;
2297  break;
2298  }
2299  const ASTRecordLayout &Layout = getASTObjCInterfaceLayout(ObjCI->getDecl());
2300  Width = toBits(Layout.getSize());
2301  Align = toBits(Layout.getAlignment());
2302  break;
2303  }
2304  case Type::BitInt: {
2305  const auto *EIT = cast<BitIntType>(T);
2306  Align =
2307  std::min(static_cast<unsigned>(std::max(
2308  getCharWidth(), llvm::PowerOf2Ceil(EIT->getNumBits()))),
2309  Target->getLongLongAlign());
2310  Width = llvm::alignTo(EIT->getNumBits(), Align);
2311  break;
2312  }
2313  case Type::Record:
2314  case Type::Enum: {
2315  const auto *TT = cast<TagType>(T);
2316 
2317  if (TT->getDecl()->isInvalidDecl()) {
2318  Width = 8;
2319  Align = 8;
2320  break;
2321  }
2322 
2323  if (const auto *ET = dyn_cast<EnumType>(TT)) {
2324  const EnumDecl *ED = ET->getDecl();
2325  TypeInfo Info =
2326  getTypeInfo(ED->getIntegerType()->getUnqualifiedDesugaredType());
2327  if (unsigned AttrAlign = ED->getMaxAlignment()) {
2328  Info.Align = AttrAlign;
2329  Info.AlignRequirement = AlignRequirementKind::RequiredByEnum;
2330  }
2331  return Info;
2332  }
2333 
2334  const auto *RT = cast<RecordType>(TT);
2335  const RecordDecl *RD = RT->getDecl();
2336  const ASTRecordLayout &Layout = getASTRecordLayout(RD);
2337  Width = toBits(Layout.getSize());
2338  Align = toBits(Layout.getAlignment());
2339  AlignRequirement = RD->hasAttr<AlignedAttr>()
2340  ? AlignRequirementKind::RequiredByRecord
2341  : AlignRequirementKind::None;
2342  break;
2343  }
2344 
2345  case Type::SubstTemplateTypeParm:
2346  return getTypeInfo(cast<SubstTemplateTypeParmType>(T)->
2347  getReplacementType().getTypePtr());
2348 
2349  case Type::Auto:
2350  case Type::DeducedTemplateSpecialization: {
2351  const auto *A = cast<DeducedType>(T);
2352  assert(!A->getDeducedType().isNull() &&
2353  "cannot request the size of an undeduced or dependent auto type");
2354  return getTypeInfo(A->getDeducedType().getTypePtr());
2355  }
2356 
2357  case Type::Paren:
2358  return getTypeInfo(cast<ParenType>(T)->getInnerType().getTypePtr());
2359 
2360  case Type::MacroQualified:
2361  return getTypeInfo(
2362  cast<MacroQualifiedType>(T)->getUnderlyingType().getTypePtr());
2363 
2364  case Type::ObjCTypeParam:
2365  return getTypeInfo(cast<ObjCTypeParamType>(T)->desugar().getTypePtr());
2366 
2367  case Type::Using:
2368  return getTypeInfo(cast<UsingType>(T)->desugar().getTypePtr());
2369 
2370  case Type::Typedef: {
2371  const TypedefNameDecl *Typedef = cast<TypedefType>(T)->getDecl();
2372  TypeInfo Info = getTypeInfo(Typedef->getUnderlyingType().getTypePtr());
2373  // If the typedef has an aligned attribute on it, it overrides any computed
2374  // alignment we have. This violates the GCC documentation (which says that
2375  // attribute(aligned) can only round up) but matches its implementation.
2376  if (unsigned AttrAlign = Typedef->getMaxAlignment()) {
2377  Align = AttrAlign;
2378  AlignRequirement = AlignRequirementKind::RequiredByTypedef;
2379  } else {
2380  Align = Info.Align;
2381  AlignRequirement = Info.AlignRequirement;
2382  }
2383  Width = Info.Width;
2384  break;
2385  }
2386 
2387  case Type::Elaborated:
2388  return getTypeInfo(cast<ElaboratedType>(T)->getNamedType().getTypePtr());
2389 
2390  case Type::Attributed:
2391  return getTypeInfo(
2392  cast<AttributedType>(T)->getEquivalentType().getTypePtr());
2393 
2394  case Type::BTFTagAttributed:
2395  return getTypeInfo(
2396  cast<BTFTagAttributedType>(T)->getWrappedType().getTypePtr());
2397 
2398  case Type::Atomic: {
2399  // Start with the base type information.
2400  TypeInfo Info = getTypeInfo(cast<AtomicType>(T)->getValueType());
2401  Width = Info.Width;
2402  Align = Info.Align;
2403 
2404  if (!Width) {
2405  // An otherwise zero-sized type should still generate an
2406  // atomic operation.
2407  Width = Target->getCharWidth();
2408  assert(Align);
2409  } else if (Width <= Target->getMaxAtomicPromoteWidth()) {
2410  // If the size of the type doesn't exceed the platform's max
2411  // atomic promotion width, make the size and alignment more
2412  // favorable to atomic operations:
2413 
2414  // Round the size up to a power of 2.
2415  if (!llvm::isPowerOf2_64(Width))
2416  Width = llvm::NextPowerOf2(Width);
2417 
2418  // Set the alignment equal to the size.
2419  Align = static_cast<unsigned>(Width);
2420  }
2421  }
2422  break;
2423 
2424  case Type::Pipe:
2425  Width = Target->getPointerWidth(getTargetAddressSpace(LangAS::opencl_global));
2426  Align = Target->getPointerAlign(getTargetAddressSpace(LangAS::opencl_global));
2427  break;
2428  }
2429 
2430  assert(llvm::isPowerOf2_32(Align) && "Alignment must be power of 2");
2431  return TypeInfo(Width, Align, AlignRequirement);
2432 }
2433 
2434 unsigned ASTContext::getTypeUnadjustedAlign(const Type *T) const {
2435  UnadjustedAlignMap::iterator I = MemoizedUnadjustedAlign.find(T);
2436  if (I != MemoizedUnadjustedAlign.end())
2437  return I->second;
2438 
2439  unsigned UnadjustedAlign;
2440  if (const auto *RT = T->getAs<RecordType>()) {
2441  const RecordDecl *RD = RT->getDecl();
2442  const ASTRecordLayout &Layout = getASTRecordLayout(RD);
2443  UnadjustedAlign = toBits(Layout.getUnadjustedAlignment());
2444  } else if (const auto *ObjCI = T->getAs<ObjCInterfaceType>()) {
2445  const ASTRecordLayout &Layout = getASTObjCInterfaceLayout(ObjCI->getDecl());
2446  UnadjustedAlign = toBits(Layout.getUnadjustedAlignment());
2447  } else {
2448  UnadjustedAlign = getTypeAlign(T->getUnqualifiedDesugaredType());
2449  }
2450 
2451  MemoizedUnadjustedAlign[T] = UnadjustedAlign;
2452  return UnadjustedAlign;
2453 }

2455 unsigned ASTContext::getOpenMPDefaultSimdAlign(QualType T) const {
2456  unsigned SimdAlign = getTargetInfo().getSimdDefaultAlign();
2457  return SimdAlign;

2498 /// getPreferredTypeAlign - Return the "preferred" alignment of the specified
2499 /// type for the current target in bits. This can be different than the ABI
2500 /// alignment in cases where it is beneficial for performance or backwards
2501 /// compatibility preserving to overalign a data type. (Note: despite the name,
2502 /// the preferred alignment is ABI-impacting, and not an optimization.)
2503 unsigned ASTContext::getPreferredTypeAlign(const Type *T) const {
2504  TypeInfo TI = getTypeInfo(T);
2505  unsigned ABIAlign = TI.Align;
2506 
2507  T = T->getBaseElementTypeUnsafe();
2508 
2509  // The preferred alignment of member pointers is that of a pointer.
2510  if (T->isMemberPointerType())
2511  return getPreferredTypeAlign(getPointerDiffType().getTypePtr());
2512 
2513  if (!Target->allowsLargerPreferedTypeAlignment())
2514  return ABIAlign;
2515 
2516  if (const auto *RT = T->getAs<RecordType>()) {
2517  const RecordDecl *RD = RT->getDecl();
2518 
2519  // When used as part of a typedef, or together with a 'packed' attribute,
2520  // the 'aligned' attribute can be used to decrease alignment. Note that the
2521  // 'packed' case is already taken into consideration when computing the
2522  // alignment, we only need to handle the typedef case here.
2523  if (TI.AlignRequirement == AlignRequirementKind::RequiredByTypedef ||
2524  RD->isInvalidDecl())
2525  return ABIAlign;
2526 
2527  unsigned PreferredAlign = static_cast<unsigned>(
2528  toBits(getASTRecordLayout(RD).PreferredAlignment));
2529  assert(PreferredAlign >= ABIAlign &&
2530  "PreferredAlign should be at least as large as ABIAlign.");
2531  return PreferredAlign;
2532  }
2533 
2534  // Double (and, for targets supporting AIX `power` alignment, long double) and
2535  // long long should be naturally aligned (despite requiring less alignment) if
2536  // possible.
2537  if (const auto *CT = T->getAs<ComplexType>())
2538  T = CT->getElementType().getTypePtr();
2539  if (const auto *ET = T->getAs<EnumType>())
2540  T = ET->getDecl()->getIntegerType().getTypePtr();
2541  if (T->isSpecificBuiltinType(BuiltinType::Double) ||
2542  T->isSpecificBuiltinType(BuiltinType::LongLong) ||
2543  T->isSpecificBuiltinType(BuiltinType::ULongLong) ||
2544  (T->isSpecificBuiltinType(BuiltinType::LongDouble) &&
2545  Target->defaultsToAIXPowerAlignment()))
2546  // Don't increase the alignment if an alignment attribute was specified on a
2547  // typedef declaration.
2548  if (!TI.isAlignRequired())
2549  return std::max(ABIAlign, (unsigned)getTypeSize(T));
2550 
2551  return ABIAlign;
2552 }
2553 
2554 /// getTargetDefaultAlignForAttributeAligned - Return the default alignment
2555 /// for __attribute__((aligned)) on this target, to be used if no alignment
2556 /// value is specified.
2557 unsigned ASTContext::getTargetDefaultAlignForAttributeAligned() const {
2558  return getTargetInfo().getDefaultAlignForAttributeAligned();
2559 }

2561 /// getAlignOfGlobalVar - Return the alignment in bits that should be given
2562 /// to a global variable of the specified type.
2563 unsigned ASTContext::getAlignOfGlobalVar(QualType T) const {
2564  uint64_t TypeSize = getTypeSize(T.getTypePtr());
2565  return std::max(getPreferredTypeAlign(T),
2566  getTargetInfo().getMinGlobalAlign(TypeSize));
2567 }

2575 CharUnits ASTContext::getOffsetOfBaseWithVBPtr(const CXXRecordDecl *RD) const {
2576  CharUnits Offset = CharUnits::Zero();
2577  const ASTRecordLayout *Layout = &getASTRecordLayout(RD);
2578  while (const CXXRecordDecl *Base = Layout->getBaseSharingVBPtr()) {
2579  Offset += Layout->getBaseClassOffset(Base);
2580  Layout = &getASTRecordLayout(Base);
2581  }
2582  return Offset;
2583 }
2584 
2585 CharUnits ASTContext::getMemberPointerPathAdjustment(const APValue &MP) const {
2586  const ValueDecl *MPD = MP.getMemberPointerDecl();
2587  CharUnits ThisAdjustment = CharUnits::Zero();
2588  ArrayRef<const CXXRecordDecl*> Path = MP.getMemberPointerPath();
2589  bool DerivedMember = MP.isMemberPointerToDerivedMember();
2590  const CXXRecordDecl *RD = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(MPD->getDeclContext());
2591  for (unsigned I = 0, N = Path.size(); I != N; ++I) {
2592  const CXXRecordDecl *Base = RD;
2593  const CXXRecordDecl *Derived = Path[I];
2594  if (DerivedMember)
2595  std::swap(Base, Derived);
2596  ThisAdjustment += getASTRecordLayout(Derived).getBaseClassOffset(Base);
2597  RD = Path[I];
2598  }
2599  if (DerivedMember)
2600  ThisAdjustment = -ThisAdjustment;
2601  return ThisAdjustment;
2602 }
2603 
2604 /// DeepCollectObjCIvars -
2605 /// This routine first collects all declared, but not synthesized, ivars in
2606 /// super class and then collects all ivars, including those synthesized for
2607 /// current class. This routine is used for implementation of current class
2608 /// when all ivars, declared and synthesized are known.
2609 void ASTContext::DeepCollectObjCIvars(const ObjCInterfaceDecl *OI,
2610  bool leafClass,
2611  SmallVectorImpl<const ObjCIvarDecl*> &Ivars) const {
2612  if (const ObjCInterfaceDecl *SuperClass = OI->getSuperClass())
2613  DeepCollectObjCIvars(SuperClass, false, Ivars);
2614  if (!leafClass) {
2615  llvm::append_range(Ivars, OI->ivars());
2616  } else {
2617  auto *IDecl = const_cast<ObjCInterfaceDecl *>(OI);
2618  for (const ObjCIvarDecl *Iv = IDecl->all_declared_ivar_begin(); Iv;
2619  Iv= Iv->getNextIvar())
2620  Ivars.push_back(Iv);
2621  }
2622 }
2623 
2624 /// CollectInheritedProtocols - Collect all protocols in current class and
2625 /// those inherited by it.
2626 void ASTContext::CollectInheritedProtocols(const Decl *CDecl,
2627  llvm::SmallPtrSet<ObjCProtocolDecl*, 8> &Protocols) {
2628  if (const auto *OI = dyn_cast<ObjCInterfaceDecl>(CDecl)) {
2629  // We can use protocol_iterator here instead of
2630  // all_referenced_protocol_iterator since we are walking all categories.
2631  for (auto *Proto : OI->all_referenced_protocols()) {
2632  CollectInheritedProtocols(Proto, Protocols);
2633  }
2634 
2635  // Categories of this Interface.
2636  for (const auto *Cat : OI->visible_categories())
2637  CollectInheritedProtocols(Cat, Protocols);
2638 
2639  if (ObjCInterfaceDecl *SD = OI->getSuperClass())
2640  while (SD) {
2641  CollectInheritedProtocols(SD, Protocols);
2642  SD = SD->getSuperClass();
2643  }
2644  } else if (const auto *OC = dyn_cast<ObjCCategoryDecl>(CDecl)) {
2645  for (auto *Proto : OC->protocols()) {
2646  CollectInheritedProtocols(Proto, Protocols);
2647  }
2648  } else if (const auto *OP = dyn_cast<ObjCProtocolDecl>(CDecl)) {
2649  // Insert the protocol.
2650  if (!Protocols.insert(
2651  const_cast<ObjCProtocolDecl *>(OP->getCanonicalDecl())).second)
2652  return;
2653 
2654  for (auto *Proto : OP->protocols())
2655  CollectInheritedProtocols(Proto, Protocols);
2656  }
2657 }
2658 
2659 static bool unionHasUniqueObjectRepresentations(const ASTContext &Context,
2660  const RecordDecl *RD) {
2661  assert(RD->isUnion() && "Must be union type");
2662  CharUnits UnionSize = Context.getTypeSizeInChars(RD->getTypeForDecl());
2663 
2664  for (const auto *Field : RD->fields()) {
2665  if (!Context.hasUniqueObjectRepresentations(Field->getType()))
2666  return false;
2667  CharUnits FieldSize = Context.getTypeSizeInChars(Field->getType());
2668  if (FieldSize != UnionSize)
2669  return false;
2670  }
2671  return !RD->field_empty();
2672 }

2674 static int64_t getSubobjectOffset(const FieldDecl *Field,
2675  const ASTContext &Context,
2676  const clang::ASTRecordLayout & /*Layout*/) {
2677  return Context.getFieldOffset(Field);
2678 }
2679 
2680 static int64_t getSubobjectOffset(const CXXRecordDecl *RD,
2681  const ASTContext &Context,
2682  const clang::ASTRecordLayout &Layout) {
2683  return Context.toBits(Layout.getBaseClassOffset(RD));
2684 }
2685 
2686 static llvm::Optional<int64_t>
2687 structHasUniqueObjectRepresentations(const ASTContext &Context,
2688  const RecordDecl *RD);
2689 
2690 static llvm::Optional<int64_t>
2691 getSubobjectSizeInBits(const FieldDecl *Field, const ASTContext &Context) {
2692  if (Field->getType()->isRecordType()) {
2693  const RecordDecl *RD = Field->getType()->getAsRecordDecl();
2694  if (!RD->isUnion())
2695  return structHasUniqueObjectRepresentations(Context, RD);
2696  }
2697  if (!Field->getType()->isReferenceType() &&
2698  !Context.hasUniqueObjectRepresentations(Field->getType()))
2699  return llvm::None;
2700 
2701  int64_t FieldSizeInBits =
2702  Context.toBits(Context.getTypeSizeInChars(Field->getType()));
2703  if (Field->isBitField()) {
2704  int64_t BitfieldSize = Field->getBitWidthValue(Context);
2705  if (BitfieldSize > FieldSizeInBits)
2706  return llvm::None;
2707  FieldSizeInBits = BitfieldSize;
2708  }
2709  return FieldSizeInBits;
2710 }
2711 
2712 static llvm::Optional<int64_t>
2713 getSubobjectSizeInBits(const CXXRecordDecl *RD, const ASTContext &Context) {
2714  return structHasUniqueObjectRepresentations(Context, RD);
2715 }
2716 
2717 template <typename RangeT>
2718 static llvm::Optional<int64_t> structSubobjectsHaveUniqueObjectRepresentations(
2719  const RangeT &Subobjects, int64_t CurOffsetInBits,
2720  const ASTContext &Context, const clang::ASTRecordLayout &Layout) {
2721  for (const auto *Subobject : Subobjects) {
2722  llvm::Optional<int64_t> SizeInBits =
2723  getSubobjectSizeInBits(Subobject, Context);
2724  if (!SizeInBits)
2725  return llvm::None;
2726  if (*SizeInBits != 0) {
2727  int64_t Offset = getSubobjectOffset(Subobject, Context, Layout);
2728  if (Offset != CurOffsetInBits)
2729  return llvm::None;
2730  CurOffsetInBits += *SizeInBits;
2731  }
2732  }
2733  return CurOffsetInBits;
2734 }
2735 
2736 static llvm::Optional<int64_t>
2737 structHasUniqueObjectRepresentations(const ASTContext &Context,
2738  const RecordDecl *RD) {
2739  assert(!RD->isUnion() && "Must be struct/class type");
2740  const auto &Layout = Context.getASTRecordLayout(RD);
2741 
2742  int64_t CurOffsetInBits = 0;
2743  if (const auto *ClassDecl = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RD)) {
2744  if (ClassDecl->isDynamicClass())
2745  return llvm::None;
2746 
2747  SmallVector<CXXRecordDecl *, 4> Bases;
2748  for (const auto &Base : ClassDecl->bases()) {
2749  // Empty types can be inherited from, and non-empty types can potentially
2750  // have tail padding, so just make sure there isn't an error.
2751  Bases.emplace_back(Base.getType()->getAsCXXRecordDecl());
2752  }
2753 
2754  llvm::sort(Bases, [&](const CXXRecordDecl *L, const CXXRecordDecl *R) {
2755  return Layout.getBaseClassOffset(L) < Layout.getBaseClassOffset(R);
2756  });
2757 
2758  llvm::Optional<int64_t> OffsetAfterBases =
2759  structSubobjectsHaveUniqueObjectRepresentations(Bases, CurOffsetInBits,
2760  Context, Layout);
2761  if (!OffsetAfterBases)
2762  return llvm::None;
2763  CurOffsetInBits = *OffsetAfterBases;
2764  }
2765 
2766  llvm::Optional<int64_t> OffsetAfterFields =
2767  structSubobjectsHaveUniqueObjectRepresentations(
2768  RD->fields(), CurOffsetInBits, Context, Layout);
2769  if (!OffsetAfterFields)
2770  return llvm::None;
2771  CurOffsetInBits = *OffsetAfterFields;
2772 
2773  return CurOffsetInBits;
2774 }
2775 
2776 bool ASTContext::hasUniqueObjectRepresentations(QualType Ty) const {
2777  // C++17 [meta.unary.prop]:
2778  // The predicate condition for a template specialization
2779  // has_unique_object_representations<T> shall be
2780  // satisfied if and only if:
2781  // (9.1) - T is trivially copyable, and
2782  // (9.2) - any two objects of type T with the same value have the same
2783  // object representation, where two objects
2784  // of array or non-union class type are considered to have the same value
2785  // if their respective sequences of
2786  // direct subobjects have the same values, and two objects of union type
2787  // are considered to have the same
2788  // value if they have the same active member and the corresponding members
2789  // have the same value.
2790  // The set of scalar types for which this condition holds is
2791  // implementation-defined. [ Note: If a type has padding
2792  // bits, the condition does not hold; otherwise, the condition holds true
2793  // for unsigned integral types. -- end note ]
2794  assert(!Ty.isNull() && "Null QualType sent to unique object rep check");
2795 
2796  // Arrays are unique only if their element type is unique.
2797  if (Ty->isArrayType())
2798  return hasUniqueObjectRepresentations(getBaseElementType(Ty));
2799 
2800  // (9.1) - T is trivially copyable...
2801  if (!Ty.isTriviallyCopyableType(*this))
2802  return false;
2803 
2804  // All integrals and enums are unique.
2805  if (Ty->isIntegralOrEnumerationType())
2806  return true;
2807 
2808  // All other pointers are unique.
2809  if (Ty->isPointerType())
2810  return true;
2811 
2812  if (Ty->isMemberPointerType()) {
2813  const auto *MPT = Ty->getAs<MemberPointerType>();
2814  return !ABI->getMemberPointerInfo(MPT).HasPadding;
2815  }
2816 
2817  if (Ty->isRecordType()) {
2818  const RecordDecl *Record = Ty->castAs<RecordType>()->getDecl();
2819 
2820  if (Record->isInvalidDecl())
2821  return false;
2822 
2823  if (Record->isUnion())
2824  return unionHasUniqueObjectRepresentations(*this, Record);
2825 
2826  Optional<int64_t> StructSize =
2827  structHasUniqueObjectRepresentations(*this, Record);
2828 
2829  return StructSize &&
2830  StructSize.getValue() == static_cast<int64_t>(getTypeSize(Ty));
2831  }
2832 
2833  // FIXME: More cases to handle here (list by rsmith):
2834  // vectors (careful about, eg, vector of 3 foo)
2835  // _Complex int and friends
2836  // _Atomic T
2837  // Obj-C block pointers
2838  // Obj-C object pointers
2839  // and perhaps OpenCL's various builtin types (pipe, sampler_t, event_t,
2840  // clk_event_t, queue_t, reserve_id_t)
2841  // There're also Obj-C class types and the Obj-C selector type, but I think it
2842  // makes sense for those to return false here.
2843 
2844  return false;
2845 }
2846 
2847 unsigned ASTContext::CountNonClassIvars(const ObjCInterfaceDecl *OI) const {
2848  unsigned count = 0;
2849  // Count ivars declared in class extension.
2850  for (const auto *Ext : OI->known_extensions())
2851  count += Ext->ivar_size();
2852 
2853  // Count ivar defined in this class's implementation. This
2854  // includes synthesized ivars.
2855  if (ObjCImplementationDecl *ImplDecl = OI->getImplementation())
2856  count += ImplDecl->ivar_size();
2857 
2858  return count;
2859 }
2860 
2861 bool ASTContext::isSentinelNullExpr(const Expr *E) {
2862  if (!E)
2863  return false;
2864 
2865  // nullptr_t is always treated as null.
2866  if (E->getType()->isNullPtrType()) return true;
2867 
2868  if (E->getType()->isAnyPointerType() &&
2869  E->IgnoreParenCasts()->isNullPointerConstant(*this,
2870  Expr::NPC_ValueDependentIsNull))
2871  return true;
2872 
2873  // Unfortunately, __null has type 'int'.
2874  if (isa<GNUNullExpr>(E)) return true;
2875 
2876  return false;
2877 }

2924 const ObjCInterfaceDecl *ASTContext::getObjContainingInterface(
2925  const NamedDecl *ND) const {

2992 
2993 QualType
2994 ASTContext::getExtQualType(const Type *baseType, Qualifiers quals) const {
2995  unsigned fastQuals = quals.getFastQualifiers();
2996  quals.removeFastQualifiers();
2997 
2998  // Check if we've already instantiated this type.
2999  llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
3000  ExtQuals::Profile(ID, baseType, quals);
3001  void *insertPos = nullptr;
3002  if (ExtQuals *eq = ExtQualNodes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, insertPos)) {
3003  assert(eq->getQualifiers() == quals);
3004  return QualType(eq, fastQuals);
3005  }
3006 
3007  // If the base type is not canonical, make the appropriate canonical type.
3008  QualType canon;
3009  if (!baseType->isCanonicalUnqualified()) {
3010  SplitQualType canonSplit = baseType->getCanonicalTypeInternal().split();
3011  canonSplit.Quals.addConsistentQualifiers(quals);
3012  canon = getExtQualType(canonSplit.Ty, canonSplit.Quals);
3013 
3014  // Re-find the insert position.
3015  (void) ExtQualNodes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, insertPos);
3016  }
3017 
3018  auto *eq = new (*this, TypeAlignment) ExtQuals(baseType, canon, quals);
3019  ExtQualNodes.InsertNode(eq, insertPos);
3020  return QualType(eq, fastQuals);
3021 }
3022 
3023 QualType ASTContext::getAddrSpaceQualType(QualType T,
3024  LangAS AddressSpace) const {
3025  QualType CanT = getCanonicalType(T);
3026  if (CanT.getAddressSpace() == AddressSpace)
3027  return T;
3028 
3029  // If we are composing extended qualifiers together, merge together
3030  // into one ExtQuals node.
3031  QualifierCollector Quals;
3032  const Type *TypeNode = Quals.strip(T);
3033 
3034  // If this type already has an address space specified, it cannot get
3035  // another one.
3036  assert(!Quals.hasAddressSpace() &&
3037  "Type cannot be in multiple addr spaces!");
3038  Quals.addAddressSpace(AddressSpace);
3039 
3040  return getExtQualType(TypeNode, Quals);
3041 }
3042 
3043 QualType ASTContext::removeAddrSpaceQualType(QualType T) const {
3044  // If the type is not qualified with an address space, just return it
3045  // immediately.
3046  if (!T.hasAddressSpace())
3047  return T;
3048 
3049  // If we are composing extended qualifiers together, merge together
3050  // into one ExtQuals node.
3051  QualifierCollector Quals;
3052  const Type *TypeNode;
3053 
3054  while (T.hasAddressSpace()) {
3055  TypeNode = Quals.strip(T);
3056 
3057  // If the type no longer has an address space after stripping qualifiers,
3058  // jump out.
3059  if (!QualType(TypeNode, 0).hasAddressSpace())
3060  break;
3061 
3062  // There might be sugar in the way. Strip it and try again.
3063  T = T.getSingleStepDesugaredType(*this);
3064  }
3065 
3066  Quals.removeAddressSpace();
3067 
3068  // Removal of the address space can mean there are no longer any
3069  // non-fast qualifiers, so creating an ExtQualType isn't possible (asserts)
3070  // or required.
3071  if (Quals.hasNonFastQualifiers())
3072  return getExtQualType(TypeNode, Quals);
3073  else
3074  return QualType(TypeNode, Quals.getFastQualifiers());
3075 }
3076 
3077 QualType ASTContext::getObjCGCQualType(QualType T,
3078  Qualifiers::GC GCAttr) const {
3079  QualType CanT = getCanonicalType(T);
3080  if (CanT.getObjCGCAttr() == GCAttr)
3081  return T;
3082 
3083  if (const auto *ptr = T->getAs<PointerType>()) {
3084  QualType Pointee = ptr->getPointeeType();
3085  if (Pointee->isAnyPointerType()) {
3086  QualType ResultType = getObjCGCQualType(Pointee, GCAttr);
3087  return getPointerType(ResultType);
3088  }
3089  }
3090 
3091  // If we are composing extended qualifiers together, merge together
3092  // into one ExtQuals node.
3093  QualifierCollector Quals;
3094  const Type *TypeNode = Quals.strip(T);
3095 
3096  // If this type already has an ObjCGC specified, it cannot get
3097  // another one.
3098  assert(!Quals.hasObjCGCAttr() &&
3099  "Type cannot have multiple ObjCGCs!");
3100  Quals.addObjCGCAttr(GCAttr);
3101 
3102  return getExtQualType(TypeNode, Quals);
3103 }
3104 
3105 QualType ASTContext::removePtrSizeAddrSpace(QualType T) const {
3106  if (const PointerType *Ptr = T->getAs<PointerType>()) {
3107  QualType Pointee = Ptr->getPointeeType();
3108  if (isPtrSizeAddressSpace(Pointee.getAddressSpace())) {
3109  return getPointerType(removeAddrSpaceQualType(Pointee));
3110  }
3111  }
3112  return T;
3113 }
3114 
3115 const FunctionType *ASTContext::adjustFunctionType(const FunctionType *T,
3116  FunctionType::ExtInfo Info) {
3117  if (T->getExtInfo() == Info)
3118  return T;
3119 
3120  QualType Result;
3121  if (const auto *FNPT = dyn_cast<FunctionNoProtoType>(T)) {
3122  Result = getFunctionNoProtoType(FNPT->getReturnType(), Info);
3123  } else {
3124  const auto *FPT = cast<FunctionProtoType>(T);
3125  FunctionProtoType::ExtProtoInfo EPI = FPT->getExtProtoInfo();
3126  EPI.ExtInfo = Info;
3127  Result = getFunctionType(FPT->getReturnType(), FPT->getParamTypes(), EPI);
3128  }
3129 
3130  return cast<FunctionType>(Result.getTypePtr());
3131 }
3132 
3133 void ASTContext::adjustDeducedFunctionResultType(FunctionDecl *FD,
3134  QualType ResultType) {
3135  FD = FD->getMostRecentDecl();
3136  while (true) {
3137  const auto *FPT = FD->getType()->castAs<FunctionProtoType>();
3138  FunctionProtoType::ExtProtoInfo EPI = FPT->getExtProtoInfo();
3139  FD->setType(getFunctionType(ResultType, FPT->getParamTypes(), EPI));
3140  if (FunctionDecl *Next = FD->getPreviousDecl())
3141  FD = Next;
3142  else
3143  break;
3144  }
3145  if (ASTMutationListener *L = getASTMutationListener())
3146  L->DeducedReturnType(FD, ResultType);
3147 }

3149 /// Get a function type and produce the equivalent function type with the
3150 /// specified exception specification. Type sugar that can be present on a
3151 /// declaration of a function with an exception specification is permitted
3152 /// and preserved. Other type sugar (for instance, typedefs) is not.
3153 QualType ASTContext::getFunctionTypeWithExceptionSpec(
3154  QualType Orig, const FunctionProtoType::ExceptionSpecInfo &ESI) {
3155  // Might have some parens.
3156  if (const auto *PT = dyn_cast<ParenType>(Orig))
3157  return getParenType(
3158  getFunctionTypeWithExceptionSpec(PT->getInnerType(), ESI));
3159 
3160  // Might be wrapped in a macro qualified type.
3161  if (const auto *MQT = dyn_cast<MacroQualifiedType>(Orig))
3162  return getMacroQualifiedType(
3163  getFunctionTypeWithExceptionSpec(MQT->getUnderlyingType(), ESI),
3164  MQT->getMacroIdentifier());
3165 
3166  // Might have a calling-convention attribute.
3167  if (const auto *AT = dyn_cast<AttributedType>(Orig))
3168  return getAttributedType(
3169  AT->getAttrKind(),
3170  getFunctionTypeWithExceptionSpec(AT->getModifiedType(), ESI),
3171  getFunctionTypeWithExceptionSpec(AT->getEquivalentType(), ESI));
3172 
3173  // Anything else must be a function type. Rebuild it with the new exception
3174  // specification.
3175  const auto *Proto = Orig->castAs<FunctionProtoType>();
3176  return getFunctionType(
3177  Proto->getReturnType(), Proto->getParamTypes(),
3178  Proto->getExtProtoInfo().withExceptionSpec(ESI));
3179 }
3180 
3181 bool ASTContext::hasSameFunctionTypeIgnoringExceptionSpec(QualType T,
3182  QualType U) {
3183  return hasSameType(T, U) ||
3184  (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus17 &&
3185  hasSameType(getFunctionTypeWithExceptionSpec(T, EST_None),
3186  getFunctionTypeWithExceptionSpec(U, EST_None)));
3187 }
3188 
3189 QualType ASTContext::getFunctionTypeWithoutPtrSizes(QualType T) {
3190  if (const auto *Proto = T->getAs<FunctionProtoType>()) {
3191  QualType RetTy = removePtrSizeAddrSpace(Proto->getReturnType());
3192  SmallVector<QualType, 16> Args(Proto->param_types());
3193  for (unsigned i = 0, n = Args.size(); i != n; ++i)
3194  Args[i] = removePtrSizeAddrSpace(Args[i]);
3195  return getFunctionType(RetTy, Args, Proto->getExtProtoInfo());
3196  }
3197 
3198  if (const FunctionNoProtoType *Proto = T->getAs<FunctionNoProtoType>()) {
3199  QualType RetTy = removePtrSizeAddrSpace(Proto->getReturnType());
3200  return getFunctionNoProtoType(RetTy, Proto->getExtInfo());
3201  }
3202 
3203  return T;
3204 }
3205 
3206 bool ASTContext::hasSameFunctionTypeIgnoringPtrSizes(QualType T, QualType U) {
3207  return hasSameType(T, U) ||
3208  hasSameType(getFunctionTypeWithoutPtrSizes(T),
3209  getFunctionTypeWithoutPtrSizes(U));
3210 }
3211 
3212 void ASTContext::adjustExceptionSpec(
3213  FunctionDecl *FD, const FunctionProtoType::ExceptionSpecInfo &ESI,
3214  bool AsWritten) {
3215  // Update the type.
3216  QualType Updated =
3217  getFunctionTypeWithExceptionSpec(FD->getType(), ESI);
3218  FD->setType(Updated);
3219 
3220  if (!AsWritten)
3221  return;
3222 
3223  // Update the type in the type source information too.
3224  if (TypeSourceInfo *TSInfo = FD->getTypeSourceInfo()) {
3225  // If the type and the type-as-written differ, we may need to update
3226  // the type-as-written too.
3227  if (TSInfo->getType() != FD->getType())
3228  Updated = getFunctionTypeWithExceptionSpec(TSInfo->getType(), ESI);
3229 
3230  // FIXME: When we get proper type location information for exceptions,
3231  // we'll also have to rebuild the TypeSourceInfo. For now, we just patch
3232  // up the TypeSourceInfo;
3233  assert(TypeLoc::getFullDataSizeForType(Updated) ==
3234  TypeLoc::getFullDataSizeForType(TSInfo->getType()) &&
3235  "TypeLoc size mismatch from updating exception specification");
3236  TSInfo->overrideType(Updated);
3237  }
3238 }

3240 /// getComplexType - Return the uniqued reference to the type for a complex
3241 /// number with the specified element type.
3242 QualType ASTContext::getComplexType(QualType T) const {
3243  // Unique pointers, to guarantee there is only one pointer of a particular
3244  // structure.
3245  llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
3246  ComplexType::Profile(ID, T);
3247 
3248  void *InsertPos = nullptr;
3249  if (ComplexType *CT = ComplexTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos))
3250  return QualType(CT, 0);
3251 
3252  // If the pointee type isn't canonical, this won't be a canonical type either,
3253  // so fill in the canonical type field.
3254  QualType Canonical;
3255  if (!T.isCanonical()) {
3256  Canonical = getComplexType(getCanonicalType(T));
3257 
3258  // Get the new insert position for the node we care about.
3259  ComplexType *NewIP = ComplexTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
3260  assert(!NewIP && "Shouldn't be in the map!"); (void)NewIP;
3261  }
3262  auto *New = new (*this, TypeAlignment) ComplexType(T, Canonical);
3263  Types.push_back(New);
3264  ComplexTypes.InsertNode(New, InsertPos);
3265  return QualType(New, 0);
3266 }

3296 QualType ASTContext::getAdjustedType(QualType Orig, QualType New) const {

3316 
3317 QualType ASTContext::getDecayedType(QualType T) const {
3318  assert((T->isArrayType() || T->isFunctionType()) && "T does not decay");
3319 
3320  QualType Decayed;
3321 
3322  // C99 6.7.5.3p7:
3323  // A declaration of a parameter as "array of type" shall be
3324  // adjusted to "qualified pointer to type", where the type
3325  // qualifiers (if any) are those specified within the [ and ] of
3326  // the array type derivation.
3327  if (T->isArrayType())
3328  Decayed = getArrayDecayedType(T);
3329 
3330  // C99 6.7.5.3p8:
3331  // A declaration of a parameter as "function returning type"
3332  // shall be adjusted to "pointer to function returning type", as
3333  // in 6.3.2.1.
3334  if (T->isFunctionType())
3335  Decayed = getPointerType(T);
3336 
3337  llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
3338  AdjustedType::Profile(ID, T, Decayed);
3339  void *InsertPos = nullptr;
3340  AdjustedType *AT = AdjustedTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
3341  if (AT)
3342  return QualType(AT, 0);
3343 
3344  QualType Canonical = getCanonicalType(Decayed);
3345 
3346  // Get the new insert position for the node we care about.
3347  AT = AdjustedTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
3348  assert(!AT && "Shouldn't be in the map!");
3349 
3350  AT = new (*this, TypeAlignment) DecayedType(T, Decayed, Canonical);
3351  Types.push_back(AT);
3352  AdjustedTypes.InsertNode(AT, InsertPos);
3353  return QualType(AT, 0);
3354 }

3391  assert((!T->isPlaceholderType() ||

3400  void *InsertPos = nullptr;

3402  LValueReferenceTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos))

3406

3496 /// getConstantArrayType - Return the unique reference to the type for an
3497 /// array of the specified element type.
3498 QualType ASTContext::getConstantArrayType(QualType EltTy,
3499  const llvm::APInt &ArySizeIn,
3500  const Expr *SizeExpr,
3501  ArrayType::ArraySizeModifier ASM,
3502  unsigned IndexTypeQuals) const {
3503  assert((EltTy->isDependentType() ||
3504  EltTy->isIncompleteType() || EltTy->isConstantSizeType()) &&
3505  "Constant array of VLAs is illegal!");
3506 
3507  // We only need the size as part of the type if it's instantiation-dependent.
3508  if (SizeExpr && !SizeExpr->isInstantiationDependent())
3509  SizeExpr = nullptr;
3510 
3511  // Convert the array size into a canonical width matching the pointer size for
3512  // the target.
3513  llvm::APInt ArySize(ArySizeIn);
3514  ArySize = ArySize.zextOrTrunc(Target->getMaxPointerWidth());
3515 
3516  llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
3517  ConstantArrayType::Profile(ID, *this, EltTy, ArySize, SizeExpr, ASM,
3518  IndexTypeQuals);
3519 
3520  void *InsertPos = nullptr;
3521  if (ConstantArrayType *ATP =
3522  ConstantArrayTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos))
3523  return QualType(ATP, 0);
3524 
3525  // If the element type isn't canonical or has qualifiers, or the array bound
3526  // is instantiation-dependent, this won't be a canonical type either, so fill
3527  // in the canonical type field.
3528  QualType Canon;
3529  if (!EltTy.isCanonical() || EltTy.hasLocalQualifiers() || SizeExpr) {
3530  SplitQualType canonSplit = getCanonicalType(EltTy).split();
3531  Canon = getConstantArrayType(QualType(canonSplit.Ty, 0), ArySize, nullptr,
3532  ASM, IndexTypeQuals);
3533  Canon = getQualifiedType(Canon, canonSplit.Quals);
3534 
3535  // Get the new insert position for the node we care about.
3536  ConstantArrayType *NewIP =
3537  ConstantArrayTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
3538  assert(!NewIP && "Shouldn't be in the map!"); (void)NewIP;
3539  }
3540 
3541  void *Mem = Allocate(
3542  ConstantArrayType::totalSizeToAlloc<const Expr *>(SizeExpr ? 1 : 0),
3543  TypeAlignment);
3544  auto *New = new (Mem)
3545  ConstantArrayType(EltTy, Canon, ArySize, SizeExpr, ASM, IndexTypeQuals);
3546  ConstantArrayTypes.InsertNode(New, InsertPos);
3547  Types.push_back(New);
3548  return QualType(New, 0);
3549 }
3550 
3551 /// getVariableArrayDecayedType - Turns the given type, which may be
3552 /// variably-modified, into the corresponding type with all the known
3553 /// sizes replaced with [*].
3554 QualType ASTContext::getVariableArrayDecayedType(QualType type) const {
3555  // Vastly most common case.
3556  if (!type->isVariablyModifiedType()) return type;
3557 
3558  QualType result;
3559 
3560  SplitQualType split = type.getSplitDesugaredType();
3561  const Type *ty = split.Ty;
3562  switch (ty->getTypeClass()) {
3563 #define TYPE(Class, Base)
3564 #define ABSTRACT_TYPE(Class, Base)
3565 #define NON_CANONICAL_TYPE(Class, Base) case Type::Class:
3566 #include "clang/AST/TypeNodes.inc"
3567  llvm_unreachable("didn't desugar past all non-canonical types?");
3568 
3569  // These types should never be variably-modified.
3570  case Type::Builtin:
3571  case Type::Complex:
3572  case Type::Vector:
3573  case Type::DependentVector:
3574  case Type::ExtVector:
3575  case Type::DependentSizedExtVector:
3576  case Type::ConstantMatrix:
3577  case Type::DependentSizedMatrix:
3578  case Type::DependentAddressSpace:
3579  case Type::ObjCObject:
3580  case Type::ObjCInterface:
3581  case Type::ObjCObjectPointer:
3582  case Type::Record:
3583  case Type::Enum:
3584  case Type::UnresolvedUsing:
3585  case Type::TypeOfExpr:
3586  case Type::TypeOf:
3587  case Type::Decltype:
3588  case Type::UnaryTransform:
3589  case Type::DependentName:
3590  case Type::InjectedClassName:
3591  case Type::TemplateSpecialization:
3592  case Type::DependentTemplateSpecialization:
3593  case Type::TemplateTypeParm:
3594  case Type::SubstTemplateTypeParmPack:
3595  case Type::Auto:
3596  case Type::DeducedTemplateSpecialization:
3597  case Type::PackExpansion:
3598  case Type::BitInt:
3599  case Type::DependentBitInt:
3600  llvm_unreachable("type should never be variably-modified");
3601 
3602  // These types can be variably-modified but should never need to
3603  // further decay.
3604  case Type::FunctionNoProto:
3605  case Type::FunctionProto:
3606  case Type::BlockPointer:
3607  case Type::MemberPointer:
3608  case Type::Pipe:
3609  return type;
3610 
3611  // These types can be variably-modified. All these modifications
3612  // preserve structure except as noted by comments.
3613  // TODO: if we ever care about optimizing VLAs, there are no-op
3614  // optimizations available here.
3615  case Type::Pointer:
3616  result = getPointerType(getVariableArrayDecayedType(
3617  cast<PointerType>(ty)->getPointeeType()));
3618  break;
3619 
3620  case Type::LValueReference: {
3621  const auto *lv = cast<LValueReferenceType>(ty);
3622  result = getLValueReferenceType(
3623  getVariableArrayDecayedType(lv->getPointeeType()),
3624  lv->isSpelledAsLValue());
3625  break;
3626  }
3627 
3628  case Type::RValueReference: {
3629  const auto *lv = cast<RValueReferenceType>(ty);
3630  result = getRValueReferenceType(
3631  getVariableArrayDecayedType(lv->getPointeeType()));
3632  break;
3633  }
3634 
3635  case Type::Atomic: {
3636  const auto *at = cast<AtomicType>(ty);
3637  result = getAtomicType(getVariableArrayDecayedType(at->getValueType()));
3638  break;
3639  }
3640 
3641  case Type::ConstantArray: {
3642  const auto *cat = cast<ConstantArrayType>(ty);
3643  result = getConstantArrayType(
3644  getVariableArrayDecayedType(cat->getElementType()),
3645  cat->getSize(),
3646  cat->getSizeExpr(),
3647  cat->getSizeModifier(),
3648  cat->getIndexTypeCVRQualifiers());
3649  break;
3650  }
3651 
3652  case Type::DependentSizedArray: {
3653  const auto *dat = cast<DependentSizedArrayType>(ty);
3654  result = getDependentSizedArrayType(
3655  getVariableArrayDecayedType(dat->getElementType()),
3656  dat->getSizeExpr(),
3657  dat->getSizeModifier(),
3658  dat->getIndexTypeCVRQualifiers(),
3659  dat->getBracketsRange());
3660  break;
3661  }
3662 
3663  // Turn incomplete types into [*] types.
3664  case Type::IncompleteArray: {
3665  const auto *iat = cast<IncompleteArrayType>(ty);
3666  result = getVariableArrayType(
3667  getVariableArrayDecayedType(iat->getElementType()),
3668  /*size*/ nullptr,
3669  ArrayType::Normal,
3670  iat->getIndexTypeCVRQualifiers(),
3671  SourceRange());
3672  break;
3673  }
3674 
3675  // Turn VLA types into [*] types.
3676  case Type::VariableArray: {
3677  const auto *vat = cast<VariableArrayType>(ty);
3678  result = getVariableArrayType(
3679  getVariableArrayDecayedType(vat->getElementType()),
3680  /*size*/ nullptr,
3681  ArrayType::Star,
3682  vat->getIndexTypeCVRQualifiers(),
3683  vat->getBracketsRange());
3684  break;
3685  }
3686  }
3687 
3688  // Apply the top-level qualifiers from the original.
3689  return getQualifiedType(result, split.Quals);
3690 }
3691 
3692 /// getVariableArrayType - Returns a non-unique reference to the type for a
3693 /// variable array of the specified element type.
3694 QualType ASTContext::getVariableArrayType(QualType EltTy,
3695  Expr *NumElts,
3696  ArrayType::ArraySizeModifier ASM,
3697  unsigned IndexTypeQuals,
3698  SourceRange Brackets) const {
3699  // Since we don't unique expressions, it isn't possible to unique VLA's
3700  // that have an expression provided for their size.
3701  QualType Canon;
3702 
3703  // Be sure to pull qualifiers off the element type.
3704  if (!EltTy.isCanonical() || EltTy.hasLocalQualifiers()) {
3705  SplitQualType canonSplit = getCanonicalType(EltTy).split();
3706  Canon = getVariableArrayType(QualType(canonSplit.Ty, 0), NumElts, ASM,
3707  IndexTypeQuals, Brackets);
3708  Canon = getQualifiedType(Canon, canonSplit.Quals);
3709  }
3710 
3711  auto *New = new (*this, TypeAlignment)
3712  VariableArrayType(EltTy, Canon, NumElts, ASM, IndexTypeQuals, Brackets);
3713 
3714  VariableArrayTypes.push_back(New);
3715  Types.push_back(New);
3716  return QualType(New, 0);
3717 }
3718 
3719 /// getDependentSizedArrayType - Returns a non-unique reference to
3720 /// the type for a dependently-sized array of the specified element
3721 /// type.
3722 QualType ASTContext::getDependentSizedArrayType(QualType elementType,
3723  Expr *numElements,
3724  ArrayType::ArraySizeModifier ASM,
3725  unsigned elementTypeQuals,
3726  SourceRange brackets) const {
3727  assert((!numElements || numElements->isTypeDependent() ||
3728  numElements->isValueDependent()) &&
3729  "Size must be type- or value-dependent!");
3730 
3731  // Dependently-sized array types that do not have a specified number
3732  // of elements will have their sizes deduced from a dependent
3733  // initializer. We do no canonicalization here at all, which is okay
3734  // because they can't be used in most locations.
3735  if (!numElements) {
3736  auto *newType
3737  = new (*this, TypeAlignment)
3738  DependentSizedArrayType(*this, elementType, QualType(),
3739  numElements, ASM, elementTypeQuals,
3740  brackets);
3741  Types.push_back(newType);
3742  return QualType(newType, 0);
3743  }
3744 
3745  // Otherwise, we actually build a new type every time, but we
3746  // also build a canonical type.
3747 
3748  SplitQualType canonElementType = getCanonicalType(elementType).split();
3749 
3750  void *insertPos = nullptr;
3751  llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
3752  DependentSizedArrayType::Profile(ID, *this,
3753  QualType(canonElementType.Ty, 0),
3754  ASM, elementTypeQuals, numElements);
3755 
3756  // Look for an existing type with these properties.
3757  DependentSizedArrayType *canonTy =
3758  DependentSizedArrayTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, insertPos);
3759 
3760  // If we don't have one, build one.
3761  if (!canonTy) {
3762  canonTy = new (*this, TypeAlignment)
3763  DependentSizedArrayType(*this, QualType(canonElementType.Ty, 0),
3764  QualType(), numElements, ASM, elementTypeQuals,
3765  brackets);
3766  DependentSizedArrayTypes.InsertNode(canonTy, insertPos);
3767  Types.push_back(canonTy);
3768  }
3769 
3770  // Apply qualifiers from the element type to the array.
3771  QualType canon = getQualifiedType(QualType(canonTy,0),
3772  canonElementType.Quals);
3773 
3774  // If we didn't need extra canonicalization for the element type or the size
3775  // expression, then just use that as our result.
3776  if (QualType(canonElementType.Ty, 0) == elementType &&
3777  canonTy->getSizeExpr() == numElements)
3778  return canon;
3779 
3780  // Otherwise, we need to build a type which follows the spelling
3781  // of the element type.
3782  auto *sugaredType
3783  = new (*this, TypeAlignment)
3784  DependentSizedArrayType(*this, elementType, canon, numElements,
3785  ASM, elementTypeQuals, brackets);
3786  Types.push_back(sugaredType);
3787  return QualType(sugaredType, 0);
3788 }
3789 
3790 QualType ASTContext::getIncompleteArrayType(QualType elementType,
3791  ArrayType::ArraySizeModifier ASM,
3792  unsigned elementTypeQuals) const {
3793  llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
3794  IncompleteArrayType::Profile(ID, elementType, ASM, elementTypeQuals);
3795 
3796  void *insertPos = nullptr;
3797  if (IncompleteArrayType *iat =
3798  IncompleteArrayTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, insertPos))
3799  return QualType(iat, 0);
3800 
3801  // If the element type isn't canonical, this won't be a canonical type
3802  // either, so fill in the canonical type field. We also have to pull
3803  // qualifiers off the element type.
3804  QualType canon;
3805 
3806  if (!elementType.isCanonical() || elementType.hasLocalQualifiers()) {
3807  SplitQualType canonSplit = getCanonicalType(elementType).split();
3808  canon = getIncompleteArrayType(QualType(canonSplit.Ty, 0),
3809  ASM, elementTypeQuals);
3810  canon = getQualifiedType(canon, canonSplit.Quals);
3811 
3812  // Get the new insert position for the node we care about.
3813  IncompleteArrayType *existing =
3814  IncompleteArrayTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, insertPos);
3815  assert(!existing && "Shouldn't be in the map!"); (void) existing;
3816  }
3817 
3818  auto *newType = new (*this, TypeAlignment)
3819  IncompleteArrayType(elementType, canon, ASM, elementTypeQuals);
3820 
3821  IncompleteArrayTypes.InsertNode(newType, insertPos);
3822  Types.push_back(newType);
3823  return QualType(newType, 0);
3824 }

3826 ASTContext::BuiltinVectorTypeInfo
3827 ASTContext::getBuiltinVectorTypeInfo(const BuiltinType *Ty) const {
3828 #define SVE_INT_ELTTY(BITS, ELTS, SIGNED, NUMVECTORS) \
3829  {getIntTypeForBitwidth(BITS, SIGNED), llvm::ElementCount::getScalable(ELTS), \
3830  NUMVECTORS};
3831 
3832 #define SVE_ELTTY(ELTTY, ELTS, NUMVECTORS) \
3833  {ELTTY, llvm::ElementCount::getScalable(ELTS), NUMVECTORS};
3834 
3835  switch (Ty->getKind()) {
3836  default:
3837  llvm_unreachable("Unsupported builtin vector type");
3838  case BuiltinType::SveInt8:
3839  return SVE_INT_ELTTY(8, 16, true, 1);
3840  case BuiltinType::SveUint8:
3841  return SVE_INT_ELTTY(8, 16, false, 1);
3842  case BuiltinType::SveInt8x2:
3843  return SVE_INT_ELTTY(8, 16, true, 2);
3844  case BuiltinType::SveUint8x2:
3845  return SVE_INT_ELTTY(8, 16, false, 2);
3846  case BuiltinType::SveInt8x3:
3847  return SVE_INT_ELTTY(8, 16, true, 3);
3848  case BuiltinType::SveUint8x3:
3849  return SVE_INT_ELTTY(8, 16, false, 3);
3850  case BuiltinType::SveInt8x4:
3851  return SVE_INT_ELTTY(8, 16, true, 4);
3852  case BuiltinType::SveUint8x4:
3853  return SVE_INT_ELTTY(8, 16, false, 4);
3854  case BuiltinType::SveInt16:
3855  return SVE_INT_ELTTY(16, 8, true, 1);
3856  case BuiltinType::SveUint16:
3857  return SVE_INT_ELTTY(16, 8, false, 1);
3858  case BuiltinType::SveInt16x2:
3859  return SVE_INT_ELTTY(16, 8, true, 2);
3860  case BuiltinType::SveUint16x2:
3861  return SVE_INT_ELTTY(16, 8, false, 2);
3862  case BuiltinType::SveInt16x3:
3863  return SVE_INT_ELTTY(16, 8, true, 3);
3864  case BuiltinType::SveUint16x3:
3865  return SVE_INT_ELTTY(16, 8, false, 3);
3866  case BuiltinType::SveInt16x4:
3867  return SVE_INT_ELTTY(16, 8, true, 4);
3868  case BuiltinType::SveUint16x4:
3869  return SVE_INT_ELTTY(16, 8, false, 4);
3870  case BuiltinType::SveInt32:
3871  return SVE_INT_ELTTY(32, 4, true, 1);
3872  case BuiltinType::SveUint32:
3873  return SVE_INT_ELTTY(32, 4, false, 1);
3874  case BuiltinType::SveInt32x2:
3875  return SVE_INT_ELTTY(32, 4, true, 2);
3876  case BuiltinType::SveUint32x2:
3877  return SVE_INT_ELTTY(32, 4, false, 2);
3878  case BuiltinType::SveInt32x3:
3879  return SVE_INT_ELTTY(32, 4, true, 3);
3880  case BuiltinType::SveUint32x3:
3881  return SVE_INT_ELTTY(32, 4, false, 3);
3882  case BuiltinType::SveInt32x4:
3883  return SVE_INT_ELTTY(32, 4, true, 4);
3884  case BuiltinType::SveUint32x4:
3885  return SVE_INT_ELTTY(32, 4, false, 4);
3886  case BuiltinType::SveInt64:
3887  return SVE_INT_ELTTY(64, 2, true, 1);
3888  case BuiltinType::SveUint64:
3889  return SVE_INT_ELTTY(64, 2, false, 1);
3890  case BuiltinType::SveInt64x2:
3891  return SVE_INT_ELTTY(64, 2, true, 2);
3892  case BuiltinType::SveUint64x2:
3893  return SVE_INT_ELTTY(64, 2, false, 2);
3894  case BuiltinType::SveInt64x3:
3895  return SVE_INT_ELTTY(64, 2, true, 3);
3896  case BuiltinType::SveUint64x3:
3897  return SVE_INT_ELTTY(64, 2, false, 3);
3898  case BuiltinType::SveInt64x4:
3899  return SVE_INT_ELTTY(64, 2, true, 4);
3900  case BuiltinType::SveUint64x4:
3901  return SVE_INT_ELTTY(64, 2, false, 4);
3902  case BuiltinType::SveBool:
3903  return SVE_ELTTY(BoolTy, 16, 1);
3904  case BuiltinType::SveFloat16:
3905  return SVE_ELTTY(HalfTy, 8, 1);
3906  case BuiltinType::SveFloat16x2:
3907  return SVE_ELTTY(HalfTy, 8, 2);
3908  case BuiltinType::SveFloat16x3:
3909  return SVE_ELTTY(HalfTy, 8, 3);
3910  case BuiltinType::SveFloat16x4:
3911  return SVE_ELTTY(HalfTy, 8, 4);
3912  case BuiltinType::SveFloat32:
3913  return SVE_ELTTY(FloatTy, 4, 1);
3914  case BuiltinType::SveFloat32x2:
3915  return SVE_ELTTY(FloatTy, 4, 2);
3916  case BuiltinType::SveFloat32x3:
3917  return SVE_ELTTY(FloatTy, 4, 3);
3918  case BuiltinType::SveFloat32x4:
3919  return SVE_ELTTY(FloatTy, 4, 4);
3920  case BuiltinType::SveFloat64:
3921  return SVE_ELTTY(DoubleTy, 2, 1);
3922  case BuiltinType::SveFloat64x2:
3923  return SVE_ELTTY(DoubleTy, 2, 2);
3924  case BuiltinType::SveFloat64x3:
3925  return SVE_ELTTY(DoubleTy, 2, 3);
3926  case BuiltinType::SveFloat64x4:
3927  return SVE_ELTTY(DoubleTy, 2, 4);
3928  case BuiltinType::SveBFloat16:
3929  return SVE_ELTTY(BFloat16Ty, 8, 1);
3930  case BuiltinType::SveBFloat16x2:
3931  return SVE_ELTTY(BFloat16Ty, 8, 2);
3932  case BuiltinType::SveBFloat16x3:
3933  return SVE_ELTTY(BFloat16Ty, 8, 3);
3934  case BuiltinType::SveBFloat16x4:
3935  return SVE_ELTTY(BFloat16Ty, 8, 4);
3936 #define RVV_VECTOR_TYPE_INT(Name, Id, SingletonId, NumEls, ElBits, NF, \
3937  IsSigned) \
3938  case BuiltinType::Id: \
3939  return {getIntTypeForBitwidth(ElBits, IsSigned), \
3940  llvm::ElementCount::getScalable(NumEls), NF};
3941 #define RVV_VECTOR_TYPE_FLOAT(Name, Id, SingletonId, NumEls, ElBits, NF) \
3942  case BuiltinType::Id: \
3943  return {ElBits == 16 ? Float16Ty : (ElBits == 32 ? FloatTy : DoubleTy), \
3944  llvm::ElementCount::getScalable(NumEls), NF};
3945 #define RVV_PREDICATE_TYPE(Name, Id, SingletonId, NumEls) \
3946  case BuiltinType::Id: \
3947  return {BoolTy, llvm::ElementCount::getScalable(NumEls), 1};
3948 #include "clang/Basic/RISCVVTypes.def"
3949  }
3950 }

3952 /// getScalableVectorType - Return the unique reference to a scalable vector
3953 /// type of the specified element type and size. VectorType must be a built-in
3954 /// type.
3955 QualType ASTContext::getScalableVectorType(QualType EltTy,
3956  unsigned NumElts) const {
3957  if (Target->hasAArch64SVETypes()) {
3958  uint64_t EltTySize = getTypeSize(EltTy);
3959 #define SVE_VECTOR_TYPE(Name, MangledName, Id, SingletonId, NumEls, ElBits, \
3960  IsSigned, IsFP, IsBF) \
3961  if (!EltTy->isBooleanType() && \
3962  ((EltTy->hasIntegerRepresentation() && \
3963  EltTy->hasSignedIntegerRepresentation() == IsSigned) || \
3964  (EltTy->hasFloatingRepresentation() && !EltTy->isBFloat16Type() && \
3965  IsFP && !IsBF) || \
3966  (EltTy->hasFloatingRepresentation() && EltTy->isBFloat16Type() && \
3967  IsBF && !IsFP)) && \
3968  EltTySize == ElBits && NumElts == NumEls) { \
3969  return SingletonId; \
3970  }
3971 #define SVE_PREDICATE_TYPE(Name, MangledName, Id, SingletonId, NumEls) \
3972  if (EltTy->isBooleanType() && NumElts == NumEls) \
3973  return SingletonId;
3974 #include "clang/Basic/AArch64SVEACLETypes.def"
3975  } else if (Target->hasRISCVVTypes()) {
3976  uint64_t EltTySize = getTypeSize(EltTy);
3977 #define RVV_VECTOR_TYPE(Name, Id, SingletonId, NumEls, ElBits, NF, IsSigned, \
3978  IsFP) \
3979  if (!EltTy->isBooleanType() && \
3980  ((EltTy->hasIntegerRepresentation() && \
3981  EltTy->hasSignedIntegerRepresentation() == IsSigned) || \
3982  (EltTy->hasFloatingRepresentation() && IsFP)) && \
3983  EltTySize == ElBits && NumElts == NumEls) \
3984  return SingletonId;
3985 #define RVV_PREDICATE_TYPE(Name, Id, SingletonId, NumEls) \
3986  if (EltTy->isBooleanType() && NumElts == NumEls) \
3987  return SingletonId;
3988 #include "clang/Basic/RISCVVTypes.def"
3989  }
3990  return QualType();
3991 }

3993 /// getVectorType - Return the unique reference to a vector type of
3994 /// the specified element type and size. VectorType must be a built-in type.
3995 QualType ASTContext::getVectorType(QualType vecType, unsigned NumElts,
3996  VectorType::VectorKind VecKind) const {
3997  assert(vecType->isBuiltinType());
3998 
3999  // Check if we've already instantiated a vector of this type.
4000  llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
4001  VectorType::Profile(ID, vecType, NumElts, Type::Vector, VecKind);
4002 
4003  void *InsertPos = nullptr;
4004  if (VectorType *VTP = VectorTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos))
4005  return QualType(VTP, 0);
4006 
4007  // If the element type isn't canonical, this won't be a canonical type either,
4008  // so fill in the canonical type field.
4009  QualType Canonical;
4010  if (!vecType.isCanonical()) {
4011  Canonical = getVectorType(getCanonicalType(vecType), NumElts, VecKind);
4012 
4013  // Get the new insert position for the node we care about.
4014  VectorType *NewIP = VectorTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
4015  assert(!NewIP && "Shouldn't be in the map!"); (void)NewIP;
4016  }
4017  auto *New = new (*this, TypeAlignment)
4018  VectorType(vecType, NumElts, Canonical, VecKind);
4019  VectorTypes.InsertNode(New, InsertPos);
4020  Types.push_back(New);
4021  return QualType(New, 0);
4022 }
4023 
4024 QualType
4025 ASTContext::getDependentVectorType(QualType VecType, Expr *SizeExpr,
4026  SourceLocation AttrLoc,
4027  VectorType::VectorKind VecKind) const {
4028  llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
4029  DependentVectorType::Profile(ID, *this, getCanonicalType(VecType), SizeExpr,
4030  VecKind);
4031  void *InsertPos = nullptr;
4032  DependentVectorType *Canon =
4033  DependentVectorTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
4034  DependentVectorType *New;
4035 
4036  if (Canon) {
4037  New = new (*this, TypeAlignment) DependentVectorType(
4038  *this, VecType, QualType(Canon, 0), SizeExpr, AttrLoc, VecKind);
4039  } else {
4040  QualType CanonVecTy = getCanonicalType(VecType);
4041  if (CanonVecTy == VecType) {
4042  New = new (*this, TypeAlignment) DependentVectorType(
4043  *this, VecType, QualType(), SizeExpr, AttrLoc, VecKind);
4044 
4045  DependentVectorType *CanonCheck =
4046  DependentVectorTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
4047  assert(!CanonCheck &&
4048  "Dependent-sized vector_size canonical type broken");
4049  (void)CanonCheck;
4050  DependentVectorTypes.InsertNode(New, InsertPos);
4051  } else {
4052  QualType CanonTy = getDependentVectorType(CanonVecTy, SizeExpr,
4053  SourceLocation(), VecKind);
4054  New = new (*this, TypeAlignment) DependentVectorType(
4055  *this, VecType, CanonTy, SizeExpr, AttrLoc, VecKind);
4056  }
4057  }
4058 
4059  Types.push_back(New);
4060  return QualType(New, 0);
4061 }
4062 
4063 /// getExtVectorType - Return the unique reference to an extended vector type of
4064 /// the specified element type and size. VectorType must be a built-in type.
4065 QualType
4066 ASTContext::getExtVectorType(QualType vecType, unsigned NumElts) const {
4067  assert(vecType->isBuiltinType() || vecType->isDependentType());
4068 
4069  // Check if we've already instantiated a vector of this type.
4070  llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
4071  VectorType::Profile(ID, vecType, NumElts, Type::ExtVector,
4072  VectorType::GenericVector);
4073  void *InsertPos = nullptr;
4074  if (VectorType *VTP = VectorTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos))
4075  return QualType(VTP, 0);
4076 
4077  // If the element type isn't canonical, this won't be a canonical type either,
4078  // so fill in the canonical type field.
4079  QualType Canonical;
4080  if (!vecType.isCanonical()) {
4081  Canonical = getExtVectorType(getCanonicalType(vecType), NumElts);
4082 
4083  // Get the new insert position for the node we care about.
4084  VectorType *NewIP = VectorTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
4085  assert(!NewIP && "Shouldn't be in the map!"); (void)NewIP;
4086  }
4087  auto *New = new (*this, TypeAlignment)
4088  ExtVectorType(vecType, NumElts, Canonical);
4089  VectorTypes.InsertNode(New, InsertPos);
4090  Types.push_back(New);
4091  return QualType(New, 0);
4092 }
