4094 QualType
4095 ASTContext::getDependentSizedExtVectorType(QualType vecType,
4096  Expr *SizeExpr,
4097  SourceLocation AttrLoc) const {
4098  llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
4099  DependentSizedExtVectorType::Profile(ID, *this, getCanonicalType(vecType),
4100  SizeExpr);
4101 
4102  void *InsertPos = nullptr;
4103  DependentSizedExtVectorType *Canon
4104  = DependentSizedExtVectorTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
4105  DependentSizedExtVectorType *New;
4106  if (Canon) {
4107  // We already have a canonical version of this array type; use it as
4108  // the canonical type for a newly-built type.
4109  New = new (*this, TypeAlignment)
4110  DependentSizedExtVectorType(*this, vecType, QualType(Canon, 0),
4111  SizeExpr, AttrLoc);
4112  } else {
4113  QualType CanonVecTy = getCanonicalType(vecType);
4114  if (CanonVecTy == vecType) {
4115  New = new (*this, TypeAlignment)
4116  DependentSizedExtVectorType(*this, vecType, QualType(), SizeExpr,
4117  AttrLoc);
4118 
4119  DependentSizedExtVectorType *CanonCheck
4120  = DependentSizedExtVectorTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
4121  assert(!CanonCheck && "Dependent-sized ext_vector canonical type broken");
4122  (void)CanonCheck;
4123  DependentSizedExtVectorTypes.InsertNode(New, InsertPos);
4124  } else {
4125  QualType CanonExtTy = getDependentSizedExtVectorType(CanonVecTy, SizeExpr,
4126  SourceLocation());
4127  New = new (*this, TypeAlignment) DependentSizedExtVectorType(
4128  *this, vecType, CanonExtTy, SizeExpr, AttrLoc);
4129  }
4130  }
4131 
4132  Types.push_back(New);
4133  return QualType(New, 0);
4134 }

4136 QualType ASTContext::getConstantMatrixType(QualType ElementTy, unsigned NumRows,

4139  ConstantMatrixType::Profile(ID, ElementTy, NumRows, NumColumns,
4140  Type::ConstantMatrix);
4141

4143  "need a valid element type");
4144  assert(ConstantMatrixType::isDimensionValid(NumRows) &&
4145  ConstantMatrixType::isDimensionValid(NumColumns) &&
4146  "need valid matrix dimensions");
4147  void *InsertPos = nullptr;
4148  if (ConstantMatrixType *MTP = MatrixTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos))
4149  return QualType(MTP, 0);
4150 
4151  QualType Canonical;
4152  if (!ElementTy.isCanonical()) {
4153  Canonical =
4154  getConstantMatrixType(getCanonicalType(ElementTy), NumRows, NumColumns);
4155 
4156  ConstantMatrixType *NewIP = MatrixTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
4157  assert(!NewIP && "Matrix type shouldn't already exist in the map");

4159  }

4162  ConstantMatrixType(ElementTy, NumRows, NumColumns, Canonical);
4163  MatrixTypes.InsertNode(New, InsertPos);

4168 QualType ASTContext::getDependentSizedMatrixType(QualType ElementTy,
4169  Expr *RowExpr,
4170  Expr *ColumnExpr,
4171  SourceLocation AttrLoc) const {
4172  QualType CanonElementTy = getCanonicalType(ElementTy);
4173  llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
4174  DependentSizedMatrixType::Profile(ID, *this, CanonElementTy, RowExpr,
4175  ColumnExpr);
4176 
4177  void *InsertPos = nullptr;
4178  DependentSizedMatrixType *Canon =
4179  DependentSizedMatrixTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
4180 
4181  if (!Canon) {
4182  Canon = new (*this, TypeAlignment) DependentSizedMatrixType(
4183  *this, CanonElementTy, QualType(), RowExpr, ColumnExpr, AttrLoc);
4184 #ifndef NDEBUG
4185  DependentSizedMatrixType *CanonCheck =
4186  DependentSizedMatrixTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
4187  assert(!CanonCheck && "Dependent-sized matrix canonical type broken");
4188 #endif
4189  DependentSizedMatrixTypes.InsertNode(Canon, InsertPos);
4190  Types.push_back(Canon);
4191  }
4192 
4193  // Already have a canonical version of the matrix type
4194  //
4195  // If it exactly matches the requested type, use it directly.
4196  if (Canon->getElementType() == ElementTy && Canon->getRowExpr() == RowExpr &&
4197  Canon->getRowExpr() == ColumnExpr)
4198  return QualType(Canon, 0);
4199 
4200  // Use Canon as the canonical type for newly-built type.
4201  DependentSizedMatrixType *New = new (*this, TypeAlignment)
4202  DependentSizedMatrixType(*this, ElementTy, QualType(Canon, 0), RowExpr,
4203  ColumnExpr, AttrLoc);
4204  Types.push_back(New);
4205  return QualType(New, 0);
4206 }

4208 QualType ASTContext::getDependentAddressSpaceType(QualType PointeeType,
4209  Expr *AddrSpaceExpr,
4210  SourceLocation AttrLoc) const {
4211  assert(AddrSpaceExpr->isInstantiationDependent());
4212 
4213  QualType canonPointeeType = getCanonicalType(PointeeType);
4214 
4215  void *insertPos = nullptr;
4216  llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
4217  DependentAddressSpaceType::Profile(ID, *this, canonPointeeType,
4218  AddrSpaceExpr);
4219 
4220  DependentAddressSpaceType *canonTy =
4221  DependentAddressSpaceTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, insertPos);
4222 
4223  if (!canonTy) {
4224  canonTy = new (*this, TypeAlignment)
4225  DependentAddressSpaceType(*this, canonPointeeType,
4226  QualType(), AddrSpaceExpr, AttrLoc);
4227  DependentAddressSpaceTypes.InsertNode(canonTy, insertPos);
4228  Types.push_back(canonTy);
4229  }
4230 
4231  if (canonPointeeType == PointeeType &&
4232  canonTy->getAddrSpaceExpr() == AddrSpaceExpr)
4233  return QualType(canonTy, 0);
4234 
4235  auto *sugaredType
4236  = new (*this, TypeAlignment)
4237  DependentAddressSpaceType(*this, PointeeType, QualType(canonTy, 0),
4238  AddrSpaceExpr, AttrLoc);
4239  Types.push_back(sugaredType);
4240  return QualType(sugaredType, 0);
4241 }

4243 /// Determine whether \p T is canonical as the result type of a function.
4244 static bool isCanonicalResultType(QualType T) {
4245  return T.isCanonical() &&
4246  (T.getObjCLifetime() == Qualifiers::OCL_None ||
4247  T.getObjCLifetime() == Qualifiers::OCL_ExplicitNone);
4248 }

4250 /// getFunctionNoProtoType - Return a K&R style C function type like 'int()'.
4251 QualType
4252 ASTContext::getFunctionNoProtoType(QualType ResultTy,
4253  const FunctionType::ExtInfo &Info) const {
4254  // Unique functions, to guarantee there is only one function of a particular
4255  // structure.
4256  llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
4257  FunctionNoProtoType::Profile(ID, ResultTy, Info);
4258 
4259  void *InsertPos = nullptr;
4260  if (FunctionNoProtoType *FT =
4261  FunctionNoProtoTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos))
4262  return QualType(FT, 0);
4263 
4264  QualType Canonical;
4265  if (!isCanonicalResultType(ResultTy)) {
4266  Canonical =
4267  getFunctionNoProtoType(getCanonicalFunctionResultType(ResultTy), Info);
4268 
4269  // Get the new insert position for the node we care about.
4270  FunctionNoProtoType *NewIP =
4271  FunctionNoProtoTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
4272  assert(!NewIP && "Shouldn't be in the map!"); (void)NewIP;
4273  }
4274 
4275  auto *New = new (*this, TypeAlignment)
4276  FunctionNoProtoType(ResultTy, Canonical, Info);
4277  Types.push_back(New);
4278  FunctionNoProtoTypes.InsertNode(New, InsertPos);
4279  return QualType(New, 0);
4280 }
4281 
4282 CanQualType
4283 ASTContext::getCanonicalFunctionResultType(QualType ResultType) const {
4284  CanQualType CanResultType = getCanonicalType(ResultType);
4285 
4286  // Canonical result types do not have ARC lifetime qualifiers.
4287  if (CanResultType.getQualifiers().hasObjCLifetime()) {
4288  Qualifiers Qs = CanResultType.getQualifiers();
4289  Qs.removeObjCLifetime();
4290  return CanQualType::CreateUnsafe(
4291  getQualifiedType(CanResultType.getUnqualifiedType(), Qs));
4292  }
4293 
4294  return CanResultType;
4295 }
4296 
4297 static bool isCanonicalExceptionSpecification(
4298  const FunctionProtoType::ExceptionSpecInfo &ESI, bool NoexceptInType) {
4299  if (ESI.Type == EST_None)
4300  return true;
4301  if (!NoexceptInType)
4302  return false;
4303 
4304  // C++17 onwards: exception specification is part of the type, as a simple
4305  // boolean "can this function type throw".
4306  if (ESI.Type == EST_BasicNoexcept)
4307  return true;
4308 
4309  // A noexcept(expr) specification is (possibly) canonical if expr is
4310  // value-dependent.
4311  if (ESI.Type == EST_DependentNoexcept)
4312  return true;
4313 
4314  // A dynamic exception specification is canonical if it only contains pack
4315  // expansions (so we can't tell whether it's non-throwing) and all its
4316  // contained types are canonical.
4317  if (ESI.Type == EST_Dynamic) {
4318  bool AnyPackExpansions = false;
4319  for (QualType ET : ESI.Exceptions) {
4320  if (!ET.isCanonical())
4321  return false;
4322  if (ET->getAs<PackExpansionType>())
4323  AnyPackExpansions = true;
4324  }
4325  return AnyPackExpansions;
4326  }
4327 
4328  return false;
4329 }
4330 
4331 QualType ASTContext::getFunctionTypeInternal(
4332  QualType ResultTy, ArrayRef<QualType> ArgArray,
4333  const FunctionProtoType::ExtProtoInfo &EPI, bool OnlyWantCanonical) const {
4334  size_t NumArgs = ArgArray.size();
4335 
4336  // Unique functions, to guarantee there is only one function of a particular
4337  // structure.
4338  llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
4339  FunctionProtoType::Profile(ID, ResultTy, ArgArray.begin(), NumArgs, EPI,
4340  *this, true);
4341 
4342  QualType Canonical;
4343  bool Unique = false;
4344 
4345  void *InsertPos = nullptr;
4346  if (FunctionProtoType *FPT =
4347  FunctionProtoTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos)) {
4348  QualType Existing = QualType(FPT, 0);
4349 
4350  // If we find a pre-existing equivalent FunctionProtoType, we can just reuse
4351  // it so long as our exception specification doesn't contain a dependent
4352  // noexcept expression, or we're just looking for a canonical type.
4353  // Otherwise, we're going to need to create a type
4354  // sugar node to hold the concrete expression.
4355  if (OnlyWantCanonical || !isComputedNoexcept(EPI.ExceptionSpec.Type) ||
4356  EPI.ExceptionSpec.NoexceptExpr == FPT->getNoexceptExpr())
4357  return Existing;
4358 
4359  // We need a new type sugar node for this one, to hold the new noexcept
4360  // expression. We do no canonicalization here, but that's OK since we don't
4361  // expect to see the same noexcept expression much more than once.
4362  Canonical = getCanonicalType(Existing);
4363  Unique = true;
4364  }
4365 
4366  bool NoexceptInType = getLangOpts().CPlusPlus17;
4367  bool IsCanonicalExceptionSpec =
4368  isCanonicalExceptionSpecification(EPI.ExceptionSpec, NoexceptInType);
4369 
4370  // Determine whether the type being created is already canonical or not.
4371  bool isCanonical = !Unique && IsCanonicalExceptionSpec &&
4372  isCanonicalResultType(ResultTy) && !EPI.HasTrailingReturn;
4373  for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumArgs && isCanonical; ++i)
4374  if (!ArgArray[i].isCanonicalAsParam())
4375  isCanonical = false;
4376 
4377  if (OnlyWantCanonical)
4378  assert(isCanonical &&
4379  "given non-canonical parameters constructing canonical type");
4380 
4381  // If this type isn't canonical, get the canonical version of it if we don't
4382  // already have it. The exception spec is only partially part of the
4383  // canonical type, and only in C++17 onwards.
4384  if (!isCanonical && Canonical.isNull()) {
4385  SmallVector<QualType, 16> CanonicalArgs;
4386  CanonicalArgs.reserve(NumArgs);
4387  for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumArgs; ++i)
4388  CanonicalArgs.push_back(getCanonicalParamType(ArgArray[i]));
4389 
4390  llvm::SmallVector<QualType, 8> ExceptionTypeStorage;
4391  FunctionProtoType::ExtProtoInfo CanonicalEPI = EPI;
4392  CanonicalEPI.HasTrailingReturn = false;
4393 
4394  if (IsCanonicalExceptionSpec) {
4395  // Exception spec is already OK.
4396  } else if (NoexceptInType) {
4397  switch (EPI.ExceptionSpec.Type) {
4398  case EST_Unparsed: case EST_Unevaluated: case EST_Uninstantiated:
4399  // We don't know yet. It shouldn't matter what we pick here; no-one
4400  // should ever look at this.
4401  LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
4402  case EST_None: case EST_MSAny: case EST_NoexceptFalse:
4403  CanonicalEPI.ExceptionSpec.Type = EST_None;
4404  break;
4405 
4406  // A dynamic exception specification is almost always "not noexcept",
4407  // with the exception that a pack expansion might expand to no types.
4408  case EST_Dynamic: {
4409  bool AnyPacks = false;
4410  for (QualType ET : EPI.ExceptionSpec.Exceptions) {
4411  if (ET->getAs<PackExpansionType>())
4412  AnyPacks = true;
4413  ExceptionTypeStorage.push_back(getCanonicalType(ET));
4414  }
4415  if (!AnyPacks)
4416  CanonicalEPI.ExceptionSpec.Type = EST_None;
4417  else {
4418  CanonicalEPI.ExceptionSpec.Type = EST_Dynamic;
4419  CanonicalEPI.ExceptionSpec.Exceptions = ExceptionTypeStorage;
4420  }
4421  break;
4422  }
4423 
4424  case EST_DynamicNone:
4425  case EST_BasicNoexcept:
4426  case EST_NoexceptTrue:
4427  case EST_NoThrow:
4428  CanonicalEPI.ExceptionSpec.Type = EST_BasicNoexcept;
4429  break;
4430 
4431  case EST_DependentNoexcept:
4432  llvm_unreachable("dependent noexcept is already canonical");
4433  }
4434  } else {
4435  CanonicalEPI.ExceptionSpec = FunctionProtoType::ExceptionSpecInfo();
4436  }
4437 
4438  // Adjust the canonical function result type.
4439  CanQualType CanResultTy = getCanonicalFunctionResultType(ResultTy);
4440  Canonical =
4441  getFunctionTypeInternal(CanResultTy, CanonicalArgs, CanonicalEPI, true);
4442 
4443  // Get the new insert position for the node we care about.
4444  FunctionProtoType *NewIP =
4445  FunctionProtoTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
4446  assert(!NewIP && "Shouldn't be in the map!"); (void)NewIP;
4447  }
4448 
4449  // Compute the needed size to hold this FunctionProtoType and the
4450  // various trailing objects.
4451  auto ESH = FunctionProtoType::getExceptionSpecSize(
4452  EPI.ExceptionSpec.Type, EPI.ExceptionSpec.Exceptions.size());
4453  size_t Size = FunctionProtoType::totalSizeToAlloc<
4454  QualType, SourceLocation, FunctionType::FunctionTypeExtraBitfields,
4455  FunctionType::ExceptionType, Expr *, FunctionDecl *,
4456  FunctionProtoType::ExtParameterInfo, Qualifiers>(
4457  NumArgs, EPI.Variadic,
4458  FunctionProtoType::hasExtraBitfields(EPI.ExceptionSpec.Type),
4459  ESH.NumExceptionType, ESH.NumExprPtr, ESH.NumFunctionDeclPtr,
4460  EPI.ExtParameterInfos ? NumArgs : 0,
4461  EPI.TypeQuals.hasNonFastQualifiers() ? 1 : 0);
4462 
4463  auto *FTP = (FunctionProtoType *)Allocate(Size, TypeAlignment);
4464  FunctionProtoType::ExtProtoInfo newEPI = EPI;
4465  new (FTP) FunctionProtoType(ResultTy, ArgArray, Canonical, newEPI);
4466  Types.push_back(FTP);
4467  if (!Unique)
4468  FunctionProtoTypes.InsertNode(FTP, InsertPos);
4469  return QualType(FTP, 0);
4470 }
4471 
4472 QualType ASTContext::getPipeType(QualType T, bool ReadOnly) const {
4473  llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
4474  PipeType::Profile(ID, T, ReadOnly);
4475 
4476  void *InsertPos = nullptr;
4477  if (PipeType *PT = PipeTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos))
4478  return QualType(PT, 0);
4479 
4480  // If the pipe element type isn't canonical, this won't be a canonical type
4481  // either, so fill in the canonical type field.
4482  QualType Canonical;
4483  if (!T.isCanonical()) {
4484  Canonical = getPipeType(getCanonicalType(T), ReadOnly);
4485 
4486  // Get the new insert position for the node we care about.
4487  PipeType *NewIP = PipeTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
4488  assert(!NewIP && "Shouldn't be in the map!");
4489  (void)NewIP;
4490  }
4491  auto *New = new (*this, TypeAlignment) PipeType(T, Canonical, ReadOnly);
4492  Types.push_back(New);
4493  PipeTypes.InsertNode(New, InsertPos);
4494  return QualType(New, 0);
4495 }

4499  return LangOpts.OpenCL ? getAddrSpaceQualType(Ty, LangAS::opencl_constant)
4500  : Ty;
4501 }

4544 #ifndef NDEBUG
4545 static bool NeedsInjectedClassNameType(const RecordDecl *D) {
4546  if (!isa<CXXRecordDecl>(D)) return false;
4547  const auto *RD = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(D);
4548  if (isa<ClassTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl>(RD))
4549  return true;
4550  if (RD->getDescribedClassTemplate() &&
4551  !isa<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(RD))
4552  return true;
4553  return false;
4554 }
4555 #endif
4556 
4557 /// getInjectedClassNameType - Return the unique reference to the
4558 /// injected class name type for the specified templated declaration.
4559 QualType ASTContext::getInjectedClassNameType(CXXRecordDecl *Decl,
4560  QualType TST) const {
4561  assert(NeedsInjectedClassNameType(Decl));
4562  if (Decl->TypeForDecl) {
4563  assert(isa<InjectedClassNameType>(Decl->TypeForDecl));
4564  } else if (CXXRecordDecl *PrevDecl = Decl->getPreviousDecl()) {
4565  assert(PrevDecl->TypeForDecl && "previous declaration has no type");
4566  Decl->TypeForDecl = PrevDecl->TypeForDecl;
4567  assert(isa<InjectedClassNameType>(Decl->TypeForDecl));
4568  } else {
4569  Type *newType =
4570  new (*this, TypeAlignment) InjectedClassNameType(Decl, TST);
4571  Decl->TypeForDecl = newType;
4572  Types.push_back(newType);
4573  }
4574  return QualType(Decl->TypeForDecl, 0);
4575 }
4576 
4577 /// getTypeDeclType - Return the unique reference to the type for the
4578 /// specified type declaration.
4579 QualType ASTContext::getTypeDeclTypeSlow(const TypeDecl *Decl) const {
4580  assert(Decl && "Passed null for Decl param");
4581  assert(!Decl->TypeForDecl && "TypeForDecl present in slow case");
4582 
4583  if (const auto *Typedef = dyn_cast<TypedefNameDecl>(Decl))
4584  return getTypedefType(Typedef);
4585 
4586  assert(!isa<TemplateTypeParmDecl>(Decl) &&
4587  "Template type parameter types are always available.");
4588 
4589  if (const auto *Record = dyn_cast<RecordDecl>(Decl)) {
4590  assert(Record->isFirstDecl() && "struct/union has previous declaration");
4591  assert(!NeedsInjectedClassNameType(Record));
4592  return getRecordType(Record);
4593  } else if (const auto *Enum = dyn_cast<EnumDecl>(Decl)) {
4594  assert(Enum->isFirstDecl() && "enum has previous declaration");
4595  return getEnumType(Enum);
4596  } else if (const auto *Using = dyn_cast<UnresolvedUsingTypenameDecl>(Decl)) {
4597  return getUnresolvedUsingType(Using);
4598  } else
4599  llvm_unreachable("TypeDecl without a type?");
4600 
4601  return QualType(Decl->TypeForDecl, 0);
4602 }
4603 
4604 /// getTypedefType - Return the unique reference to the type for the
4605 /// specified typedef name decl.
4606 QualType ASTContext::getTypedefType(const TypedefNameDecl *Decl,
4607  QualType Underlying) const {
4608  if (Decl->TypeForDecl) return QualType(Decl->TypeForDecl, 0);
4609 
4610  if (Underlying.isNull())
4611  Underlying = Decl->getUnderlyingType();
4612  QualType Canonical = getCanonicalType(Underlying);
4613  auto *newType = new (*this, TypeAlignment)
4614  TypedefType(Type::Typedef, Decl, Underlying, Canonical);
4615  Decl->TypeForDecl = newType;
4616  Types.push_back(newType);
4617  return QualType(newType, 0);
4618 }

4746 /// Retrieve a
4747 QualType ASTContext::getSubstTemplateTypeParmPackType(
4748  const TemplateTypeParmType *Parm,
4749  const TemplateArgument &ArgPack) {
4750 #ifndef NDEBUG
4751  for (const auto &P : ArgPack.pack_elements()) {
4752  assert(P.getKind() == TemplateArgument::Type &&"Pack contains a non-type");
4753  assert(P.getAsType().isCanonical() && "Pack contains non-canonical type");
4754  }
4755 #endif
4756 
4757  llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
4758  SubstTemplateTypeParmPackType::Profile(ID, Parm, ArgPack);
4759  void *InsertPos = nullptr;
4760  if (SubstTemplateTypeParmPackType *SubstParm
4761  = SubstTemplateTypeParmPackTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos))
4762  return QualType(SubstParm, 0);
4763

4765  if (!Parm->isCanonicalUnqualified()) {
4766  Canon = getCanonicalType(QualType(Parm, 0));
4767  Canon = getSubstTemplateTypeParmPackType(cast<TemplateTypeParmType>(Canon),
4768  ArgPack);
4769  SubstTemplateTypeParmPackTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
4770  }
4771 
4772  auto *SubstParm
4773  = new (*this, TypeAlignment) SubstTemplateTypeParmPackType(Parm, Canon,
4774  ArgPack);
4775  Types.push_back(SubstParm);
4776  SubstTemplateTypeParmPackTypes.InsertNode(SubstParm, InsertPos);
4777  return QualType(SubstParm, 0);
4778 }

4780 /// Retrieve the template type parameter type for a template
4781 /// parameter or parameter pack with the given depth, index, and (optionally)
4782 /// name.
4783 QualType ASTContext::getTemplateTypeParmType(unsigned Depth, unsigned Index,
4784  bool ParameterPack,
4785  TemplateTypeParmDecl *TTPDecl) const {

4787  TemplateTypeParmType::Profile(ID, Depth, Index, ParameterPack, TTPDecl);

4790  = TemplateTypeParmTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
4791 
4792  if (TypeParm)
4793  return QualType(TypeParm, 0);

4797  TypeParm = new (*this, TypeAlignment) TemplateTypeParmType(TTPDecl, Canon);

4800  = TemplateTypeParmTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
4801  assert(!TypeCheck && "Template type parameter canonical type broken");
4802  (void)TypeCheck;
4803  } else

4805  TemplateTypeParmType(Depth, Index, ParameterPack);

4813 TypeSourceInfo *
4814 ASTContext::getTemplateSpecializationTypeInfo(TemplateName Name,
4815  SourceLocation NameLoc,
4816  const TemplateArgumentListInfo &Args,
4817  QualType Underlying) const {
4818  assert(!Name.getAsDependentTemplateName() &&
4819  "No dependent template names here!");
4820  QualType TST = getTemplateSpecializationType(Name, Args, Underlying);
4821 
4822  TypeSourceInfo *DI = CreateTypeSourceInfo(TST);
4823  TemplateSpecializationTypeLoc TL =
4824  DI->getTypeLoc().castAs<TemplateSpecializationTypeLoc>();
4825  TL.setTemplateKeywordLoc(SourceLocation());
4826  TL.setTemplateNameLoc(NameLoc);
4827  TL.setLAngleLoc(Args.getLAngleLoc());
4828  TL.setRAngleLoc(Args.getRAngleLoc());
4829  for (unsigned i = 0, e = TL.getNumArgs(); i != e; ++i)
4830  TL.setArgLocInfo(i, Args[i].getLocInfo());
4831  return DI;
4832 }

4834 QualType
4835 ASTContext::getTemplateSpecializationType(TemplateName Template,
4836  const TemplateArgumentListInfo &Args,
4837  QualType Underlying) const {
4838  assert(!Template.getAsDependentTemplateName() &&
4839  "No dependent template names here!");
4840 
4841  SmallVector<TemplateArgument, 4> ArgVec;
4842  ArgVec.reserve(Args.size());
4843  for (const TemplateArgumentLoc &Arg : Args.arguments())
4844  ArgVec.push_back(Arg.getArgument());

4849 #ifndef NDEBUG
4850 static bool hasAnyPackExpansions(ArrayRef<TemplateArgument> Args) {
4851  for (const TemplateArgument &Arg : Args)
4852  if (Arg.isPackExpansion())
4853  return true;
4854 
4855  return true;
4856 }
4857 #endif
4858 
4859 QualType
4860 ASTContext::getTemplateSpecializationType(TemplateName Template,
4861  ArrayRef<TemplateArgument> Args,
4862  QualType Underlying) const {
4863  assert(!Template.getAsDependentTemplateName() &&
4864  "No dependent template names here!");
4865  // Look through qualified template names.
4866  if (QualifiedTemplateName *QTN = Template.getAsQualifiedTemplateName())
4867  Template = TemplateName(QTN->getTemplateDecl());
4868 
4869  bool IsTypeAlias =
4870  Template.getAsTemplateDecl() &&
4871  isa<TypeAliasTemplateDecl>(Template.getAsTemplateDecl());
4872  QualType CanonType;
4873  if (!Underlying.isNull())
4874  CanonType = getCanonicalType(Underlying);
4875  else {
4876  // We can get here with an alias template when the specialization contains
4877  // a pack expansion that does not match up with a parameter pack.
4878  assert((!IsTypeAlias || hasAnyPackExpansions(Args)) &&
4879  "Caller must compute aliased type");
4880  IsTypeAlias = false;
4881  CanonType = getCanonicalTemplateSpecializationType(Template, Args);
4882  }
4883 
4884  // Allocate the (non-canonical) template specialization type, but don't
4885  // try to unique it: these types typically have location information that
4886  // we don't unique and don't want to lose.
4887  void *Mem = Allocate(sizeof(TemplateSpecializationType) +
4888  sizeof(TemplateArgument) * Args.size() +
4889  (IsTypeAlias? sizeof(QualType) : 0),
4890  TypeAlignment);
4891  auto *Spec
4892  = new (Mem) TemplateSpecializationType(Template, Args, CanonType,
4893  IsTypeAlias ? Underlying : QualType());
4894 
4895  Types.push_back(Spec);
4896  return QualType(Spec, 0);
4897 }
4898 
4899 static bool
4900 getCanonicalTemplateArguments(const ASTContext &C,
4901  ArrayRef<TemplateArgument> OrigArgs,
4902  SmallVectorImpl<TemplateArgument> &CanonArgs) {
4903  bool AnyNonCanonArgs = false;
4904  unsigned NumArgs = OrigArgs.size();
4905  CanonArgs.resize(NumArgs);
4906  for (unsigned I = 0; I != NumArgs; ++I) {
4907  const TemplateArgument &OrigArg = OrigArgs[I];
4908  TemplateArgument &CanonArg = CanonArgs[I];
4909  CanonArg = C.getCanonicalTemplateArgument(OrigArg);
4910  if (!CanonArg.structurallyEquals(OrigArg))
4911  AnyNonCanonArgs = true;
4912  }
4913  return AnyNonCanonArgs;
4914 }
4915 
4916 QualType ASTContext::getCanonicalTemplateSpecializationType(
4917  TemplateName Template, ArrayRef<TemplateArgument> Args) const {
4918  assert(!Template.getAsDependentTemplateName() &&
4919  "No dependent template names here!");
4920 
4921  // Look through qualified template names.
4922  if (QualifiedTemplateName *QTN = Template.getAsQualifiedTemplateName())
4923  Template = TemplateName(QTN->getTemplateDecl());
4924 
4925  // Build the canonical template specialization type.
4926  TemplateName CanonTemplate = getCanonicalTemplateName(Template);
4927  SmallVector<TemplateArgument, 4> CanonArgs;
4928  ::getCanonicalTemplateArguments(*this, Args, CanonArgs);
4929 
4930  // Determine whether this canonical template specialization type already
4931  // exists.
4932  llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
4933  TemplateSpecializationType::Profile(ID, CanonTemplate,
4934  CanonArgs, *this);
4935 
4936  void *InsertPos = nullptr;
4937  TemplateSpecializationType *Spec
4938  = TemplateSpecializationTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
4939 
4940  if (!Spec) {
4941  // Allocate a new canonical template specialization type.
4942  void *Mem = Allocate((sizeof(TemplateSpecializationType) +
4943  sizeof(TemplateArgument) * CanonArgs.size()),
4944  TypeAlignment);
4945  Spec = new (Mem) TemplateSpecializationType(CanonTemplate,
4946  CanonArgs,
4947  QualType(), QualType());
4948  Types.push_back(Spec);
4949  TemplateSpecializationTypes.InsertNode(Spec, InsertPos);
4950  }
4951 
4952  assert(Spec->isDependentType() &&
4953  "Non-dependent template-id type must have a canonical type");
4954  return QualType(Spec, 0);
4955 }

4957 QualType ASTContext::getElaboratedType(ElaboratedTypeKeyword Keyword,
4958  NestedNameSpecifier *NNS,
4959  QualType NamedType,
4960  TagDecl *OwnedTagDecl) const {
4961  llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
4962  ElaboratedType::Profile(ID, Keyword, NNS, NamedType, OwnedTagDecl);
4963 
4964  void *InsertPos = nullptr;
4965  ElaboratedType *T = ElaboratedTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
4966  if (T)
4967  return QualType(T, 0);
4968 
4969  QualType Canon = NamedType;
4970  if (!Canon.isCanonical()) {
4971  Canon = getCanonicalType(NamedType);
4972  ElaboratedType *CheckT = ElaboratedTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
4973  assert(!CheckT && "Elaborated canonical type broken");
4974  (void)CheckT;
4975  }
4976 
4977  void *Mem = Allocate(ElaboratedType::totalSizeToAlloc<TagDecl *>(!!OwnedTagDecl),
4978  TypeAlignment);
4979  T = new (Mem) ElaboratedType(Keyword, NNS, NamedType, Canon, OwnedTagDecl);
4980 
4981  Types.push_back(T);
4982  ElaboratedTypes.InsertNode(T, InsertPos);
4983  return QualType(T, 0);
4984 }

5061 QualType
5062 ASTContext::getDependentTemplateSpecializationType(
5063  ElaboratedTypeKeyword Keyword,
5064  NestedNameSpecifier *NNS,
5065  const IdentifierInfo *Name,
5066  ArrayRef<TemplateArgument> Args) const {
5067  assert((!NNS || NNS->isDependent()) &&
5068  "nested-name-specifier must be dependent");
5069 
5070  llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
5071  DependentTemplateSpecializationType::Profile(ID, *this, Keyword, NNS,
5072  Name, Args);
5073 
5074  void *InsertPos = nullptr;
5075  DependentTemplateSpecializationType *T
5076  = DependentTemplateSpecializationTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
5077  if (T)
5078  return QualType(T, 0);
5079 
5080  NestedNameSpecifier *CanonNNS = getCanonicalNestedNameSpecifier(NNS);
5081 
5082  ElaboratedTypeKeyword CanonKeyword = Keyword;
5083  if (Keyword == ETK_None) CanonKeyword = ETK_Typename;
5084 
5085  SmallVector<TemplateArgument, 16> CanonArgs;
5086  bool AnyNonCanonArgs =
5087  ::getCanonicalTemplateArguments(*this, Args, CanonArgs);
5088 
5089  QualType Canon;
5090  if (AnyNonCanonArgs || CanonNNS != NNS || CanonKeyword != Keyword) {
5091  Canon = getDependentTemplateSpecializationType(CanonKeyword, CanonNNS,
5092  Name,
5093  CanonArgs);
5094 
5095  // Find the insert position again.
5096  DependentTemplateSpecializationTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
5097  }
5098 
5099  void *Mem = Allocate((sizeof(DependentTemplateSpecializationType) +
5100  sizeof(TemplateArgument) * Args.size()),
5101  TypeAlignment);
5102  T = new (Mem) DependentTemplateSpecializationType(Keyword, NNS,
5103  Name, Args, Canon);
5104  Types.push_back(T);
5105  DependentTemplateSpecializationTypes.InsertNode(T, InsertPos);
5106  return QualType(T, 0);
5107 }
5108 
5109 TemplateArgument ASTContext::getInjectedTemplateArg(NamedDecl *Param) {
5110  TemplateArgument Arg;
5111  if (const auto *TTP = dyn_cast<TemplateTypeParmDecl>(Param)) {
5112  QualType ArgType = getTypeDeclType(TTP);
5113  if (TTP->isParameterPack())
5114  ArgType = getPackExpansionType(ArgType, None);
5115 
5116  Arg = TemplateArgument(ArgType);
5117  } else if (auto *NTTP = dyn_cast<NonTypeTemplateParmDecl>(Param)) {
5118  QualType T =
5119  NTTP->getType().getNonPackExpansionType().getNonLValueExprType(*this);
5120  // For class NTTPs, ensure we include the 'const' so the type matches that
5121  // of a real template argument.
5122  // FIXME: It would be more faithful to model this as something like an
5123  // lvalue-to-rvalue conversion applied to a const-qualified lvalue.
5124  if (T->isRecordType())
5125  T.addConst();
5126  Expr *E = new (*this) DeclRefExpr(
5127  *this, NTTP, /*enclosing*/ false, T,
5128  Expr::getValueKindForType(NTTP->getType()), NTTP->getLocation());
5129 
5130  if (NTTP->isParameterPack())
5131  E = new (*this) PackExpansionExpr(DependentTy, E, NTTP->getLocation(),
5132  None);
5133  Arg = TemplateArgument(E);
5134  } else {
5135  auto *TTP = cast<TemplateTemplateParmDecl>(Param);
5136  if (TTP->isParameterPack())
5137  Arg = TemplateArgument(TemplateName(TTP), Optional<unsigned>());
5138  else
5139  Arg = TemplateArgument(TemplateName(TTP));
5140  }
5141 
5142  if (Param->isTemplateParameterPack())
5143  Arg = TemplateArgument::CreatePackCopy(*this, Arg);
5144 
5145  return Arg;
5146 }
5147 
5148 void
5149 ASTContext::getInjectedTemplateArgs(const TemplateParameterList *Params,
5150  SmallVectorImpl<TemplateArgument> &Args) {
5151  Args.reserve(Args.size() + Params->size());
5152 
5153  for (NamedDecl *Param : *Params)
5154  Args.push_back(getInjectedTemplateArg(Param));
5155 }
5156 
5157 QualType ASTContext::getPackExpansionType(QualType Pattern,
5158  Optional<unsigned> NumExpansions,
5159  bool ExpectPackInType) {
5160  assert((!ExpectPackInType || Pattern->containsUnexpandedParameterPack()) &&
5161  "Pack expansions must expand one or more parameter packs");
5162 
5163  llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
5164  PackExpansionType::Profile(ID, Pattern, NumExpansions);
5165 
5166  void *InsertPos = nullptr;
5167  PackExpansionType *T = PackExpansionTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
5168  if (T)
5169  return QualType(T, 0);
5170 
5171  QualType Canon;
5172  if (!Pattern.isCanonical()) {
5173  Canon = getPackExpansionType(getCanonicalType(Pattern), NumExpansions,
5174  /*ExpectPackInType=*/false);
5175 
5176  // Find the insert position again, in case we inserted an element into
5177  // PackExpansionTypes and invalidated our insert position.
5178  PackExpansionTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
5179  }
5180 
5181  T = new (*this, TypeAlignment)
5182  PackExpansionType(Pattern, Canon, NumExpansions);
5183  Types.push_back(T);
5184  PackExpansionTypes.InsertNode(T, InsertPos);
5185  return QualType(T, 0);
5186 }
5187 
5188 /// CmpProtocolNames - Comparison predicate for sorting protocols
5189 /// alphabetically.
5190 static int CmpProtocolNames(ObjCProtocolDecl *const *LHS,
5191  ObjCProtocolDecl *const *RHS) {
5192  return DeclarationName::compare((*LHS)->getDeclName(), (*RHS)->getDeclName());
5193 }
5194 
5195 static bool areSortedAndUniqued(ArrayRef<ObjCProtocolDecl *> Protocols) {
5196  if (Protocols.empty()) return true;
5197 
5198  if (Protocols[0]->getCanonicalDecl() != Protocols[0])
5199  return false;
5200 
5201  for (unsigned i = 1; i != Protocols.size(); ++i)
5202  if (CmpProtocolNames(&Protocols[i - 1], &Protocols[i]) >= 0 ||
5203  Protocols[i]->getCanonicalDecl() != Protocols[i])
5204  return false;
5205  return true;
5206 }
5207 
5208 static void
5209 SortAndUniqueProtocols(SmallVectorImpl<ObjCProtocolDecl *> &Protocols) {
5210  // Sort protocols, keyed by name.
5211  llvm::array_pod_sort(Protocols.begin(), Protocols.end(), CmpProtocolNames);
5212 
5213  // Canonicalize.
5214  for (ObjCProtocolDecl *&P : Protocols)
5215  P = P->getCanonicalDecl();
5216 
5217  // Remove duplicates.
5218  auto ProtocolsEnd = std::unique(Protocols.begin(), Protocols.end());
5219  Protocols.erase(ProtocolsEnd, Protocols.end());
5220 }
5221 
5222 QualType ASTContext::getObjCObjectType(QualType BaseType,
5223  ObjCProtocolDecl * const *Protocols,
5224  unsigned NumProtocols) const {
5225  return getObjCObjectType(BaseType, {},
5226  llvm::makeArrayRef(Protocols, NumProtocols),
5227  /*isKindOf=*/false);
5228 }
5229 
5230 QualType ASTContext::getObjCObjectType(
5231  QualType baseType,
5232  ArrayRef<QualType> typeArgs,
5233  ArrayRef<ObjCProtocolDecl *> protocols,
5234  bool isKindOf) const {
5235  // If the base type is an interface and there aren't any protocols or
5236  // type arguments to add, then the interface type will do just fine.
5237  if (typeArgs.empty() && protocols.empty() && !isKindOf &&
5238  isa<ObjCInterfaceType>(baseType))
5239  return baseType;
5240 
5241  // Look in the folding set for an existing type.
5242  llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
5243  ObjCObjectTypeImpl::Profile(ID, baseType, typeArgs, protocols, isKindOf);
5244  void *InsertPos = nullptr;
5245  if (ObjCObjectType *QT = ObjCObjectTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos))
5246  return QualType(QT, 0);
5247 
5248  // Determine the type arguments to be used for canonicalization,
5249  // which may be explicitly specified here or written on the base
5250  // type.
5251  ArrayRef<QualType> effectiveTypeArgs = typeArgs;
5252  if (effectiveTypeArgs.empty()) {
5253  if (const auto *baseObject = baseType->getAs<ObjCObjectType>())
5254  effectiveTypeArgs = baseObject->getTypeArgs();
5255  }
5256 
5257  // Build the canonical type, which has the canonical base type and a
5258  // sorted-and-uniqued list of protocols and the type arguments
5259  // canonicalized.
5260  QualType canonical;
5261  bool typeArgsAreCanonical = llvm::all_of(
5262  effectiveTypeArgs, [&](QualType type) { return type.isCanonical(); });
5263  bool protocolsSorted = areSortedAndUniqued(protocols);
5264  if (!typeArgsAreCanonical || !protocolsSorted || !baseType.isCanonical()) {
5265  // Determine the canonical type arguments.
5266  ArrayRef<QualType> canonTypeArgs;
5267  SmallVector<QualType, 4> canonTypeArgsVec;
5268  if (!typeArgsAreCanonical) {
5269  canonTypeArgsVec.reserve(effectiveTypeArgs.size());
5270  for (auto typeArg : effectiveTypeArgs)
5271  canonTypeArgsVec.push_back(getCanonicalType(typeArg));
5272  canonTypeArgs = canonTypeArgsVec;
5273  } else {
5274  canonTypeArgs = effectiveTypeArgs;
5275  }
5276 
5277  ArrayRef<ObjCProtocolDecl *> canonProtocols;
5278  SmallVector<ObjCProtocolDecl*, 8> canonProtocolsVec;
5279  if (!protocolsSorted) {
5280  canonProtocolsVec.append(protocols.begin(), protocols.end());
5281  SortAndUniqueProtocols(canonProtocolsVec);
5282  canonProtocols = canonProtocolsVec;
5283  } else {
5284  canonProtocols = protocols;
5285  }
5286 
5287  canonical = getObjCObjectType(getCanonicalType(baseType), canonTypeArgs,
5288  canonProtocols, isKindOf);
5289 
5290  // Regenerate InsertPos.
5291  ObjCObjectTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
5292  }
5293 
5294  unsigned size = sizeof(ObjCObjectTypeImpl);
5295  size += typeArgs.size() * sizeof(QualType);
5296  size += protocols.size() * sizeof(ObjCProtocolDecl *);
5297  void *mem = Allocate(size, TypeAlignment);
5298  auto *T =
5299  new (mem) ObjCObjectTypeImpl(canonical, baseType, typeArgs, protocols,
5300  isKindOf);
5301 
5302  Types.push_back(T);
5303  ObjCObjectTypes.InsertNode(T, InsertPos);
5304  return QualType(T, 0);
5305 }
5306 
5307 /// Apply Objective-C protocol qualifiers to the given type.
5308 /// If this is for the canonical type of a type parameter, we can apply
5309 /// protocol qualifiers on the ObjCObjectPointerType.
5310 QualType
5311 ASTContext::applyObjCProtocolQualifiers(QualType type,
5312  ArrayRef<ObjCProtocolDecl *> protocols, bool &hasError,
5313  bool allowOnPointerType) const {
5314  hasError = false;
5315 
5316  if (const auto *objT = dyn_cast<ObjCTypeParamType>(type.getTypePtr())) {
5317  return getObjCTypeParamType(objT->getDecl(), protocols);
5318  }
5319 
5320  // Apply protocol qualifiers to ObjCObjectPointerType.
5321  if (allowOnPointerType) {
5322  if (const auto *objPtr =
5323  dyn_cast<ObjCObjectPointerType>(type.getTypePtr())) {
5324  const ObjCObjectType *objT = objPtr->getObjectType();
5325  // Merge protocol lists and construct ObjCObjectType.
5326  SmallVector<ObjCProtocolDecl*, 8> protocolsVec;
5327  protocolsVec.append(objT->qual_begin(),
5328  objT->qual_end());
5329  protocolsVec.append(protocols.begin(), protocols.end());
5330  ArrayRef<ObjCProtocolDecl *> protocols = protocolsVec;
5331  type = getObjCObjectType(
5332  objT->getBaseType(),
5333  objT->getTypeArgsAsWritten(),
5334  protocols,
5335  objT->isKindOfTypeAsWritten());
5336  return getObjCObjectPointerType(type);
5337  }
5338  }
5339 
5340  // Apply protocol qualifiers to ObjCObjectType.
5341  if (const auto *objT = dyn_cast<ObjCObjectType>(type.getTypePtr())){
5342  // FIXME: Check for protocols to which the class type is already
5343  // known to conform.
5344 
5345  return getObjCObjectType(objT->getBaseType(),
5346  objT->getTypeArgsAsWritten(),
5347  protocols,
5348  objT->isKindOfTypeAsWritten());
5349  }
5350 
5351  // If the canonical type is ObjCObjectType, ...
5352  if (type->isObjCObjectType()) {
5353  // Silently overwrite any existing protocol qualifiers.
5354  // TODO: determine whether that's the right thing to do.
5355 
5356  // FIXME: Check for protocols to which the class type is already
5357  // known to conform.
5358  return getObjCObjectType(type, {}, protocols, false);
5359  }
5360 
5361  // id<protocol-list>
5362  if (type->isObjCIdType()) {
5363  const auto *objPtr = type->castAs<ObjCObjectPointerType>();
5364  type = getObjCObjectType(ObjCBuiltinIdTy, {}, protocols,
5365  objPtr->isKindOfType());
5366  return getObjCObjectPointerType(type);
5367  }
5368 
5369  // Class<protocol-list>
5370  if (type->isObjCClassType()) {
5371  const auto *objPtr = type->castAs<ObjCObjectPointerType>();
5372  type = getObjCObjectType(ObjCBuiltinClassTy, {}, protocols,
5373  objPtr->isKindOfType());
5374  return getObjCObjectPointerType(type);
5375  }
5376 
5377  hasError = true;
5378  return type;
5379 }
5380 
5381 QualType
5382 ASTContext::getObjCTypeParamType(const ObjCTypeParamDecl *Decl,
5383  ArrayRef<ObjCProtocolDecl *> protocols) const {
5384  // Look in the folding set for an existing type.
5385  llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
5386  ObjCTypeParamType::Profile(ID, Decl, Decl->getUnderlyingType(), protocols);
5387  void *InsertPos = nullptr;
5388  if (ObjCTypeParamType *TypeParam =
5389  ObjCTypeParamTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos))
5390  return QualType(TypeParam, 0);
5391 
5392  // We canonicalize to the underlying type.
5393  QualType Canonical = getCanonicalType(Decl->getUnderlyingType());
5394  if (!protocols.empty()) {
5395  // Apply the protocol qualifers.
5396  bool hasError;
5397  Canonical = getCanonicalType(applyObjCProtocolQualifiers(
5398  Canonical, protocols, hasError, true /*allowOnPointerType*/));
5399  assert(!hasError && "Error when apply protocol qualifier to bound type");
5400  }
5401 
5402  unsigned size = sizeof(ObjCTypeParamType);
5403  size += protocols.size() * sizeof(ObjCProtocolDecl *);
5404  void *mem = Allocate(size, TypeAlignment);
5405  auto *newType = new (mem) ObjCTypeParamType(Decl, Canonical, protocols);
5406 
5407  Types.push_back(newType);
5408  ObjCTypeParamTypes.InsertNode(newType, InsertPos);
5409  return QualType(newType, 0);
5410 }
5411 
5412 void ASTContext::adjustObjCTypeParamBoundType(const ObjCTypeParamDecl *Orig,
5413  ObjCTypeParamDecl *New) const {
5414  New->setTypeSourceInfo(getTrivialTypeSourceInfo(Orig->getUnderlyingType()));
5415  // Update TypeForDecl after updating TypeSourceInfo.
5416  auto NewTypeParamTy = cast<ObjCTypeParamType>(New->getTypeForDecl());
5417  SmallVector<ObjCProtocolDecl *, 8> protocols;
5418  protocols.append(NewTypeParamTy->qual_begin(), NewTypeParamTy->qual_end());
5419  QualType UpdatedTy = getObjCTypeParamType(New, protocols);
5420  New->setTypeForDecl(UpdatedTy.getTypePtr());
5421 }
5422 
5423 /// ObjCObjectAdoptsQTypeProtocols - Checks that protocols in IC's
5424 /// protocol list adopt all protocols in QT's qualified-id protocol
5425 /// list.
5426 bool ASTContext::ObjCObjectAdoptsQTypeProtocols(QualType QT,
5427  ObjCInterfaceDecl *IC) {
5428  if (!QT->isObjCQualifiedIdType())
5429  return false;
5430 
5431  if (const auto *OPT = QT->getAs<ObjCObjectPointerType>()) {
5432  // If both the right and left sides have qualifiers.
5433  for (auto *Proto : OPT->quals()) {
5434  if (!IC->ClassImplementsProtocol(Proto, false))
5435  return false;
5436  }
5437  return true;
5438  }
5439  return false;
5440 }
5441 
5442 /// QIdProtocolsAdoptObjCObjectProtocols - Checks that protocols in
5443 /// QT's qualified-id protocol list adopt all protocols in IDecl's list
5444 /// of protocols.
5445 bool ASTContext::QIdProtocolsAdoptObjCObjectProtocols(QualType QT,
5446  ObjCInterfaceDecl *IDecl) {
5447  if (!QT->isObjCQualifiedIdType())
5448  return false;
5449  const auto *OPT = QT->getAs<ObjCObjectPointerType>();
5450  if (!OPT)
5451  return false;
5452  if (!IDecl->hasDefinition())
5453  return false;
5454  llvm::SmallPtrSet<ObjCProtocolDecl *, 8> InheritedProtocols;
5455  CollectInheritedProtocols(IDecl, InheritedProtocols);
5456  if (InheritedProtocols.empty())
5457  return false;
5458  // Check that if every protocol in list of id<plist> conforms to a protocol
5459  // of IDecl's, then bridge casting is ok.
5460  bool Conforms = false;
5461  for (auto *Proto : OPT->quals()) {
5462  Conforms = false;
5463  for (auto *PI : InheritedProtocols) {
5464  if (ProtocolCompatibleWithProtocol(Proto, PI)) {
5465  Conforms = true;
5466  break;
5467  }
5468  }
5469  if (!Conforms)
5470  break;
5471  }
5472  if (Conforms)
5473  return true;
5474 
5475  for (auto *PI : InheritedProtocols) {
5476  // If both the right and left sides have qualifiers.
5477  bool Adopts = false;
5478  for (auto *Proto : OPT->quals()) {
5479  // return 'true' if 'PI' is in the inheritance hierarchy of Proto
5480  if ((Adopts = ProtocolCompatibleWithProtocol(PI, Proto)))
5481  break;
5482  }
5483  if (!Adopts)
5484  return false;
5485  }
5486  return true;
5487 }
5488 
5489 /// getObjCObjectPointerType - Return a ObjCObjectPointerType type for
5490 /// the given object type.
5491 QualType ASTContext::getObjCObjectPointerType(QualType ObjectT) const {
5492  llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
5493  ObjCObjectPointerType::Profile(ID, ObjectT);
5494 
5495  void *InsertPos = nullptr;
5496  if (ObjCObjectPointerType *QT =
5497  ObjCObjectPointerTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos))
5498  return QualType(QT, 0);
5499 
5500  // Find the canonical object type.
5501  QualType Canonical;
5502  if (!ObjectT.isCanonical()) {
5503  Canonical = getObjCObjectPointerType(getCanonicalType(ObjectT));
5504 
5505  // Regenerate InsertPos.
5506  ObjCObjectPointerTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
5507  }
5508 
5509  // No match.
5510  void *Mem = Allocate(sizeof(ObjCObjectPointerType), TypeAlignment);
5511  auto *QType =
5512  new (Mem) ObjCObjectPointerType(Canonical, ObjectT);
5513 
5514  Types.push_back(QType);
5515  ObjCObjectPointerTypes.InsertNode(QType, InsertPos);
5516  return QualType(QType, 0);
5517 }

5519 /// getObjCInterfaceType - Return the unique reference to the type for the
5520 /// specified ObjC interface decl. The list of protocols is optional.
5521 QualType ASTContext::getObjCInterfaceType(const ObjCInterfaceDecl *Decl,
5522  ObjCInterfaceDecl *PrevDecl) const {
5523  if (Decl->TypeForDecl)
5524  return QualType(Decl->TypeForDecl, 0);
5525 
5526  if (PrevDecl) {
5527  assert(PrevDecl->TypeForDecl && "previous decl has no TypeForDecl");
5528  Decl->TypeForDecl = PrevDecl->TypeForDecl;
5529  return QualType(PrevDecl->TypeForDecl, 0);
5530  }
5531 
5532  // Prefer the definition, if there is one.
5533  if (const ObjCInterfaceDecl *Def = Decl->getDefinition())
5534  Decl = Def;
5535 
5536  void *Mem = Allocate(sizeof(ObjCInterfaceType), TypeAlignment);
5537  auto *T = new (Mem) ObjCInterfaceType(Decl);
5538  Decl->TypeForDecl = T;
5539  Types.push_back(T);
5540  return QualType(T, 0);
5541 }
5542 
5543 /// getTypeOfExprType - Unlike many "get<Type>" functions, we can't unique
5544 /// TypeOfExprType AST's (since expression's are never shared). For example,
5545 /// multiple declarations that refer to "typeof(x)" all contain different
5546 /// DeclRefExpr's. This doesn't effect the type checker, since it operates
5547 /// on canonical type's (which are always unique).
5548 QualType ASTContext::getTypeOfExprType(Expr *tofExpr) const {
5549  TypeOfExprType *toe;
5550  if (tofExpr->isTypeDependent()) {
5551  llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
5552  DependentTypeOfExprType::Profile(ID, *this, tofExpr);
5553 
5554  void *InsertPos = nullptr;
5555  DependentTypeOfExprType *Canon
5556  = DependentTypeOfExprTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
5557  if (Canon) {
5558  // We already have a "canonical" version of an identical, dependent
5559  // typeof(expr) type. Use that as our canonical type.
5560  toe = new (*this, TypeAlignment) TypeOfExprType(tofExpr,
5561  QualType((TypeOfExprType*)Canon, 0));
5562  } else {
5563  // Build a new, canonical typeof(expr) type.
5564  Canon
5565  = new (*this, TypeAlignment) DependentTypeOfExprType(*this, tofExpr);
5566  DependentTypeOfExprTypes.InsertNode(Canon, InsertPos);
5567  toe = Canon;
5568  }
5569  } else {
5570  QualType Canonical = getCanonicalType(tofExpr->getType());
5571  toe = new (*this, TypeAlignment) TypeOfExprType(tofExpr, Canonical);
5572  }
5573  Types.push_back(toe);
5574  return QualType(toe, 0);
5575 }
5576 
5577 /// getTypeOfType - Unlike many "get<Type>" functions, we don't unique
5578 /// TypeOfType nodes. The only motivation to unique these nodes would be
5579 /// memory savings. Since typeof(t) is fairly uncommon, space shouldn't be
5580 /// an issue. This doesn't affect the type checker, since it operates
5581 /// on canonical types (which are always unique).
5582 QualType ASTContext::getTypeOfType(QualType tofType) const {
5583  QualType Canonical = getCanonicalType(tofType);
5584  auto *tot = new (*this, TypeAlignment) TypeOfType(tofType, Canonical);
5585  Types.push_back(tot);
5586  return QualType(tot, 0);
5587 }
5588 
5589 /// getReferenceQualifiedType - Given an expr, will return the type for
5590 /// that expression, as in [dcl.type.simple]p4 but without taking id-expressions
5591 /// and class member access into account.
5592 QualType ASTContext::getReferenceQualifiedType(const Expr *E) const {
5593  // C++11 [dcl.type.simple]p4:
5594  // [...]
5595  QualType T = E->getType();
5596  switch (E->getValueKind()) {
5597  // - otherwise, if e is an xvalue, decltype(e) is T&&, where T is the
5598  // type of e;
5599  case VK_XValue:
5600  return getRValueReferenceType(T);
5601  // - otherwise, if e is an lvalue, decltype(e) is T&, where T is the
5602  // type of e;
5603  case VK_LValue:
5604  return getLValueReferenceType(T);
5605  // - otherwise, decltype(e) is the type of e.
5606  case VK_PRValue:
5607  return T;
5608  }
5609  llvm_unreachable("Unknown value kind");
5610 }
5611 
5612 /// Unlike many "get<Type>" functions, we don't unique DecltypeType
5613 /// nodes. This would never be helpful, since each such type has its own
5614 /// expression, and would not give a significant memory saving, since there
5615 /// is an Expr tree under each such type.
5616 QualType ASTContext::getDecltypeType(Expr *e, QualType UnderlyingType) const {
5617  DecltypeType *dt;
5618 
5619  // C++11 [temp.type]p2:
5620  // If an expression e involves a template parameter, decltype(e) denotes a
5621  // unique dependent type. Two such decltype-specifiers refer to the same
5622  // type only if their expressions are equivalent (14.5.6.1).
5623  if (e->isInstantiationDependent()) {
5624  llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
5625  DependentDecltypeType::Profile(ID, *this, e);
5626 
5627  void *InsertPos = nullptr;
5628  DependentDecltypeType *Canon
5629  = DependentDecltypeTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
5630  if (!Canon) {
5631  // Build a new, canonical decltype(expr) type.
5632  Canon = new (*this, TypeAlignment) DependentDecltypeType(*this, e);
5633  DependentDecltypeTypes.InsertNode(Canon, InsertPos);
5634  }
5635  dt = new (*this, TypeAlignment)
5636  DecltypeType(e, UnderlyingType, QualType((DecltypeType *)Canon, 0));
5637  } else {
5638  dt = new (*this, TypeAlignment)
5639  DecltypeType(e, UnderlyingType, getCanonicalType(UnderlyingType));
5640  }
5641  Types.push_back(dt);
5642  return QualType(dt, 0);
5643 }
5644 
5645 /// getUnaryTransformationType - We don't unique these, since the memory
5646 /// savings are minimal and these are rare.
5647 QualType ASTContext::getUnaryTransformType(QualType BaseType,
5648  QualType UnderlyingType,
5649  UnaryTransformType::UTTKind Kind)
5650  const {
5651  UnaryTransformType *ut = nullptr;
5652 
5653  if (BaseType->isDependentType()) {
5654  // Look in the folding set for an existing type.
5655  llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
5656  DependentUnaryTransformType::Profile(ID, getCanonicalType(BaseType), Kind);
5657 
5658  void *InsertPos = nullptr;
5659  DependentUnaryTransformType *Canon
5660  = DependentUnaryTransformTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
5661 
5662  if (!Canon) {
5663  // Build a new, canonical __underlying_type(type) type.
5664  Canon = new (*this, TypeAlignment)
5665  DependentUnaryTransformType(*this, getCanonicalType(BaseType),
5666  Kind);
5667  DependentUnaryTransformTypes.InsertNode(Canon, InsertPos);
5668  }
5669  ut = new (*this, TypeAlignment) UnaryTransformType (BaseType,
5670  QualType(), Kind,
5671  QualType(Canon, 0));
5672  } else {
5673  QualType CanonType = getCanonicalType(UnderlyingType);
5674  ut = new (*this, TypeAlignment) UnaryTransformType (BaseType,
5675  UnderlyingType, Kind,
5676  CanonType);
5677  }
5678  Types.push_back(ut);
5679  return QualType(ut, 0);
5680 }
5681 
5682 QualType ASTContext::getAutoTypeInternal(
5683  QualType DeducedType, AutoTypeKeyword Keyword, bool IsDependent,
5684  bool IsPack, ConceptDecl *TypeConstraintConcept,
5685  ArrayRef<TemplateArgument> TypeConstraintArgs, bool IsCanon) const {
5686  if (DeducedType.isNull() && Keyword == AutoTypeKeyword::Auto &&
5687  !TypeConstraintConcept && !IsDependent)
5688  return getAutoDeductType();
5689 
5690  // Look in the folding set for an existing type.
5691  void *InsertPos = nullptr;
5692  llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
5693  AutoType::Profile(ID, *this, DeducedType, Keyword, IsDependent,
5694  TypeConstraintConcept, TypeConstraintArgs);
5695  if (AutoType *AT = AutoTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos))
5696  return QualType(AT, 0);
5697 
5698  QualType Canon;
5699  if (!IsCanon) {
5700  if (DeducedType.isNull()) {
5701  SmallVector<TemplateArgument, 4> CanonArgs;
5702  bool AnyNonCanonArgs =
5703  ::getCanonicalTemplateArguments(*this, TypeConstraintArgs, CanonArgs);
5704  if (AnyNonCanonArgs) {
5705  Canon = getAutoTypeInternal(QualType(), Keyword, IsDependent, IsPack,
5706  TypeConstraintConcept, CanonArgs, true);
5707  // Find the insert position again.
5708  AutoTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
5709  }
5710  } else {
5711  Canon = DeducedType.getCanonicalType();
5712  }
5713  }
5714 
5715  void *Mem = Allocate(sizeof(AutoType) +
5716  sizeof(TemplateArgument) * TypeConstraintArgs.size(),
5717  TypeAlignment);
5718  auto *AT = new (Mem) AutoType(
5719  DeducedType, Keyword,
5720  (IsDependent ? TypeDependence::DependentInstantiation
5721  : TypeDependence::None) |
5722  (IsPack ? TypeDependence::UnexpandedPack : TypeDependence::None),
5723  Canon, TypeConstraintConcept, TypeConstraintArgs);
5724  Types.push_back(AT);
5725  AutoTypes.InsertNode(AT, InsertPos);
5726  return QualType(AT, 0);
5727 }

5729 /// getAutoType - Return the uniqued reference to the 'auto' type which has been
5730 /// deduced to the given type, or to the canonical undeduced 'auto' type, or the
5731 /// canonical deduced-but-dependent 'auto' type.
5732 QualType
5733 ASTContext::getAutoType(QualType DeducedType, AutoTypeKeyword Keyword,
5734  bool IsDependent, bool IsPack,
5735  ConceptDecl *TypeConstraintConcept,
5736  ArrayRef<TemplateArgument> TypeConstraintArgs) const {
5737  assert((!IsPack || IsDependent) && "only use IsPack for a dependent pack");
5738  assert((!IsDependent || DeducedType.isNull()) &&
5739  "A dependent auto should be undeduced");
5740  return getAutoTypeInternal(DeducedType, Keyword, IsDependent, IsPack,
5741  TypeConstraintConcept, TypeConstraintArgs);
5742 }

5744 /// Return the uniqued reference to the deduced template specialization type
5745 /// which has been deduced to the given type, or to the canonical undeduced
5746 /// such type, or the canonical deduced-but-dependent such type.
5747 QualType ASTContext::getDeducedTemplateSpecializationType(
5748  TemplateName Template, QualType DeducedType, bool IsDependent) const {
5749  // Look in the folding set for an existing type.
5750  void *InsertPos = nullptr;
5751  llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
5752  DeducedTemplateSpecializationType::Profile(ID, Template, DeducedType,
5753  IsDependent);
5754  if (DeducedTemplateSpecializationType *DTST =
5755  DeducedTemplateSpecializationTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos))
5756  return QualType(DTST, 0);
5757 
5758  auto *DTST = new (*this, TypeAlignment)
5759  DeducedTemplateSpecializationType(Template, DeducedType, IsDependent);
5760  llvm::FoldingSetNodeID TempID;
5761  DTST->Profile(TempID);
5762  assert(ID == TempID && "ID does not match");
5763  Types.push_back(DTST);
5764  DeducedTemplateSpecializationTypes.InsertNode(DTST, InsertPos);
5765  return QualType(DTST, 0);
5766 }

5768 /// getAtomicType - Return the uniqued reference to the atomic type for
5769 /// the given value type.
5770 QualType ASTContext::getAtomicType(QualType T) const {
5771  // Unique pointers, to guarantee there is only one pointer of a particular
5772  // structure.
5773  llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
5774  AtomicType::Profile(ID, T);
5775 
5776  void *InsertPos = nullptr;
5777  if (AtomicType *AT = AtomicTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos))
5778  return QualType(AT, 0);
5779 
5780  // If the atomic value type isn't canonical, this won't be a canonical type
5781  // either, so fill in the canonical type field.
5782  QualType Canonical;
5783  if (!T.isCanonical()) {
5784  Canonical = getAtomicType(getCanonicalType(T));
5785 
5786  // Get the new insert position for the node we care about.
5787  AtomicType *NewIP = AtomicTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
5788  assert(!NewIP && "Shouldn't be in the map!"); (void)NewIP;
5789  }
5790  auto *New = new (*this, TypeAlignment) AtomicType(T, Canonical);
5791  Types.push_back(New);
5792  AtomicTypes.InsertNode(New, InsertPos);
5793  return QualType(New, 0);
5794 }
5795 
5796 /// getAutoDeductType - Get type pattern for deducing against 'auto'.
5797 QualType ASTContext::getAutoDeductType() const {
5798  if (AutoDeductTy.isNull())
5799  AutoDeductTy = QualType(new (*this, TypeAlignment)
5800  AutoType(QualType(), AutoTypeKeyword::Auto,
5801  TypeDependence::None, QualType(),
5802  /*concept*/ nullptr, /*args*/ {}),
5803  0);
5804  return AutoDeductTy;
5805 }

5892 CanQualType ASTContext::getCanonicalParamType(QualType T) const {
5893  // Push qualifiers into arrays, and then discard any remaining
5894  // qualifiers.
5895  T = getCanonicalType(T);
5896  T = getVariableArrayDecayedType(T);
5897  const Type *Ty = T.getTypePtr();
5898  QualType Result;
5899  if (isa<ArrayType>(Ty)) {
5900  Result = getArrayDecayedType(QualType(Ty,0));
5901  } else if (isa<FunctionType>(Ty)) {
5902  Result = getPointerType(QualType(Ty, 0));
5903  } else {
5904  Result = QualType(Ty, 0);
5905  }
5906 
5907  return CanQualType::CreateUnsafe(Result);
5908 }
5909 
5910 QualType ASTContext::getUnqualifiedArrayType(QualType type,
5911  Qualifiers &quals) {
5912  SplitQualType splitType = type.getSplitUnqualifiedType();
5913 
5914  // FIXME: getSplitUnqualifiedType() actually walks all the way to
5915  // the unqualified desugared type and then drops it on the floor.
5916  // We then have to strip that sugar back off with
5917  // getUnqualifiedDesugaredType(), which is silly.
5918  const auto *AT =
5919  dyn_cast<ArrayType>(splitType.Ty->getUnqualifiedDesugaredType());
5920 
5921  // If we don't have an array, just use the results in splitType.
5922  if (!AT) {
5923  quals = splitType.Quals;
5924  return QualType(splitType.Ty, 0);
5925  }
5926 
5927  // Otherwise, recurse on the array's element type.
5928  QualType elementType = AT->getElementType();
5929  QualType unqualElementType = getUnqualifiedArrayType(elementType, quals);
5930 
5931  // If that didn't change the element type, AT has no qualifiers, so we
5932  // can just use the results in splitType.
5933  if (elementType == unqualElementType) {
5934  assert(quals.empty()); // from the recursive call
5935  quals = splitType.Quals;
5936  return QualType(splitType.Ty, 0);
5937  }
5938 
5939  // Otherwise, add in the qualifiers from the outermost type, then
5940  // build the type back up.
5941  quals.addConsistentQualifiers(splitType.Quals);
5942 
5943  if (const auto *CAT = dyn_cast<ConstantArrayType>(AT)) {
5944  return getConstantArrayType(unqualElementType, CAT->getSize(),
5945  CAT->getSizeExpr(), CAT->getSizeModifier(), 0);
5946  }
5947 
5948  if (const auto *IAT = dyn_cast<IncompleteArrayType>(AT)) {
5949  return getIncompleteArrayType(unqualElementType, IAT->getSizeModifier(), 0);
5950  }
5951 
5952  if (const auto *VAT = dyn_cast<VariableArrayType>(AT)) {
5953  return getVariableArrayType(unqualElementType,
5954  VAT->getSizeExpr(),
5955  VAT->getSizeModifier(),
5956  VAT->getIndexTypeCVRQualifiers(),
5957  VAT->getBracketsRange());
5958  }
5959 
5960  const auto *DSAT = cast<DependentSizedArrayType>(AT);
5961  return getDependentSizedArrayType(unqualElementType, DSAT->getSizeExpr(),
5962  DSAT->getSizeModifier(), 0,
5963  SourceRange());
5964 }
5965 
5966 /// Attempt to unwrap two types that may both be array types with the same bound
5967 /// (or both be array types of unknown bound) for the purpose of comparing the
5968 /// cv-decomposition of two types per C++ [conv.qual].
5969 ///
5970 /// \param AllowPiMismatch Allow the Pi1 and Pi2 to differ as described in
5971 /// C++20 [conv.qual], if permitted by the current language mode.
5972 void ASTContext::UnwrapSimilarArrayTypes(QualType &T1, QualType &T2,
5973  bool AllowPiMismatch) {
5974  while (true) {
5975  auto *AT1 = getAsArrayType(T1);
5976  if (!AT1)
5977  return;
5978 
5979  auto *AT2 = getAsArrayType(T2);
5980  if (!AT2)
5981  return;
5982 
5983  // If we don't have two array types with the same constant bound nor two
5984  // incomplete array types, we've unwrapped everything we can.
5985  // C++20 also permits one type to be a constant array type and the other
5986  // to be an incomplete array type.
5987  // FIXME: Consider also unwrapping array of unknown bound and VLA.
5988  if (auto *CAT1 = dyn_cast<ConstantArrayType>(AT1)) {
5989  auto *CAT2 = dyn_cast<ConstantArrayType>(AT2);
5990  if (!((CAT2 && CAT1->getSize() == CAT2->getSize()) ||
5991  (AllowPiMismatch && getLangOpts().CPlusPlus20 &&
5992  isa<IncompleteArrayType>(AT2))))
5993  return;
5994  } else if (isa<IncompleteArrayType>(AT1)) {
5995  if (!(isa<IncompleteArrayType>(AT2) ||
5996  (AllowPiMismatch && getLangOpts().CPlusPlus20 &&
5997  isa<ConstantArrayType>(AT2))))
5998  return;
5999  } else {
6000  return;
6001  }
6002 
6003  T1 = AT1->getElementType();
6004  T2 = AT2->getElementType();
6005  }
6006 }
6007 
6008 /// Attempt to unwrap two types that may be similar (C++ [conv.qual]).
6009 ///
6010 /// If T1 and T2 are both pointer types of the same kind, or both array types
6011 /// with the same bound, unwraps layers from T1 and T2 until a pointer type is
6012 /// unwrapped. Top-level qualifiers on T1 and T2 are ignored.
6013 ///
6014 /// This function will typically be called in a loop that successively
6015 /// "unwraps" pointer and pointer-to-member types to compare them at each
6016 /// level.
6017 ///
6018 /// \param AllowPiMismatch Allow the Pi1 and Pi2 to differ as described in
6019 /// C++20 [conv.qual], if permitted by the current language mode.
6020 ///
6021 /// \return \c true if a pointer type was unwrapped, \c false if we reached a
6022 /// pair of types that can't be unwrapped further.
6023 bool ASTContext::UnwrapSimilarTypes(QualType &T1, QualType &T2,
6024  bool AllowPiMismatch) {
6025  UnwrapSimilarArrayTypes(T1, T2, AllowPiMismatch);
6026 
6027  const auto *T1PtrType = T1->getAs<PointerType>();
6028  const auto *T2PtrType = T2->getAs<PointerType>();
6029  if (T1PtrType && T2PtrType) {
6030  T1 = T1PtrType->getPointeeType();
6031  T2 = T2PtrType->getPointeeType();
6032  return true;
6033  }
6034 
6035  const auto *T1MPType = T1->getAs<MemberPointerType>();
6036  const auto *T2MPType = T2->getAs<MemberPointerType>();
6037  if (T1MPType && T2MPType &&
6038  hasSameUnqualifiedType(QualType(T1MPType->getClass(), 0),
6039  QualType(T2MPType->getClass(), 0))) {
6040  T1 = T1MPType->getPointeeType();
6041  T2 = T2MPType->getPointeeType();
6042  return true;
6043  }
6044 
6045  if (getLangOpts().ObjC) {
6046  const auto *T1OPType = T1->getAs<ObjCObjectPointerType>();
6047  const auto *T2OPType = T2->getAs<ObjCObjectPointerType>();
6048  if (T1OPType && T2OPType) {
6049  T1 = T1OPType->getPointeeType();
6050  T2 = T2OPType->getPointeeType();
6051  return true;
6052  }
6053  }
6054 
6055  // FIXME: Block pointers, too?
6056 
6057  return false;
6058 }
6059 
6060 bool ASTContext::hasSimilarType(QualType T1, QualType T2) {
6061  while (true) {
6062  Qualifiers Quals;
6063  T1 = getUnqualifiedArrayType(T1, Quals);
6064  T2 = getUnqualifiedArrayType(T2, Quals);
6065  if (hasSameType(T1, T2))
6066  return true;
6067  if (!UnwrapSimilarTypes(T1, T2))
6068  return false;
6069  }
6070 }
6071 
6072 bool ASTContext::hasCvrSimilarType(QualType T1, QualType T2) {
6073  while (true) {
6074  Qualifiers Quals1, Quals2;
6075  T1 = getUnqualifiedArrayType(T1, Quals1);
6076  T2 = getUnqualifiedArrayType(T2, Quals2);
6077 
6078  Quals1.removeCVRQualifiers();
6079  Quals2.removeCVRQualifiers();
6080  if (Quals1 != Quals2)
6081  return false;
6082 
6083  if (hasSameType(T1, T2))
6084  return true;
6085 
6086  if (!UnwrapSimilarTypes(T1, T2, /*AllowPiMismatch*/ false))
6087  return false;
6088  }
6089 }
