7451 static std::string charUnitsToString(const CharUnits &CU) {
7452  return llvm::itostr(CU.getQuantity());
7453 }
7454 
7455 /// getObjCEncodingForBlock - Return the encoded type for this block
7456 /// declaration.
7457 std::string ASTContext::getObjCEncodingForBlock(const BlockExpr *Expr) const {
7458  std::string S;
7459 
7460  const BlockDecl *Decl = Expr->getBlockDecl();
7461  QualType BlockTy =
7462  Expr->getType()->castAs<BlockPointerType>()->getPointeeType();
7463  QualType BlockReturnTy = BlockTy->castAs<FunctionType>()->getReturnType();
7464  // Encode result type.
7465  if (getLangOpts().EncodeExtendedBlockSig)
7466  getObjCEncodingForMethodParameter(Decl::OBJC_TQ_None, BlockReturnTy, S,
7467  true /*Extended*/);
7468  else
7469  getObjCEncodingForType(BlockReturnTy, S);
7470  // Compute size of all parameters.
7471  // Start with computing size of a pointer in number of bytes.
7472  // FIXME: There might(should) be a better way of doing this computation!
7473  CharUnits PtrSize = getTypeSizeInChars(VoidPtrTy);
7474  CharUnits ParmOffset = PtrSize;
7475  for (auto PI : Decl->parameters()) {
7476  QualType PType = PI->getType();
7477  CharUnits sz = getObjCEncodingTypeSize(PType);
7478  if (sz.isZero())
7479  continue;
7480  assert(sz.isPositive() && "BlockExpr - Incomplete param type");
7481  ParmOffset += sz;
7482  }
7483  // Size of the argument frame
7484  S += charUnitsToString(ParmOffset);
7485  // Block pointer and offset.
7486  S += "@?0";
7487 
7488  // Argument types.
7489  ParmOffset = PtrSize;
7490  for (auto PVDecl : Decl->parameters()) {
7491  QualType PType = PVDecl->getOriginalType();
7492  if (const auto *AT =
7493  dyn_cast<ArrayType>(PType->getCanonicalTypeInternal())) {
7494  // Use array's original type only if it has known number of
7495  // elements.
7496  if (!isa<ConstantArrayType>(AT))
7497  PType = PVDecl->getType();
7498  } else if (PType->isFunctionType())
7499  PType = PVDecl->getType();
7500  if (getLangOpts().EncodeExtendedBlockSig)
7501  getObjCEncodingForMethodParameter(Decl::OBJC_TQ_None, PType,
7502  S, true /*Extended*/);
7503  else
7504  getObjCEncodingForType(PType, S);
7505  S += charUnitsToString(ParmOffset);
7506  ParmOffset += getObjCEncodingTypeSize(PType);
7507  }
7508 
7509  return S;
7510 }
7511 
7512 std::string
7513 ASTContext::getObjCEncodingForFunctionDecl(const FunctionDecl *Decl) const {
7514  std::string S;
7515  // Encode result type.
7516  getObjCEncodingForType(Decl->getReturnType(), S);
7517  CharUnits ParmOffset;
7518  // Compute size of all parameters.
7519  for (auto PI : Decl->parameters()) {
7520  QualType PType = PI->getType();
7521  CharUnits sz = getObjCEncodingTypeSize(PType);
7522  if (sz.isZero())
7523  continue;
7524 
7525  assert(sz.isPositive() &&
7526  "getObjCEncodingForFunctionDecl - Incomplete param type");
7527  ParmOffset += sz;
7528  }
7529  S += charUnitsToString(ParmOffset);
7530  ParmOffset = CharUnits::Zero();
7531 
7532  // Argument types.
7533  for (auto PVDecl : Decl->parameters()) {
7534  QualType PType = PVDecl->getOriginalType();
7535  if (const auto *AT =
7536  dyn_cast<ArrayType>(PType->getCanonicalTypeInternal())) {
7537  // Use array's original type only if it has known number of
7538  // elements.
7539  if (!isa<ConstantArrayType>(AT))
7540  PType = PVDecl->getType();
7541  } else if (PType->isFunctionType())
7542  PType = PVDecl->getType();
7543  getObjCEncodingForType(PType, S);
7544  S += charUnitsToString(ParmOffset);
7545  ParmOffset += getObjCEncodingTypeSize(PType);
7546  }
7547 
7548  return S;
7549 }
7550 
7551 /// getObjCEncodingForMethodParameter - Return the encoded type for a single
7552 /// method parameter or return type. If Extended, include class names and
7553 /// block object types.
7554 void ASTContext::getObjCEncodingForMethodParameter(Decl::ObjCDeclQualifier QT,
7555  QualType T, std::string& S,
7556  bool Extended) const {
7557  // Encode type qualifier, 'in', 'inout', etc. for the parameter.
7558  getObjCEncodingForTypeQualifier(QT, S);
7559  // Encode parameter type.
7560  ObjCEncOptions Options = ObjCEncOptions()
7561  .setExpandPointedToStructures()
7562  .setExpandStructures()
7563  .setIsOutermostType();
7564  if (Extended)
7565  Options.setEncodeBlockParameters().setEncodeClassNames();
7566  getObjCEncodingForTypeImpl(T, S, Options, /*Field=*/nullptr);
7567 }
7568 
7569 /// getObjCEncodingForMethodDecl - Return the encoded type for this method
7570 /// declaration.
7571 std::string ASTContext::getObjCEncodingForMethodDecl(const ObjCMethodDecl *Decl,
7572  bool Extended) const {
7573  // FIXME: This is not very efficient.
7574  // Encode return type.
7575  std::string S;
7576  getObjCEncodingForMethodParameter(Decl->getObjCDeclQualifier(),
7577  Decl->getReturnType(), S, Extended);
7578  // Compute size of all parameters.
7579  // Start with computing size of a pointer in number of bytes.
7580  // FIXME: There might(should) be a better way of doing this computation!
7581  CharUnits PtrSize = getTypeSizeInChars(VoidPtrTy);
7582  // The first two arguments (self and _cmd) are pointers; account for
7583  // their size.
7584  CharUnits ParmOffset = 2 * PtrSize;
7585  for (ObjCMethodDecl::param_const_iterator PI = Decl->param_begin(),
7586  E = Decl->sel_param_end(); PI != E; ++PI) {
7587  QualType PType = (*PI)->getType();
7588  CharUnits sz = getObjCEncodingTypeSize(PType);
7589  if (sz.isZero())
7590  continue;
7591 
7592  assert(sz.isPositive() &&
7593  "getObjCEncodingForMethodDecl - Incomplete param type");
7594  ParmOffset += sz;
7595  }
7596  S += charUnitsToString(ParmOffset);
7597  S += "@0:";
7598  S += charUnitsToString(PtrSize);
7599 
7600  // Argument types.
7601  ParmOffset = 2 * PtrSize;
7602  for (ObjCMethodDecl::param_const_iterator PI = Decl->param_begin(),
7603  E = Decl->sel_param_end(); PI != E; ++PI) {
7604  const ParmVarDecl *PVDecl = *PI;
7605  QualType PType = PVDecl->getOriginalType();
7606  if (const auto *AT =
7607  dyn_cast<ArrayType>(PType->getCanonicalTypeInternal())) {
7608  // Use array's original type only if it has known number of
7609  // elements.
7610  if (!isa<ConstantArrayType>(AT))
7611  PType = PVDecl->getType();
7612  } else if (PType->isFunctionType())
7613  PType = PVDecl->getType();
7614  getObjCEncodingForMethodParameter(PVDecl->getObjCDeclQualifier(),
7615  PType, S, Extended);
7616  S += charUnitsToString(ParmOffset);
7617  ParmOffset += getObjCEncodingTypeSize(PType);
7618  }
7619 
7620  return S;
7621 }
7622 
7623 ObjCPropertyImplDecl *
7624 ASTContext::getObjCPropertyImplDeclForPropertyDecl(
7625  const ObjCPropertyDecl *PD,
7626  const Decl *Container) const {
7627  if (!Container)
7628  return nullptr;
7629  if (const auto *CID = dyn_cast<ObjCCategoryImplDecl>(Container)) {
7630  for (auto *PID : CID->property_impls())
7631  if (PID->getPropertyDecl() == PD)
7632  return PID;
7633  } else {
7634  const auto *OID = cast<ObjCImplementationDecl>(Container);
7635  for (auto *PID : OID->property_impls())
7636  if (PID->getPropertyDecl() == PD)
7637  return PID;
7638  }
7639  return nullptr;
7640 }
7641 
7642 /// getObjCEncodingForPropertyDecl - Return the encoded type for this
7643 /// property declaration. If non-NULL, Container must be either an
7644 /// ObjCCategoryImplDecl or ObjCImplementationDecl; it should only be
7645 /// NULL when getting encodings for protocol properties.
7646 /// Property attributes are stored as a comma-delimited C string. The simple
7647 /// attributes readonly and bycopy are encoded as single characters. The
7648 /// parametrized attributes, getter=name, setter=name, and ivar=name, are
7649 /// encoded as single characters, followed by an identifier. Property types
7650 /// are also encoded as a parametrized attribute. The characters used to encode
7651 /// these attributes are defined by the following enumeration:
7652 /// @code
7653 /// enum PropertyAttributes {
7654 /// kPropertyReadOnly = 'R', // property is read-only.
7655 /// kPropertyBycopy = 'C', // property is a copy of the value last assigned
7656 /// kPropertyByref = '&', // property is a reference to the value last assigned
7657 /// kPropertyDynamic = 'D', // property is dynamic
7658 /// kPropertyGetter = 'G', // followed by getter selector name
7659 /// kPropertySetter = 'S', // followed by setter selector name
7660 /// kPropertyInstanceVariable = 'V' // followed by instance variable name
7661 /// kPropertyType = 'T' // followed by old-style type encoding.
7662 /// kPropertyWeak = 'W' // 'weak' property
7663 /// kPropertyStrong = 'P' // property GC'able
7664 /// kPropertyNonAtomic = 'N' // property non-atomic
7665 /// };
7666 /// @endcode
7667 std::string
7668 ASTContext::getObjCEncodingForPropertyDecl(const ObjCPropertyDecl *PD,
7669  const Decl *Container) const {
7670  // Collect information from the property implementation decl(s).
7671  bool Dynamic = false;
7672  ObjCPropertyImplDecl *SynthesizePID = nullptr;
7673 
7674  if (ObjCPropertyImplDecl *PropertyImpDecl =
7675  getObjCPropertyImplDeclForPropertyDecl(PD, Container)) {
7676  if (PropertyImpDecl->getPropertyImplementation() == ObjCPropertyImplDecl::Dynamic)
7677  Dynamic = true;
7678  else
7679  SynthesizePID = PropertyImpDecl;
7680  }
7681 
7682  // FIXME: This is not very efficient.
7683  std::string S = "T";
7684 
7685  // Encode result type.
7686  // GCC has some special rules regarding encoding of properties which
7687  // closely resembles encoding of ivars.
7688  getObjCEncodingForPropertyType(PD->getType(), S);
7689 
7690  if (PD->isReadOnly()) {
7691  S += ",R";
7692  if (PD->getPropertyAttributes() & ObjCPropertyAttribute::kind_copy)
7693  S += ",C";
7694  if (PD->getPropertyAttributes() & ObjCPropertyAttribute::kind_retain)
7695  S += ",&";
7696  if (PD->getPropertyAttributes() & ObjCPropertyAttribute::kind_weak)
7697  S += ",W";
7698  } else {
7699  switch (PD->getSetterKind()) {
7700  case ObjCPropertyDecl::Assign: break;
7701  case ObjCPropertyDecl::Copy: S += ",C"; break;
7702  case ObjCPropertyDecl::Retain: S += ",&"; break;
7703  case ObjCPropertyDecl::Weak: S += ",W"; break;
7704  }
7705  }
7706 
7707  // It really isn't clear at all what this means, since properties
7708  // are "dynamic by default".
7709  if (Dynamic)
7710  S += ",D";
7711 
7712  if (PD->getPropertyAttributes() & ObjCPropertyAttribute::kind_nonatomic)
7713  S += ",N";
7714 
7715  if (PD->getPropertyAttributes() & ObjCPropertyAttribute::kind_getter) {
7716  S += ",G";
7717  S += PD->getGetterName().getAsString();
7718  }
7719 
7720  if (PD->getPropertyAttributes() & ObjCPropertyAttribute::kind_setter) {
7721  S += ",S";
7722  S += PD->getSetterName().getAsString();
7723  }
7724 
7725  if (SynthesizePID) {
7726  const ObjCIvarDecl *OID = SynthesizePID->getPropertyIvarDecl();
7727  S += ",V";
7728  S += OID->getNameAsString();
7729  }
7730 
7731  // FIXME: OBJCGC: weak & strong
7732  return S;
7733 }
7734 
7735 /// getLegacyIntegralTypeEncoding -
7736 /// Another legacy compatibility encoding: 32-bit longs are encoded as
7737 /// 'l' or 'L' , but not always. For typedefs, we need to use
7738 /// 'i' or 'I' instead if encoding a struct field, or a pointer!
7739 void ASTContext::getLegacyIntegralTypeEncoding (QualType &PointeeTy) const {
7740  if (isa<TypedefType>(PointeeTy.getTypePtr())) {
7741  if (const auto *BT = PointeeTy->getAs<BuiltinType>()) {
7742  if (BT->getKind() == BuiltinType::ULong && getIntWidth(PointeeTy) == 32)
7743  PointeeTy = UnsignedIntTy;
7744  else
7745  if (BT->getKind() == BuiltinType::Long && getIntWidth(PointeeTy) == 32)
7746  PointeeTy = IntTy;
7747  }
7748  }
7749 }
7750 
7751 void ASTContext::getObjCEncodingForType(QualType T, std::string& S,
7752  const FieldDecl *Field,
7753  QualType *NotEncodedT) const {
7754  // We follow the behavior of gcc, expanding structures which are
7755  // directly pointed to, and expanding embedded structures. Note that
7756  // these rules are sufficient to prevent recursive encoding of the
7757  // same type.
7758  getObjCEncodingForTypeImpl(T, S,
7759  ObjCEncOptions()
7760  .setExpandPointedToStructures()
7761  .setExpandStructures()
7762  .setIsOutermostType(),
7763  Field, NotEncodedT);
7764 }
7765 
7766 void ASTContext::getObjCEncodingForPropertyType(QualType T,
7767  std::string& S) const {
7768  // Encode result type.
7769  // GCC has some special rules regarding encoding of properties which
7770  // closely resembles encoding of ivars.
7771  getObjCEncodingForTypeImpl(T, S,
7772  ObjCEncOptions()
7773  .setExpandPointedToStructures()
7774  .setExpandStructures()
7775  .setIsOutermostType()
7776  .setEncodingProperty(),
7777  /*Field=*/nullptr);
7778 }
7779 
7780 static char getObjCEncodingForPrimitiveType(const ASTContext *C,
7781  const BuiltinType *BT) {
7782  BuiltinType::Kind kind = BT->getKind();
7783  switch (kind) {
7784  case BuiltinType::Void: return 'v';
7785  case BuiltinType::Bool: return 'B';
7786  case BuiltinType::Char8:
7787  case BuiltinType::Char_U:
7788  case BuiltinType::UChar: return 'C';
7789  case BuiltinType::Char16:
7790  case BuiltinType::UShort: return 'S';
7791  case BuiltinType::Char32:
7792  case BuiltinType::UInt: return 'I';
7793  case BuiltinType::ULong:
7794  return C->getTargetInfo().getLongWidth() == 32 ? 'L' : 'Q';
7795  case BuiltinType::UInt128: return 'T';
7796  case BuiltinType::ULongLong: return 'Q';
7797  case BuiltinType::Char_S:
7798  case BuiltinType::SChar: return 'c';
7799  case BuiltinType::Short: return 's';
7800  case BuiltinType::WChar_S:
7801  case BuiltinType::WChar_U:
7802  case BuiltinType::Int: return 'i';
7803  case BuiltinType::Long:
7804  return C->getTargetInfo().getLongWidth() == 32 ? 'l' : 'q';
7805  case BuiltinType::LongLong: return 'q';
7806  case BuiltinType::Int128: return 't';
7807  case BuiltinType::Float: return 'f';
7808  case BuiltinType::Double: return 'd';
7809  case BuiltinType::LongDouble: return 'D';
7810  case BuiltinType::NullPtr: return '*'; // like char*
7811 
7812  case BuiltinType::BFloat16:
7813  case BuiltinType::Float16:
7814  case BuiltinType::Float128:
7815  case BuiltinType::Ibm128:
7816  case BuiltinType::Half:
7817  case BuiltinType::ShortAccum:
7818  case BuiltinType::Accum:
7819  case BuiltinType::LongAccum:
7820  case BuiltinType::UShortAccum:
7821  case BuiltinType::UAccum:
7822  case BuiltinType::ULongAccum:
7823  case BuiltinType::ShortFract:
7824  case BuiltinType::Fract:
7825  case BuiltinType::LongFract:
7826  case BuiltinType::UShortFract:
7827  case BuiltinType::UFract:
7828  case BuiltinType::ULongFract:
7829  case BuiltinType::SatShortAccum:
7830  case BuiltinType::SatAccum:
7831  case BuiltinType::SatLongAccum:
7832  case BuiltinType::SatUShortAccum:
7833  case BuiltinType::SatUAccum:
7834  case BuiltinType::SatULongAccum:
7835  case BuiltinType::SatShortFract:
7836  case BuiltinType::SatFract:
7837  case BuiltinType::SatLongFract:
7838  case BuiltinType::SatUShortFract:
7839  case BuiltinType::SatUFract:
7840  case BuiltinType::SatULongFract:
7841  // FIXME: potentially need @encodes for these!
7842  return ' ';
7843 
7844 #define SVE_TYPE(Name, Id, SingletonId) \
7845  case BuiltinType::Id:
7846 #include "clang/Basic/AArch64SVEACLETypes.def"
7847 #define RVV_TYPE(Name, Id, SingletonId) case BuiltinType::Id:
7848 #include "clang/Basic/RISCVVTypes.def"
7849  {
7850  DiagnosticsEngine &Diags = C->getDiagnostics();
7851  unsigned DiagID = Diags.getCustomDiagID(DiagnosticsEngine::Error,
7852  "cannot yet @encode type %0");
7853  Diags.Report(DiagID) << BT->getName(C->getPrintingPolicy());
7854  return ' ';
7855  }
7856 
7857  case BuiltinType::ObjCId:
7858  case BuiltinType::ObjCClass:
7859  case BuiltinType::ObjCSel:
7860  llvm_unreachable("@encoding ObjC primitive type");
7861 
7862  // OpenCL and placeholder types don't need @encodings.
7863 #define IMAGE_TYPE(ImgType, Id, SingletonId, Access, Suffix) \
7864  case BuiltinType::Id:
7865 #include "clang/Basic/OpenCLImageTypes.def"
7866 #define IMAGE_TYPE(ImgType, Id, SingletonId, Access, Suffix) \
7867  case BuiltinType::Sampled##Id:
7868 #define IMAGE_WRITE_TYPE(Type, Id, Ext)
7869 #define IMAGE_READ_WRITE_TYPE(Type, Id, Ext)
7870 #include "clang/Basic/OpenCLImageTypes.def"
7871 #define EXT_OPAQUE_TYPE(ExtType, Id, Ext) \
7872  case BuiltinType::Id:
7873 #include "clang/Basic/OpenCLExtensionTypes.def"
7874  case BuiltinType::OCLEvent:
7875  case BuiltinType::OCLClkEvent:
7876  case BuiltinType::OCLQueue:
7877  case BuiltinType::OCLReserveID:
7878  case BuiltinType::OCLSampler:
7879  case BuiltinType::Dependent:
7880 #define PPC_VECTOR_TYPE(Name, Id, Size) \
7881  case BuiltinType::Id:
7882 #include "clang/Basic/PPCTypes.def"
7883 #define BUILTIN_TYPE(KIND, ID)
7884 #define PLACEHOLDER_TYPE(KIND, ID) \
7885  case BuiltinType::KIND:
7886 #include "clang/AST/BuiltinTypes.def"
7887  llvm_unreachable("invalid builtin type for @encode");
7888  }
7889  llvm_unreachable("invalid BuiltinType::Kind value");
7890 }
7891 
7892 static char ObjCEncodingForEnumType(const ASTContext *C, const EnumType *ET) {
7893  EnumDecl *Enum = ET->getDecl();
7894 
7895  // The encoding of an non-fixed enum type is always 'i', regardless of size.
7896  if (!Enum->isFixed())
7897  return 'i';
7898 
7899  // The encoding of a fixed enum type matches its fixed underlying type.
7900  const auto *BT = Enum->getIntegerType()->castAs<BuiltinType>();
7901  return getObjCEncodingForPrimitiveType(C, BT);
7902 }
7903 
7904 static void EncodeBitField(const ASTContext *Ctx, std::string& S,
7905  QualType T, const FieldDecl *FD) {
7906  assert(FD->isBitField() && "not a bitfield - getObjCEncodingForTypeImpl");
7907  S += 'b';
7908  // The NeXT runtime encodes bit fields as b followed by the number of bits.
7909  // The GNU runtime requires more information; bitfields are encoded as b,
7910  // then the offset (in bits) of the first element, then the type of the
7911  // bitfield, then the size in bits. For example, in this structure:
7912  //
7913  // struct
7914  // {
7915  // int integer;
7916  // int flags:2;
7917  // };
7918  // On a 32-bit system, the encoding for flags would be b2 for the NeXT
7919  // runtime, but b32i2 for the GNU runtime. The reason for this extra
7920  // information is not especially sensible, but we're stuck with it for
7921  // compatibility with GCC, although providing it breaks anything that
7922  // actually uses runtime introspection and wants to work on both runtimes...
7923  if (Ctx->getLangOpts().ObjCRuntime.isGNUFamily()) {
7924  uint64_t Offset;
7925 
7926  if (const auto *IVD = dyn_cast<ObjCIvarDecl>(FD)) {
7927  Offset = Ctx->lookupFieldBitOffset(IVD->getContainingInterface(), nullptr,
7928  IVD);
7929  } else {
7930  const RecordDecl *RD = FD->getParent();
7931  const ASTRecordLayout &RL = Ctx->getASTRecordLayout(RD);
7932  Offset = RL.getFieldOffset(FD->getFieldIndex());
7933  }
7934 
7935  S += llvm::utostr(Offset);
7936 
7937  if (const auto *ET = T->getAs<EnumType>())
7938  S += ObjCEncodingForEnumType(Ctx, ET);
7939  else {
7940  const auto *BT = T->castAs<BuiltinType>();
7941  S += getObjCEncodingForPrimitiveType(Ctx, BT);
7942  }
7943  }
7944  S += llvm::utostr(FD->getBitWidthValue(*Ctx));
7945 }
7946 
7947 // Helper function for determining whether the encoded type string would include
7948 // a template specialization type.
7949 static bool hasTemplateSpecializationInEncodedString(const Type *T,
7950  bool VisitBasesAndFields) {
7951  T = T->getBaseElementTypeUnsafe();
7952 
7953  if (auto *PT = T->getAs<PointerType>())
7954  return hasTemplateSpecializationInEncodedString(
7955  PT->getPointeeType().getTypePtr(), false);
7956 
7957  auto *CXXRD = T->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
7958 
7959  if (!CXXRD)
7960  return false;
7961 
7962  if (isa<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(CXXRD))
7963  return true;
7964 
7965  if (!CXXRD->hasDefinition() || !VisitBasesAndFields)
7966  return false;
7967 
7968  for (auto B : CXXRD->bases())
7969  if (hasTemplateSpecializationInEncodedString(B.getType().getTypePtr(),
7970  true))
7971  return true;
7972 
7973  for (auto *FD : CXXRD->fields())
7974  if (hasTemplateSpecializationInEncodedString(FD->getType().getTypePtr(),
7975  true))
7976  return true;
7977 
7978  return false;
7979 }
7980 
7981 // FIXME: Use SmallString for accumulating string.
7982 void ASTContext::getObjCEncodingForTypeImpl(QualType T, std::string &S,
7983  const ObjCEncOptions Options,
7984  const FieldDecl *FD,
7985  QualType *NotEncodedT) const {
7986  CanQualType CT = getCanonicalType(T);
7987  switch (CT->getTypeClass()) {
7988  case Type::Builtin:
7989  case Type::Enum:
7990  if (FD && FD->isBitField())
7991  return EncodeBitField(this, S, T, FD);
7992  if (const auto *BT = dyn_cast<BuiltinType>(CT))
7993  S += getObjCEncodingForPrimitiveType(this, BT);
7994  else
7995  S += ObjCEncodingForEnumType(this, cast<EnumType>(CT));
7996  return;
7997 
7998  case Type::Complex:
7999  S += 'j';
8000  getObjCEncodingForTypeImpl(T->castAs<ComplexType>()->getElementType(), S,
8001  ObjCEncOptions(),
8002  /*Field=*/nullptr);
8003  return;
8004 
8005  case Type::Atomic:
8006  S += 'A';
8007  getObjCEncodingForTypeImpl(T->castAs<AtomicType>()->getValueType(), S,
8008  ObjCEncOptions(),
8009  /*Field=*/nullptr);
8010  return;
8011 
8012  // encoding for pointer or reference types.
8013  case Type::Pointer:
8014  case Type::LValueReference:
8015  case Type::RValueReference: {
8016  QualType PointeeTy;
8017  if (isa<PointerType>(CT)) {
8018  const auto *PT = T->castAs<PointerType>();
8019  if (PT->isObjCSelType()) {
8020  S += ':';
8021  return;
8022  }
8023  PointeeTy = PT->getPointeeType();
8024  } else {
8025  PointeeTy = T->castAs<ReferenceType>()->getPointeeType();
8026  }
8027 
8028  bool isReadOnly = false;
8029  // For historical/compatibility reasons, the read-only qualifier of the
8030  // pointee gets emitted _before_ the '^'. The read-only qualifier of
8031  // the pointer itself gets ignored, _unless_ we are looking at a typedef!
8032  // Also, do not emit the 'r' for anything but the outermost type!
8033  if (isa<TypedefType>(T.getTypePtr())) {
8034  if (Options.IsOutermostType() && T.isConstQualified()) {
8035  isReadOnly = true;
8036  S += 'r';
8037  }
8038  } else if (Options.IsOutermostType()) {
8039  QualType P = PointeeTy;
8040  while (auto PT = P->getAs<PointerType>())
8041  P = PT->getPointeeType();
8042  if (P.isConstQualified()) {
8043  isReadOnly = true;
8044  S += 'r';
8045  }
8046  }
8047  if (isReadOnly) {
8048  // Another legacy compatibility encoding. Some ObjC qualifier and type
8049  // combinations need to be rearranged.
8050  // Rewrite "in const" from "nr" to "rn"
8051  if (StringRef(S).endswith("nr"))
8052  S.replace(S.end()-2, S.end(), "rn");
8053  }
8054 
8055  if (PointeeTy->isCharType()) {
8056  // char pointer types should be encoded as '*' unless it is a
8057  // type that has been typedef'd to 'BOOL'.
8058  if (!isTypeTypedefedAsBOOL(PointeeTy)) {
8059  S += '*';
8060  return;
8061  }
8062  } else if (const auto *RTy = PointeeTy->getAs<RecordType>()) {
8063  // GCC binary compat: Need to convert "struct objc_class *" to "#".
8064  if (RTy->getDecl()->getIdentifier() == &Idents.get("objc_class")) {
8065  S += '#';
8066  return;
8067  }
8068  // GCC binary compat: Need to convert "struct objc_object *" to "@".
8069  if (RTy->getDecl()->getIdentifier() == &Idents.get("objc_object")) {
8070  S += '@';
8071  return;
8072  }
8073  // If the encoded string for the class includes template names, just emit
8074  // "^v" for pointers to the class.
8075  if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus &&
8076  (!getLangOpts().EncodeCXXClassTemplateSpec &&
8077  hasTemplateSpecializationInEncodedString(
8078  RTy, Options.ExpandPointedToStructures()))) {
8079  S += "^v";
8080  return;
8081  }
8082  // fall through...
8083  }
8084  S += '^';
8085  getLegacyIntegralTypeEncoding(PointeeTy);
8086 
8087  ObjCEncOptions NewOptions;
8088  if (Options.ExpandPointedToStructures())
8089  NewOptions.setExpandStructures();
8090  getObjCEncodingForTypeImpl(PointeeTy, S, NewOptions,
8091  /*Field=*/nullptr, NotEncodedT);
8092  return;
8093  }
8094 
8095  case Type::ConstantArray:
8096  case Type::IncompleteArray:
8097  case Type::VariableArray: {
8098  const auto *AT = cast<ArrayType>(CT);
8099 
8100  if (isa<IncompleteArrayType>(AT) && !Options.IsStructField()) {
8101  // Incomplete arrays are encoded as a pointer to the array element.
8102  S += '^';
8103 
8104  getObjCEncodingForTypeImpl(
8105  AT->getElementType(), S,
8106  Options.keepingOnly(ObjCEncOptions().setExpandStructures()), FD);
8107  } else {
8108  S += '[';
8109 
8110  if (const auto *CAT = dyn_cast<ConstantArrayType>(AT))
8111  S += llvm::utostr(CAT->getSize().getZExtValue());
8112  else {
8113  //Variable length arrays are encoded as a regular array with 0 elements.
8114  assert((isa<VariableArrayType>(AT) || isa<IncompleteArrayType>(AT)) &&
8115  "Unknown array type!");
8116  S += '0';
8117  }
8118 
8119  getObjCEncodingForTypeImpl(
8120  AT->getElementType(), S,
8121  Options.keepingOnly(ObjCEncOptions().setExpandStructures()), FD,
8122  NotEncodedT);
8123  S += ']';
8124  }
8125  return;
8126  }
8127 
8128  case Type::FunctionNoProto:
8129  case Type::FunctionProto:
8130  S += '?';
8131  return;
8132 
8133  case Type::Record: {
8134  RecordDecl *RDecl = cast<RecordType>(CT)->getDecl();
8135  S += RDecl->isUnion() ? '(' : '{';
8136  // Anonymous structures print as '?'
8137  if (const IdentifierInfo *II = RDecl->getIdentifier()) {
8138  S += II->getName();
8139  if (const auto *Spec = dyn_cast<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(RDecl)) {
8140  const TemplateArgumentList &TemplateArgs = Spec->getTemplateArgs();
8141  llvm::raw_string_ostream OS(S);
8142  printTemplateArgumentList(OS, TemplateArgs.asArray(),
8143  getPrintingPolicy());
8144  }
8145  } else {
8146  S += '?';
8147  }
8148  if (Options.ExpandStructures()) {
8149  S += '=';
8150  if (!RDecl->isUnion()) {
8151  getObjCEncodingForStructureImpl(RDecl, S, FD, true, NotEncodedT);
8152  } else {
8153  for (const auto *Field : RDecl->fields()) {
8154  if (FD) {
8155  S += '"';
8156  S += Field->getNameAsString();
8157  S += '"';
8158  }
8159 
8160  // Special case bit-fields.
8161  if (Field->isBitField()) {
8162  getObjCEncodingForTypeImpl(Field->getType(), S,
8163  ObjCEncOptions().setExpandStructures(),
8164  Field);
8165  } else {
8166  QualType qt = Field->getType();
8167  getLegacyIntegralTypeEncoding(qt);
8168  getObjCEncodingForTypeImpl(
8169  qt, S,
8170  ObjCEncOptions().setExpandStructures().setIsStructField(), FD,
8171  NotEncodedT);
8172  }
8173  }
8174  }
8175  }
8176  S += RDecl->isUnion() ? ')' : '}';
8177  return;
8178  }
8179 
8180  case Type::BlockPointer: {
8181  const auto *BT = T->castAs<BlockPointerType>();
8182  S += "@?"; // Unlike a pointer-to-function, which is "^?".
8183  if (Options.EncodeBlockParameters()) {
8184  const auto *FT = BT->getPointeeType()->castAs<FunctionType>();
8185 
8186  S += '<';
8187  // Block return type
8188  getObjCEncodingForTypeImpl(FT->getReturnType(), S,
8189  Options.forComponentType(), FD, NotEncodedT);
8190  // Block self
8191  S += "@?";
8192  // Block parameters
8193  if (const auto *FPT = dyn_cast<FunctionProtoType>(FT)) {
8194  for (const auto &I : FPT->param_types())
8195  getObjCEncodingForTypeImpl(I, S, Options.forComponentType(), FD,
8196  NotEncodedT);
8197  }
8198  S += '>';
8199  }
8200  return;
8201  }
8202 
8203  case Type::ObjCObject: {
8204  // hack to match legacy encoding of *id and *Class
8205  QualType Ty = getObjCObjectPointerType(CT);
8206  if (Ty->isObjCIdType()) {
8207  S += "{objc_object=}";
8208  return;
8209  }
8210  else if (Ty->isObjCClassType()) {
8211  S += "{objc_class=}";
8212  return;
8213  }
8214  // TODO: Double check to make sure this intentionally falls through.
8215  LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
8216  }
8217 
8218  case Type::ObjCInterface: {
8219  // Ignore protocol qualifiers when mangling at this level.
8220  // @encode(class_name)
8221  ObjCInterfaceDecl *OI = T->castAs<ObjCObjectType>()->getInterface();
8222  S += '{';
8223  S += OI->getObjCRuntimeNameAsString();
8224  if (Options.ExpandStructures()) {
8225  S += '=';
8226  SmallVector<const ObjCIvarDecl*, 32> Ivars;
8227  DeepCollectObjCIvars(OI, true, Ivars);
8228  for (unsigned i = 0, e = Ivars.size(); i != e; ++i) {
8229  const FieldDecl *Field = Ivars[i];
8230  if (Field->isBitField())
8231  getObjCEncodingForTypeImpl(Field->getType(), S,
8232  ObjCEncOptions().setExpandStructures(),
8233  Field);
8234  else
8235  getObjCEncodingForTypeImpl(Field->getType(), S,
8236  ObjCEncOptions().setExpandStructures(), FD,
8237  NotEncodedT);
8238  }
8239  }
8240  S += '}';
8241  return;
8242  }
8243 
8244  case Type::ObjCObjectPointer: {
8245  const auto *OPT = T->castAs<ObjCObjectPointerType>();
8246  if (OPT->isObjCIdType()) {
8247  S += '@';
8248  return;
8249  }
8250 
8251  if (OPT->isObjCClassType() || OPT->isObjCQualifiedClassType()) {
8252  // FIXME: Consider if we need to output qualifiers for 'Class<p>'.
8253  // Since this is a binary compatibility issue, need to consult with
8254  // runtime folks. Fortunately, this is a *very* obscure construct.
8255  S += '#';
8256  return;
8257  }
8258 
8259  if (OPT->isObjCQualifiedIdType()) {
8260  getObjCEncodingForTypeImpl(
8261  getObjCIdType(), S,
8262  Options.keepingOnly(ObjCEncOptions()
8263  .setExpandPointedToStructures()
8264  .setExpandStructures()),
8265  FD);
8266  if (FD || Options.EncodingProperty() || Options.EncodeClassNames()) {
8267  // Note that we do extended encoding of protocol qualifier list
8268  // Only when doing ivar or property encoding.
8269  S += '"';
8270  for (const auto *I : OPT->quals()) {
8271  S += '<';
8272  S += I->getObjCRuntimeNameAsString();
8273  S += '>';
8274  }
8275  S += '"';
8276  }
8277  return;
8278  }
8279 
8280  S += '@';
8281  if (OPT->getInterfaceDecl() &&
8282  (FD || Options.EncodingProperty() || Options.EncodeClassNames())) {
8283  S += '"';
8284  S += OPT->getInterfaceDecl()->getObjCRuntimeNameAsString();
8285  for (const auto *I : OPT->quals()) {
8286  S += '<';
8287  S += I->getObjCRuntimeNameAsString();
8288  S += '>';
8289  }
8290  S += '"';
8291  }
8292  return;
8293  }
8294 
8295  // gcc just blithely ignores member pointers.
8296  // FIXME: we should do better than that. 'M' is available.
8297  case Type::MemberPointer:
8298  // This matches gcc's encoding, even though technically it is insufficient.
8299  //FIXME. We should do a better job than gcc.
8300  case Type::Vector:
8301  case Type::ExtVector:
8302  // Until we have a coherent encoding of these three types, issue warning.
8303  if (NotEncodedT)
8304  *NotEncodedT = T;
8305  return;
8306 
8307  case Type::ConstantMatrix:
8308  if (NotEncodedT)
8309  *NotEncodedT = T;
8310  return;
8311 
8312  case Type::BitInt:
8313  if (NotEncodedT)
8314  *NotEncodedT = T;
8315  return;
8316 
8317  // We could see an undeduced auto type here during error recovery.
8318  // Just ignore it.
8319  case Type::Auto:
8320  case Type::DeducedTemplateSpecialization:
8321  return;
8322 
8323  case Type::Pipe:
8324 #define ABSTRACT_TYPE(KIND, BASE)
8325 #define TYPE(KIND, BASE)
8326 #define DEPENDENT_TYPE(KIND, BASE) \
8327  case Type::KIND:
8328 #define NON_CANONICAL_TYPE(KIND, BASE) \
8329  case Type::KIND:
8330 #define NON_CANONICAL_UNLESS_DEPENDENT_TYPE(KIND, BASE) \
8331  case Type::KIND:
8332 #include "clang/AST/TypeNodes.inc"
8333  llvm_unreachable("@encode for dependent type!");
8334  }
8335  llvm_unreachable("bad type kind!");
8336 }
8337 
8338 void ASTContext::getObjCEncodingForStructureImpl(RecordDecl *RDecl,
8339  std::string &S,
8340  const FieldDecl *FD,
8341  bool includeVBases,
8342  QualType *NotEncodedT) const {
8343  assert(RDecl && "Expected non-null RecordDecl");
8344  assert(!RDecl->isUnion() && "Should not be called for unions");
8345  if (!RDecl->getDefinition() || RDecl->getDefinition()->isInvalidDecl())
8346  return;
8347 
8348  const auto *CXXRec = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RDecl);
8349  std::multimap<uint64_t, NamedDecl *> FieldOrBaseOffsets;
8350  const ASTRecordLayout &layout = getASTRecordLayout(RDecl);
8351 
8352  if (CXXRec) {
8353  for (const auto &BI : CXXRec->bases()) {
8354  if (!BI.isVirtual()) {
8355  CXXRecordDecl *base = BI.getType()->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
8356  if (base->isEmpty())
8357  continue;
8358  uint64_t offs = toBits(layout.getBaseClassOffset(base));
8359  FieldOrBaseOffsets.insert(FieldOrBaseOffsets.upper_bound(offs),
8360  std::make_pair(offs, base));
8361  }
8362  }
8363  }
8364 
8365  unsigned i = 0;
8366  for (FieldDecl *Field : RDecl->fields()) {
8367  if (!Field->isZeroLengthBitField(*this) && Field->isZeroSize(*this))
8368  continue;
8369  uint64_t offs = layout.getFieldOffset(i);
8370  FieldOrBaseOffsets.insert(FieldOrBaseOffsets.upper_bound(offs),
8371  std::make_pair(offs, Field));
8372  ++i;
8373  }
8374 
8375  if (CXXRec && includeVBases) {
8376  for (const auto &BI : CXXRec->vbases()) {
8377  CXXRecordDecl *base = BI.getType()->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
8378  if (base->isEmpty())
8379  continue;
8380  uint64_t offs = toBits(layout.getVBaseClassOffset(base));
8381  if (offs >= uint64_t(toBits(layout.getNonVirtualSize())) &&
8382  FieldOrBaseOffsets.find(offs) == FieldOrBaseOffsets.end())
8383  FieldOrBaseOffsets.insert(FieldOrBaseOffsets.end(),
8384  std::make_pair(offs, base));
8385  }
8386  }
8387 
8388  CharUnits size;
8389  if (CXXRec) {
8390  size = includeVBases ? layout.getSize() : layout.getNonVirtualSize();
8391  } else {
8392  size = layout.getSize();
8393  }
8394 
8395 #ifndef NDEBUG
8396  uint64_t CurOffs = 0;
8397 #endif
8398  std::multimap<uint64_t, NamedDecl *>::iterator
8399  CurLayObj = FieldOrBaseOffsets.begin();
8400 
8401  if (CXXRec && CXXRec->isDynamicClass() &&
8402  (CurLayObj == FieldOrBaseOffsets.end() || CurLayObj->first != 0)) {
8403  if (FD) {
8404  S += "\"_vptr$";
8405  std::string recname = CXXRec->getNameAsString();
8406  if (recname.empty()) recname = "?";
8407  S += recname;
8408  S += '"';
8409  }
8410  S += "^^?";
8411 #ifndef NDEBUG
8412  CurOffs += getTypeSize(VoidPtrTy);
8413 #endif
8414  }
8415 
8416  if (!RDecl->hasFlexibleArrayMember()) {
8417  // Mark the end of the structure.
8418  uint64_t offs = toBits(size);
8419  FieldOrBaseOffsets.insert(FieldOrBaseOffsets.upper_bound(offs),
8420  std::make_pair(offs, nullptr));
8421  }
8422 
8423  for (; CurLayObj != FieldOrBaseOffsets.end(); ++CurLayObj) {
8424 #ifndef NDEBUG
8425  assert(CurOffs <= CurLayObj->first);
8426  if (CurOffs < CurLayObj->first) {
8427  uint64_t padding = CurLayObj->first - CurOffs;
8428  // FIXME: There doesn't seem to be a way to indicate in the encoding that
8429  // packing/alignment of members is different that normal, in which case
8430  // the encoding will be out-of-sync with the real layout.
8431  // If the runtime switches to just consider the size of types without
8432  // taking into account alignment, we could make padding explicit in the
8433  // encoding (e.g. using arrays of chars). The encoding strings would be
8434  // longer then though.
8435  CurOffs += padding;
8436  }
8437 #endif
8438 
8439  NamedDecl *dcl = CurLayObj->second;
8440  if (!dcl)
8441  break; // reached end of structure.
8442 
8443  if (auto *base = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(dcl)) {
8444  // We expand the bases without their virtual bases since those are going
8445  // in the initial structure. Note that this differs from gcc which
8446  // expands virtual bases each time one is encountered in the hierarchy,
8447  // making the encoding type bigger than it really is.
8448  getObjCEncodingForStructureImpl(base, S, FD, /*includeVBases*/false,
8449  NotEncodedT);
8450  assert(!base->isEmpty());
8451 #ifndef NDEBUG
8452  CurOffs += toBits(getASTRecordLayout(base).getNonVirtualSize());
8453 #endif
8454  } else {
8455  const auto *field = cast<FieldDecl>(dcl);
8456  if (FD) {
8457  S += '"';
8458  S += field->getNameAsString();
8459  S += '"';
8460  }
8461 
8462  if (field->isBitField()) {
8463  EncodeBitField(this, S, field->getType(), field);
8464 #ifndef NDEBUG
8465  CurOffs += field->getBitWidthValue(*this);
8466 #endif
8467  } else {
8468  QualType qt = field->getType();
8469  getLegacyIntegralTypeEncoding(qt);
8470  getObjCEncodingForTypeImpl(
8471  qt, S, ObjCEncOptions().setExpandStructures().setIsStructField(),
8472  FD, NotEncodedT);
8473 #ifndef NDEBUG
8474  CurOffs += getTypeSize(field->getType());
8475 #endif
8476  }
8477  }
8478  }
8479 }
8480 
8481 void ASTContext::getObjCEncodingForTypeQualifier(Decl::ObjCDeclQualifier QT,
8482  std::string& S) const {
8483  if (QT & Decl::OBJC_TQ_In)
8484  S += 'n';
8485  if (QT & Decl::OBJC_TQ_Inout)
8486  S += 'N';
8487  if (QT & Decl::OBJC_TQ_Out)
8488  S += 'o';
8489  if (QT & Decl::OBJC_TQ_Bycopy)
8490  S += 'O';
8491  if (QT & Decl::OBJC_TQ_Byref)
8492  S += 'R';
8493  if (QT & Decl::OBJC_TQ_Oneway)
8494  S += 'V';
8495 }

8562 static TypedefDecl *
8563 CreateAArch64ABIBuiltinVaListDecl(const ASTContext *Context) {
8564  // struct __va_list
8565  RecordDecl *VaListTagDecl = Context->buildImplicitRecord("__va_list");
8566  if (Context->getLangOpts().CPlusPlus) {
8567  // namespace std { struct __va_list {
8568  auto *NS = NamespaceDecl::Create(
8569  const_cast<ASTContext &>(*Context), Context->getTranslationUnitDecl(),
8570  /*Inline*/ false, SourceLocation(), SourceLocation(),
8571  &Context->Idents.get("std"),
8572  /*PrevDecl*/ nullptr);
8573  NS->setImplicit();
8574  VaListTagDecl->setDeclContext(NS);
8575  }
8576 
8577  VaListTagDecl->startDefinition();
8578 
8579  const size_t NumFields = 5;
8580  QualType FieldTypes[NumFields];
8581  const char *FieldNames[NumFields];
8582 
8583  // void *__stack;
8584  FieldTypes[0] = Context->getPointerType(Context->VoidTy);
8585  FieldNames[0] = "__stack";
8586 
8587  // void *__gr_top;
8588  FieldTypes[1] = Context->getPointerType(Context->VoidTy);
8589  FieldNames[1] = "__gr_top";
8590 
8591  // void *__vr_top;
8592  FieldTypes[2] = Context->getPointerType(Context->VoidTy);
8593  FieldNames[2] = "__vr_top";
8594 
8595  // int __gr_offs;
8596  FieldTypes[3] = Context->IntTy;
8597  FieldNames[3] = "__gr_offs";
8598 
8599  // int __vr_offs;
8600  FieldTypes[4] = Context->IntTy;
8601  FieldNames[4] = "__vr_offs";
8602 
8603  // Create fields
8604  for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumFields; ++i) {
8605  FieldDecl *Field = FieldDecl::Create(const_cast<ASTContext &>(*Context),
8606  VaListTagDecl,
8607  SourceLocation(),
8608  SourceLocation(),
8609  &Context->Idents.get(FieldNames[i]),
8610  FieldTypes[i], /*TInfo=*/nullptr,
8611  /*BitWidth=*/nullptr,
8612  /*Mutable=*/false,
8613  ICIS_NoInit);
8614  Field->setAccess(AS_public);
8615  VaListTagDecl->addDecl(Field);
8616  }
8617  VaListTagDecl->completeDefinition();
8618  Context->VaListTagDecl = VaListTagDecl;
8619  QualType VaListTagType = Context->getRecordType(VaListTagDecl);
8620 
8621  // } __builtin_va_list;
8622  return Context->buildImplicitTypedef(VaListTagType, "__builtin_va_list");
8623 }

8625 static TypedefDecl *CreatePowerABIBuiltinVaListDecl(const ASTContext *Context) {
8626  // typedef struct __va_list_tag {
8627  RecordDecl *VaListTagDecl;
8628 
8629  VaListTagDecl = Context->buildImplicitRecord("__va_list_tag");
8630  VaListTagDecl->startDefinition();
8631 
8632  const size_t NumFields = 5;
8633  QualType FieldTypes[NumFields];
8634  const char *FieldNames[NumFields];
8635 
8636  // unsigned char gpr;
8637  FieldTypes[0] = Context->UnsignedCharTy;
8638  FieldNames[0] = "gpr";
8639 
8640  // unsigned char fpr;
8641  FieldTypes[1] = Context->UnsignedCharTy;
8642  FieldNames[1] = "fpr";
8643 
8644  // unsigned short reserved;
8645  FieldTypes[2] = Context->UnsignedShortTy;
8646  FieldNames[2] = "reserved";
8647 
8648  // void* overflow_arg_area;
8649  FieldTypes[3] = Context->getPointerType(Context->VoidTy);
8650  FieldNames[3] = "overflow_arg_area";
8651 
8652  // void* reg_save_area;
8653  FieldTypes[4] = Context->getPointerType(Context->VoidTy);
8654  FieldNames[4] = "reg_save_area";
8655 
8656  // Create fields
8657  for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumFields; ++i) {
8658  FieldDecl *Field = FieldDecl::Create(*Context, VaListTagDecl,
8659  SourceLocation(),
8660  SourceLocation(),
8661  &Context->Idents.get(FieldNames[i]),
8662  FieldTypes[i], /*TInfo=*/nullptr,
8663  /*BitWidth=*/nullptr,
8664  /*Mutable=*/false,
8665  ICIS_NoInit);
8666  Field->setAccess(AS_public);
8667  VaListTagDecl->addDecl(Field);
8668  }
8669  VaListTagDecl->completeDefinition();
8670  Context->VaListTagDecl = VaListTagDecl;
8671  QualType VaListTagType = Context->getRecordType(VaListTagDecl);
8672 
8673  // } __va_list_tag;
8674  TypedefDecl *VaListTagTypedefDecl =
8675  Context->buildImplicitTypedef(VaListTagType, "__va_list_tag");
8676 
8677  QualType VaListTagTypedefType =
8678  Context->getTypedefType(VaListTagTypedefDecl);
8679 
8680  // typedef __va_list_tag __builtin_va_list[1];
8681  llvm::APInt Size(Context->getTypeSize(Context->getSizeType()), 1);
8682  QualType VaListTagArrayType
8683  = Context->getConstantArrayType(VaListTagTypedefType,
8684  Size, nullptr, ArrayType::Normal, 0);
8685  return Context->buildImplicitTypedef(VaListTagArrayType, "__builtin_va_list");
8686 }

8688 static TypedefDecl *
8689 CreateX86_64ABIBuiltinVaListDecl(const ASTContext *Context) {
8690  // struct __va_list_tag {
8691  RecordDecl *VaListTagDecl;
8692  VaListTagDecl = Context->buildImplicitRecord("__va_list_tag");
8693  VaListTagDecl->startDefinition();
8694 
8695  const size_t NumFields = 4;
8696  QualType FieldTypes[NumFields];
8697  const char *FieldNames[NumFields];
8698 
8699  // unsigned gp_offset;
8700  FieldTypes[0] = Context->UnsignedIntTy;
8701  FieldNames[0] = "gp_offset";
8702 
8703  // unsigned fp_offset;
8704  FieldTypes[1] = Context->UnsignedIntTy;
8705  FieldNames[1] = "fp_offset";
8706 
8707  // void* overflow_arg_area;
8708  FieldTypes[2] = Context->getPointerType(Context->VoidTy);
8709  FieldNames[2] = "overflow_arg_area";
8710 
8711  // void* reg_save_area;
8712  FieldTypes[3] = Context->getPointerType(Context->VoidTy);
8713  FieldNames[3] = "reg_save_area";
8714 
8715  // Create fields
8716  for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumFields; ++i) {
8717  FieldDecl *Field = FieldDecl::Create(const_cast<ASTContext &>(*Context),
8718  VaListTagDecl,
8719  SourceLocation(),
8720  SourceLocation(),
8721  &Context->Idents.get(FieldNames[i]),
8722  FieldTypes[i], /*TInfo=*/nullptr,
8723  /*BitWidth=*/nullptr,
8724  /*Mutable=*/false,
8725  ICIS_NoInit);
8726  Field->setAccess(AS_public);
8727  VaListTagDecl->addDecl(Field);
8728  }
8729  VaListTagDecl->completeDefinition();
8730  Context->VaListTagDecl = VaListTagDecl;
8731  QualType VaListTagType = Context->getRecordType(VaListTagDecl);
8732 
8733  // };
8734 
8735  // typedef struct __va_list_tag __builtin_va_list[1];
8736  llvm::APInt Size(Context->getTypeSize(Context->getSizeType()), 1);
8737  QualType VaListTagArrayType = Context->getConstantArrayType(
8738  VaListTagType, Size, nullptr, ArrayType::Normal, 0);
8739  return Context->buildImplicitTypedef(VaListTagArrayType, "__builtin_va_list");
8740 }

8897 static TypedefDecl *CreateVaListDecl(const ASTContext *Context,
8898  TargetInfo::BuiltinVaListKind Kind) {
8899  switch (Kind) {
8900  case TargetInfo::CharPtrBuiltinVaList:
8901  return CreateCharPtrBuiltinVaListDecl(Context);
8902  case TargetInfo::VoidPtrBuiltinVaList:
8903  return CreateVoidPtrBuiltinVaListDecl(Context);
8904  case TargetInfo::AArch64ABIBuiltinVaList:
8905  return CreateAArch64ABIBuiltinVaListDecl(Context);
8906  case TargetInfo::PowerABIBuiltinVaList:
8907  return CreatePowerABIBuiltinVaListDecl(Context);
8908  case TargetInfo::X86_64ABIBuiltinVaList:
8909  return CreateX86_64ABIBuiltinVaListDecl(Context);
8910  case TargetInfo::PNaClABIBuiltinVaList:
8911  return CreatePNaClABIBuiltinVaListDecl(Context);
8912  case TargetInfo::AAPCSABIBuiltinVaList:
8913  return CreateAAPCSABIBuiltinVaListDecl(Context);
8914  case TargetInfo::SystemZBuiltinVaList:
8915  return CreateSystemZBuiltinVaListDecl(Context);
8916  case TargetInfo::HexagonBuiltinVaList:
8917  return CreateHexagonBuiltinVaListDecl(Context);
8918  }
8919 
8920  llvm_unreachable("Unhandled __builtin_va_list type kind");
8921 }

8959 /// Retrieve the template name that corresponds to a non-empty
8960 /// lookup.
8961 TemplateName
8962 ASTContext::getOverloadedTemplateName(UnresolvedSetIterator Begin,
8963  UnresolvedSetIterator End) const {
8964  unsigned size = End - Begin;
8965  assert(size > 1 && "set is not overloaded!");
8966 
8967  void *memory = Allocate(sizeof(OverloadedTemplateStorage) +
8968  size * sizeof(FunctionTemplateDecl*));
8969  auto *OT = new (memory) OverloadedTemplateStorage(size);
8970 
8971  NamedDecl **Storage = OT->getStorage();
8972  for (UnresolvedSetIterator I = Begin; I != End; ++I) {
8973  NamedDecl *D = *I;
8974  assert(isa<FunctionTemplateDecl>(D) ||
8975  isa<UnresolvedUsingValueDecl>(D) ||
8976  (isa<UsingShadowDecl>(D) &&
8977  isa<FunctionTemplateDecl>(D->getUnderlyingDecl())));
8978  *Storage++ = D;
8979  }
8980 
8981  return TemplateName(OT);
8982 }
8983 
8984 /// Retrieve a template name representing an unqualified-id that has been
8985 /// assumed to name a template for ADL purposes.
8986 TemplateName ASTContext::getAssumedTemplateName(DeclarationName Name) const {
8987  auto *OT = new (*this) AssumedTemplateStorage(Name);
8988  return TemplateName(OT);
8989 }

8991 /// Retrieve the template name that represents a qualified
8992 /// template name such as \c std::vector.
8993 TemplateName
8994 ASTContext::getQualifiedTemplateName(NestedNameSpecifier *NNS,
8995  bool TemplateKeyword,
8996  TemplateDecl *Template) const {
8997  assert(NNS && "Missing nested-name-specifier in qualified template name");
8998 
8999  // FIXME: Canonicalization?
9000  llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
9001  QualifiedTemplateName::Profile(ID, NNS, TemplateKeyword, Template);
9002 
9003  void *InsertPos = nullptr;
9004  QualifiedTemplateName *QTN =
9005  QualifiedTemplateNames.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
9006  if (!QTN) {
9007  QTN = new (*this, alignof(QualifiedTemplateName))
9008  QualifiedTemplateName(NNS, TemplateKeyword, Template);
9009  QualifiedTemplateNames.InsertNode(QTN, InsertPos);
9010  }
9011 
9012  return TemplateName(QTN);
9013 }
9014 
9015 /// Retrieve the template name that represents a dependent
9016 /// template name such as \c MetaFun::template apply.
9017 TemplateName
9018 ASTContext::getDependentTemplateName(NestedNameSpecifier *NNS,
9019  const IdentifierInfo *Name) const {
9020  assert((!NNS || NNS->isDependent()) &&
9021  "Nested name specifier must be dependent");
9022 
9023  llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
9024  DependentTemplateName::Profile(ID, NNS, Name);
9025 
9026  void *InsertPos = nullptr;
9027  DependentTemplateName *QTN =
9028  DependentTemplateNames.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
9029 
9030  if (QTN)
9031  return TemplateName(QTN);
9032 
9033  NestedNameSpecifier *CanonNNS = getCanonicalNestedNameSpecifier(NNS);
9034  if (CanonNNS == NNS) {
9035  QTN = new (*this, alignof(DependentTemplateName))
9036  DependentTemplateName(NNS, Name);
9037  } else {
9038  TemplateName Canon = getDependentTemplateName(CanonNNS, Name);
9039  QTN = new (*this, alignof(DependentTemplateName))
9040  DependentTemplateName(NNS, Name, Canon);
9041  DependentTemplateName *CheckQTN =
9042  DependentTemplateNames.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
9043  assert(!CheckQTN && "Dependent type name canonicalization broken");
9044  (void)CheckQTN;
9045  }
9046 
9047  DependentTemplateNames.InsertNode(QTN, InsertPos);
9048  return TemplateName(QTN);
9049 }
9050 
9051 /// Retrieve the template name that represents a dependent
9052 /// template name such as \c MetaFun::template operator+.
9053 TemplateName
9054 ASTContext::getDependentTemplateName(NestedNameSpecifier *NNS,
9055  OverloadedOperatorKind Operator) const {
9056  assert((!NNS || NNS->isDependent()) &&
9057  "Nested name specifier must be dependent");
9058 
9059  llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
9060  DependentTemplateName::Profile(ID, NNS, Operator);
9061 
9062  void *InsertPos = nullptr;
9063  DependentTemplateName *QTN
9064  = DependentTemplateNames.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
9065 
9066  if (QTN)
9067  return TemplateName(QTN);
9068 
9069  NestedNameSpecifier *CanonNNS = getCanonicalNestedNameSpecifier(NNS);
9070  if (CanonNNS == NNS) {
9071  QTN = new (*this, alignof(DependentTemplateName))
9072  DependentTemplateName(NNS, Operator);
9073  } else {
9074  TemplateName Canon = getDependentTemplateName(CanonNNS, Operator);
9075  QTN = new (*this, alignof(DependentTemplateName))
9076  DependentTemplateName(NNS, Operator, Canon);
9077 
9078  DependentTemplateName *CheckQTN
9079  = DependentTemplateNames.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
9080  assert(!CheckQTN && "Dependent template name canonicalization broken");
9081  (void)CheckQTN;
9082  }
9083 
9084  DependentTemplateNames.InsertNode(QTN, InsertPos);
9085  return TemplateName(QTN);
9086 }

9106 TemplateName

9108  const TemplateArgument &ArgPack) const {

9110  llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
9111  SubstTemplateTemplateParmPackStorage::Profile(ID, Self, Param, ArgPack);
9112

9127 /// getFromTargetType - Given one of the integer types provided by
9128 /// TargetInfo, produce the corresponding type. The unsigned @p Type
9129 /// is actually a value of type @c TargetInfo::IntType.
9130 CanQualType ASTContext::getFromTargetType(unsigned Type) const {
9131  switch (Type) {
9132  case TargetInfo::NoInt: return {};
9133  case TargetInfo::SignedChar: return SignedCharTy;
9134  case TargetInfo::UnsignedChar: return UnsignedCharTy;
9135  case TargetInfo::SignedShort: return ShortTy;
9136  case TargetInfo::UnsignedShort: return UnsignedShortTy;
9137  case TargetInfo::SignedInt: return IntTy;
9138  case TargetInfo::UnsignedInt: return UnsignedIntTy;
9139  case TargetInfo::SignedLong: return LongTy;
9140  case TargetInfo::UnsignedLong: return UnsignedLongTy;
9141  case TargetInfo::SignedLongLong: return LongLongTy;
9142  case TargetInfo::UnsignedLongLong: return UnsignedLongLongTy;
9143  }
9144 
9145  llvm_unreachable("Unhandled TargetInfo::IntType value");
9146 }

9148 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
9149 // Type Predicates.
9150 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
9151 
9152 /// getObjCGCAttr - Returns one of GCNone, Weak or Strong objc's
9153 /// garbage collection attribute.
9154 ///
9155 Qualifiers::GC ASTContext::getObjCGCAttrKind(QualType Ty) const {
9156  if (getLangOpts().getGC() == LangOptions::NonGC)
9157  return Qualifiers::GCNone;
9158 
9159  assert(getLangOpts().ObjC);
9160  Qualifiers::GC GCAttrs = Ty.getObjCGCAttr();
9161 
9162  // Default behaviour under objective-C's gc is for ObjC pointers
9163  // (or pointers to them) be treated as though they were declared
9164  // as __strong.
9165  if (GCAttrs == Qualifiers::GCNone) {
9166  if (Ty->isObjCObjectPointerType() || Ty->isBlockPointerType())
9167  return Qualifiers::Strong;
9168  else if (Ty->isPointerType())
9169  return getObjCGCAttrKind(Ty->castAs<PointerType>()->getPointeeType());
9170  } else {
9171  // It's not valid to set GC attributes on anything that isn't a
9172  // pointer.
9173 #ifndef NDEBUG
9174  QualType CT = Ty->getCanonicalTypeInternal();
9175  while (const auto *AT = dyn_cast<ArrayType>(CT))
9176  CT = AT->getElementType();
9177  assert(CT->isAnyPointerType() || CT->isBlockPointerType());
9178 #endif
9179  }
9180  return GCAttrs;
9181 }
