10850 
10851 /// DecodeTypeFromStr - This decodes one type descriptor from Str, advancing the
10852 /// pointer over the consumed characters. This returns the resultant type. If
10853 /// AllowTypeModifiers is false then modifier like * are not parsed, just basic
10854 /// types. This allows "v2i*" to be parsed as a pointer to a v2i instead of
10855 /// a vector of "i*".
10856 ///
10857 /// RequiresICE is filled in on return to indicate whether the value is required
10858 /// to be an Integer Constant Expression.
10859 static QualType DecodeTypeFromStr(const char *&Str, const ASTContext &Context,
10860  ASTContext::GetBuiltinTypeError &Error,
10861  bool &RequiresICE,
10862  bool AllowTypeModifiers) {
10863  // Modifiers.
10864  int HowLong = 0;
10865  bool Signed = false, Unsigned = false;
10866  RequiresICE = false;
10867 
10868  // Read the prefixed modifiers first.
10869  bool Done = false;
10870  #ifndef NDEBUG
10871  bool IsSpecial = false;
10872  #endif
10873  while (!Done) {
10874  switch (*Str++) {
10875  default: Done = true; --Str; break;
10876  case 'I':
10877  RequiresICE = true;
10878  break;
10879  case 'S':
10880  assert(!Unsigned && "Can't use both 'S' and 'U' modifiers!");
10881  assert(!Signed && "Can't use 'S' modifier multiple times!");
10882  Signed = true;
10883  break;
10884  case 'U':
10885  assert(!Signed && "Can't use both 'S' and 'U' modifiers!");
10886  assert(!Unsigned && "Can't use 'U' modifier multiple times!");
10887  Unsigned = true;
10888  break;
10889  case 'L':
10890  assert(!IsSpecial && "Can't use 'L' with 'W', 'N', 'Z' or 'O' modifiers");
10891  assert(HowLong <= 2 && "Can't have LLLL modifier");
10892  ++HowLong;
10893  break;
10894  case 'N':
10895  // 'N' behaves like 'L' for all non LP64 targets and 'int' otherwise.
10896  assert(!IsSpecial && "Can't use two 'N', 'W', 'Z' or 'O' modifiers!");
10897  assert(HowLong == 0 && "Can't use both 'L' and 'N' modifiers!");
10898  #ifndef NDEBUG
10899  IsSpecial = true;
10900  #endif
10901  if (Context.getTargetInfo().getLongWidth() == 32)
10902  ++HowLong;
10903  break;
10904  case 'W':
10905  // This modifier represents int64 type.
10906  assert(!IsSpecial && "Can't use two 'N', 'W', 'Z' or 'O' modifiers!");
10907  assert(HowLong == 0 && "Can't use both 'L' and 'W' modifiers!");
10908  #ifndef NDEBUG
10909  IsSpecial = true;
10910  #endif
10911  switch (Context.getTargetInfo().getInt64Type()) {
10912  default:
10913  llvm_unreachable("Unexpected integer type");
10914  case TargetInfo::SignedLong:
10915  HowLong = 1;
10916  break;
10917  case TargetInfo::SignedLongLong:
10918  HowLong = 2;
10919  break;
10920  }
10921  break;
10922  case 'Z':
10923  // This modifier represents int32 type.
10924  assert(!IsSpecial && "Can't use two 'N', 'W', 'Z' or 'O' modifiers!");
10925  assert(HowLong == 0 && "Can't use both 'L' and 'Z' modifiers!");
10926  #ifndef NDEBUG
10927  IsSpecial = true;
10928  #endif
10929  switch (Context.getTargetInfo().getIntTypeByWidth(32, true)) {
10930  default:
10931  llvm_unreachable("Unexpected integer type");
10932  case TargetInfo::SignedInt:
10933  HowLong = 0;
10934  break;
10935  case TargetInfo::SignedLong:
10936  HowLong = 1;
10937  break;
10938  case TargetInfo::SignedLongLong:
10939  HowLong = 2;
10940  break;
10941  }
10942  break;
10943  case 'O':
10944  assert(!IsSpecial && "Can't use two 'N', 'W', 'Z' or 'O' modifiers!");
10945  assert(HowLong == 0 && "Can't use both 'L' and 'O' modifiers!");
10946  #ifndef NDEBUG
10947  IsSpecial = true;
10948  #endif
10949  if (Context.getLangOpts().OpenCL)
10950  HowLong = 1;
10951  else
10952  HowLong = 2;
10953  break;
10954  }
10955  }
10956 
10957  QualType Type;
10958 
10959  // Read the base type.
10960  switch (*Str++) {
10961  default: llvm_unreachable("Unknown builtin type letter!");
10962  case 'x':
10963  assert(HowLong == 0 && !Signed && !Unsigned &&
10964  "Bad modifiers used with 'x'!");
10965  Type = Context.Float16Ty;
10966  break;
10967  case 'y':
10968  assert(HowLong == 0 && !Signed && !Unsigned &&
10969  "Bad modifiers used with 'y'!");
10970  Type = Context.BFloat16Ty;
10971  break;
10972  case 'v':
10973  assert(HowLong == 0 && !Signed && !Unsigned &&
10974  "Bad modifiers used with 'v'!");
10975  Type = Context.VoidTy;
10976  break;
10977  case 'h':
10978  assert(HowLong == 0 && !Signed && !Unsigned &&
10979  "Bad modifiers used with 'h'!");
10980  Type = Context.HalfTy;
10981  break;
10982  case 'f':
10983  assert(HowLong == 0 && !Signed && !Unsigned &&
10984  "Bad modifiers used with 'f'!");
10985  Type = Context.FloatTy;
10986  break;
10987  case 'd':
10988  assert(HowLong < 3 && !Signed && !Unsigned &&
10989  "Bad modifiers used with 'd'!");
10990  if (HowLong == 1)
10991  Type = Context.LongDoubleTy;
10992  else if (HowLong == 2)
10993  Type = Context.Float128Ty;
10994  else
10995  Type = Context.DoubleTy;
10996  break;
10997  case 's':
10998  assert(HowLong == 0 && "Bad modifiers used with 's'!");
10999  if (Unsigned)
11000  Type = Context.UnsignedShortTy;
11001  else
11002  Type = Context.ShortTy;
11003  break;
11004  case 'i':
11005  if (HowLong == 3)
11006  Type = Unsigned ? Context.UnsignedInt128Ty : Context.Int128Ty;
11007  else if (HowLong == 2)
11008  Type = Unsigned ? Context.UnsignedLongLongTy : Context.LongLongTy;
11009  else if (HowLong == 1)
11010  Type = Unsigned ? Context.UnsignedLongTy : Context.LongTy;
11011  else
11012  Type = Unsigned ? Context.UnsignedIntTy : Context.IntTy;
11013  break;
11014  case 'c':
11015  assert(HowLong == 0 && "Bad modifiers used with 'c'!");
11016  if (Signed)
11017  Type = Context.SignedCharTy;
11018  else if (Unsigned)
11019  Type = Context.UnsignedCharTy;
11020  else
11021  Type = Context.CharTy;
11022  break;
11023  case 'b': // boolean
11024  assert(HowLong == 0 && !Signed && !Unsigned && "Bad modifiers for 'b'!");
11025  Type = Context.BoolTy;
11026  break;
11027  case 'z': // size_t.
11028  assert(HowLong == 0 && !Signed && !Unsigned && "Bad modifiers for 'z'!");
11029  Type = Context.getSizeType();
11030  break;
11031  case 'w': // wchar_t.
11032  assert(HowLong == 0 && !Signed && !Unsigned && "Bad modifiers for 'w'!");
11033  Type = Context.getWideCharType();
11034  break;
11035  case 'F':
11036  Type = Context.getCFConstantStringType();
11037  break;
11038  case 'G':
11039  Type = Context.getObjCIdType();
11040  break;
11041  case 'H':
11042  Type = Context.getObjCSelType();
11043  break;
11044  case 'M':
11045  Type = Context.getObjCSuperType();
11046  break;
11047  case 'a':
11048  Type = Context.getBuiltinVaListType();
11049  assert(!Type.isNull() && "builtin va list type not initialized!");
11050  break;
11051  case 'A':
11052  // This is a "reference" to a va_list; however, what exactly
11053  // this means depends on how va_list is defined. There are two
11054  // different kinds of va_list: ones passed by value, and ones
11055  // passed by reference. An example of a by-value va_list is
11056  // x86, where va_list is a char*. An example of by-ref va_list
11057  // is x86-64, where va_list is a __va_list_tag[1]. For x86,
11058  // we want this argument to be a char*&; for x86-64, we want
11059  // it to be a __va_list_tag*.
11060  Type = Context.getBuiltinVaListType();
11061  assert(!Type.isNull() && "builtin va list type not initialized!");
11062  if (Type->isArrayType())
11063  Type = Context.getArrayDecayedType(Type);
11064  else
11065  Type = Context.getLValueReferenceType(Type);
11066  break;
11067  case 'q': {
11068  char *End;
11069  unsigned NumElements = strtoul(Str, &End, 10);
11070  assert(End != Str && "Missing vector size");
11071  Str = End;
11072 
11073  QualType ElementType = DecodeTypeFromStr(Str, Context, Error,
11074  RequiresICE, false);
11075  assert(!RequiresICE && "Can't require vector ICE");
11076 
11077  Type = Context.getScalableVectorType(ElementType, NumElements);
11078  break;
11079  }
11080  case 'V': {
11081  char *End;
11082  unsigned NumElements = strtoul(Str, &End, 10);
11083  assert(End != Str && "Missing vector size");
11084  Str = End;
11085 
11086  QualType ElementType = DecodeTypeFromStr(Str, Context, Error,
11087  RequiresICE, false);
11088  assert(!RequiresICE && "Can't require vector ICE");
11089 
11090  // TODO: No way to make AltiVec vectors in builtins yet.
11091  Type = Context.getVectorType(ElementType, NumElements,
11092  VectorType::GenericVector);
11093  break;
11094  }
11095  case 'E': {
11096  char *End;
11097 
11098  unsigned NumElements = strtoul(Str, &End, 10);
11099  assert(End != Str && "Missing vector size");
11100 
11101  Str = End;
11102 
11103  QualType ElementType = DecodeTypeFromStr(Str, Context, Error, RequiresICE,
11104  false);
11105  Type = Context.getExtVectorType(ElementType, NumElements);
11106  break;
11107  }
11108  case 'X': {
11109  QualType ElementType = DecodeTypeFromStr(Str, Context, Error, RequiresICE,
11110  false);
11111  assert(!RequiresICE && "Can't require complex ICE");
11112  Type = Context.getComplexType(ElementType);
11113  break;
11114  }
11115  case 'Y':
11116  Type = Context.getPointerDiffType();
11117  break;
11118  case 'P':
11119  Type = Context.getFILEType();
11120  if (Type.isNull()) {
11121  Error = ASTContext::GE_Missing_stdio;
11122  return {};
11123  }
11124  break;
11125  case 'J':
11126  if (Signed)
11127  Type = Context.getsigjmp_bufType();
11128  else
11129  Type = Context.getjmp_bufType();
11130 
11131  if (Type.isNull()) {
11132  Error = ASTContext::GE_Missing_setjmp;
11133  return {};
11134  }
11135  break;
11136  case 'K':
11137  assert(HowLong == 0 && !Signed && !Unsigned && "Bad modifiers for 'K'!");
11138  Type = Context.getucontext_tType();
11139 
11140  if (Type.isNull()) {
11141  Error = ASTContext::GE_Missing_ucontext;
11142  return {};
11143  }
11144  break;
11145  case 'p':
11146  Type = Context.getProcessIDType();
11147  break;
11148  }
11149 
11150  // If there are modifiers and if we're allowed to parse them, go for it.
11151  Done = !AllowTypeModifiers;
11152  while (!Done) {
11153  switch (char c = *Str++) {
11154  default: Done = true; --Str; break;
11155  case '*':
11156  case '&': {
11157  // Both pointers and references can have their pointee types
11158  // qualified with an address space.
11159  char *End;
11160  unsigned AddrSpace = strtoul(Str, &End, 10);
11161  if (End != Str) {
11162  // Note AddrSpace == 0 is not the same as an unspecified address space.
11163  Type = Context.getAddrSpaceQualType(
11164  Type,
11165  Context.getLangASForBuiltinAddressSpace(AddrSpace));
11166  Str = End;
11167  }
11168  if (c == '*')
11169  Type = Context.getPointerType(Type);
11170  else
11171  Type = Context.getLValueReferenceType(Type);
11172  break;
11173  }
11174  // FIXME: There's no way to have a built-in with an rvalue ref arg.
11175  case 'C':
11176  Type = Type.withConst();
11177  break;
11178  case 'D':
11179  Type = Context.getVolatileType(Type);
11180  break;
11181  case 'R':
11182  Type = Type.withRestrict();
11183  break;
11184  }
11185  }
11186 
11187  assert((!RequiresICE || Type->isIntegralOrEnumerationType()) &&
11188  "Integer constant 'I' type must be an integer");
11189 
11190  return Type;
11191 }
11192 
11193 // On some targets such as PowerPC, some of the builtins are defined with custom
11194 // type descriptors for target-dependent types. These descriptors are decoded in
11195 // other functions, but it may be useful to be able to fall back to default
11196 // descriptor decoding to define builtins mixing target-dependent and target-
11197 // independent types. This function allows decoding one type descriptor with
11198 // default decoding.
11199 QualType ASTContext::DecodeTypeStr(const char *&Str, const ASTContext &Context,
11200  GetBuiltinTypeError &Error, bool &RequireICE,
11201  bool AllowTypeModifiers) const {
11202  return DecodeTypeFromStr(Str, Context, Error, RequireICE, AllowTypeModifiers);
11203 }
11204 
11205 /// GetBuiltinType - Return the type for the specified builtin.
11206 QualType ASTContext::GetBuiltinType(unsigned Id,
11207  GetBuiltinTypeError &Error,
11208  unsigned *IntegerConstantArgs) const {
11209  const char *TypeStr = BuiltinInfo.getTypeString(Id);
11210  if (TypeStr[0] == '\0') {
11211  Error = GE_Missing_type;
11212  return {};
11213  }
11214 
11215  SmallVector<QualType, 8> ArgTypes;
11216 
11217  bool RequiresICE = false;
11218  Error = GE_None;
11219  QualType ResType = DecodeTypeFromStr(TypeStr, *this, Error,
11220  RequiresICE, true);
11221  if (Error != GE_None)
11222  return {};
11223 
11224  assert(!RequiresICE && "Result of intrinsic cannot be required to be an ICE");
11225 
11226  while (TypeStr[0] && TypeStr[0] != '.') {
11227  QualType Ty = DecodeTypeFromStr(TypeStr, *this, Error, RequiresICE, true);
11228  if (Error != GE_None)
11229  return {};
11230 
11231  // If this argument is required to be an IntegerConstantExpression and the
11232  // caller cares, fill in the bitmask we return.
11233  if (RequiresICE && IntegerConstantArgs)
11234  *IntegerConstantArgs |= 1 << ArgTypes.size();
11235 
11236  // Do array -> pointer decay. The builtin should use the decayed type.
11237  if (Ty->isArrayType())
11238  Ty = getArrayDecayedType(Ty);
11239 
11240  ArgTypes.push_back(Ty);
11241  }
11242 
11243  if (Id == Builtin::BI__GetExceptionInfo)
11244  return {};
11245 
11246  assert((TypeStr[0] != '.' || TypeStr[1] == 0) &&
11247  "'.' should only occur at end of builtin type list!");
11248 
11249  bool Variadic = (TypeStr[0] == '.');
11250 
11251  FunctionType::ExtInfo EI(getDefaultCallingConvention(
11252  Variadic, /*IsCXXMethod=*/false, /*IsBuiltin=*/true));
11253  if (BuiltinInfo.isNoReturn(Id)) EI = EI.withNoReturn(true);
11254 
11255 
11256  // We really shouldn't be making a no-proto type here.
11257  if (ArgTypes.empty() && Variadic && !getLangOpts().CPlusPlus)
11258  return getFunctionNoProtoType(ResType, EI);
11259 
11260  FunctionProtoType::ExtProtoInfo EPI;
11261  EPI.ExtInfo = EI;
11262  EPI.Variadic = Variadic;
11263  if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus && BuiltinInfo.isNoThrow(Id))
11264  EPI.ExceptionSpec.Type =
11265  getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11 ? EST_BasicNoexcept : EST_DynamicNone;
11266 
11267  return getFunctionType(ResType, ArgTypes, EPI);
11268 }
11269 
11270 static GVALinkage basicGVALinkageForFunction(const ASTContext &Context,
11271  const FunctionDecl *FD) {
11272  if (!FD->isExternallyVisible())
11273  return GVA_Internal;
11274 
11275  // Non-user-provided functions get emitted as weak definitions with every
11276  // use, no matter whether they've been explicitly instantiated etc.
11277  if (const auto *MD = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(FD))
11278  if (!MD->isUserProvided())
11279  return GVA_DiscardableODR;
11280 
11281  GVALinkage External;
11282  switch (FD->getTemplateSpecializationKind()) {
11283  case TSK_Undeclared:
11284  case TSK_ExplicitSpecialization:
11285  External = GVA_StrongExternal;
11286  break;
11287 
11288  case TSK_ExplicitInstantiationDefinition:
11289  return GVA_StrongODR;
11290 
11291  // C++11 [temp.explicit]p10:
11292  // [ Note: The intent is that an inline function that is the subject of
11293  // an explicit instantiation declaration will still be implicitly
11294  // instantiated when used so that the body can be considered for
11295  // inlining, but that no out-of-line copy of the inline function would be
11296  // generated in the translation unit. -- end note ]
11297  case TSK_ExplicitInstantiationDeclaration:
11298  return GVA_AvailableExternally;
11299 
11300  case TSK_ImplicitInstantiation:
11301  External = GVA_DiscardableODR;
11302  break;
11303  }
11304 
11305  if (!FD->isInlined())
11306  return External;
11307 
11308  if ((!Context.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus &&
11309  !Context.getTargetInfo().getCXXABI().isMicrosoft() &&
11310  !FD->hasAttr<DLLExportAttr>()) ||
11311  FD->hasAttr<GNUInlineAttr>()) {
11312  // FIXME: This doesn't match gcc's behavior for dllexport inline functions.
11313 
11314  // GNU or C99 inline semantics. Determine whether this symbol should be
11315  // externally visible.
11316  if (FD->isInlineDefinitionExternallyVisible())
11317  return External;
11318 
11319  // C99 inline semantics, where the symbol is not externally visible.
11320  return GVA_AvailableExternally;
11321  }
11322 
11323  // Functions specified with extern and inline in -fms-compatibility mode
11324  // forcibly get emitted. While the body of the function cannot be later
11325  // replaced, the function definition cannot be discarded.
11326  if (FD->isMSExternInline())
11327  return GVA_StrongODR;
11328 
11329  return GVA_DiscardableODR;
11330 }
11331 
11332 static GVALinkage adjustGVALinkageForAttributes(const ASTContext &Context,
11333  const Decl *D, GVALinkage L) {
11334  // See http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/xa0d9ste.aspx
11335  // dllexport/dllimport on inline functions.
11336  if (D->hasAttr<DLLImportAttr>()) {
11337  if (L == GVA_DiscardableODR || L == GVA_StrongODR)
11338  return GVA_AvailableExternally;
11339  } else if (D->hasAttr<DLLExportAttr>()) {
11340  if (L == GVA_DiscardableODR)
11341  return GVA_StrongODR;
11342  } else if (Context.getLangOpts().CUDA && Context.getLangOpts().CUDAIsDevice) {
11343  // Device-side functions with __global__ attribute must always be
11344  // visible externally so they can be launched from host.
11345  if (D->hasAttr<CUDAGlobalAttr>() &&
11346  (L == GVA_DiscardableODR || L == GVA_Internal))
11347  return GVA_StrongODR;
11348  // Single source offloading languages like CUDA/HIP need to be able to
11349  // access static device variables from host code of the same compilation
11350  // unit. This is done by externalizing the static variable with a shared
11351  // name between the host and device compilation which is the same for the
11352  // same compilation unit whereas different among different compilation
11353  // units.
11354  if (Context.shouldExternalizeStaticVar(D))
11355  return GVA_StrongExternal;
11356  } else if (Context.getLangOpts().SYCLIsDevice &&
11357  D->hasAttr<OpenCLKernelAttr>()) {
11358  if (L == GVA_DiscardableODR)
11359  return GVA_StrongODR;
11360  }
11361  return L;
11362 }
11363 
11364 /// Adjust the GVALinkage for a declaration based on what an external AST source
11365 /// knows about whether there can be other definitions of this declaration.
11366 static GVALinkage
11367 adjustGVALinkageForExternalDefinitionKind(const ASTContext &Ctx, const Decl *D,
11368  GVALinkage L) {
11369  ExternalASTSource *Source = Ctx.getExternalSource();
11370  if (!Source)
11371  return L;
11372 
11373  switch (Source->hasExternalDefinitions(D)) {
11374  case ExternalASTSource::EK_Never:
11375  // Other translation units rely on us to provide the definition.
11376  if (L == GVA_DiscardableODR)
11377  return GVA_StrongODR;
11378  break;
11379 
11380  case ExternalASTSource::EK_Always:
11381  return GVA_AvailableExternally;
11382 
11383  case ExternalASTSource::EK_ReplyHazy:
11384  break;
11385  }
11386  return L;
11387 }
11388 
11389 GVALinkage ASTContext::GetGVALinkageForFunction(const FunctionDecl *FD) const {
11390  return adjustGVALinkageForExternalDefinitionKind(*this, FD,
11391  adjustGVALinkageForAttributes(*this, FD,
11392  basicGVALinkageForFunction(*this, FD)));
11393 }
11394 
11395 static GVALinkage basicGVALinkageForVariable(const ASTContext &Context,
11396  const VarDecl *VD) {
11397  if (!VD->isExternallyVisible())
11398  return GVA_Internal;
11399 
11400  if (VD->isStaticLocal()) {
11401  const DeclContext *LexicalContext = VD->getParentFunctionOrMethod();
11402  while (LexicalContext && !isa<FunctionDecl>(LexicalContext))
11403  LexicalContext = LexicalContext->getLexicalParent();
11404 
11405  // ObjC Blocks can create local variables that don't have a FunctionDecl
11406  // LexicalContext.
11407  if (!LexicalContext)
11408  return GVA_DiscardableODR;
11409 
11410  // Otherwise, let the static local variable inherit its linkage from the
11411  // nearest enclosing function.
11412  auto StaticLocalLinkage =
11413  Context.GetGVALinkageForFunction(cast<FunctionDecl>(LexicalContext));
11414 
11415  // Itanium ABI 5.2.2: "Each COMDAT group [for a static local variable] must
11416  // be emitted in any object with references to the symbol for the object it
11417  // contains, whether inline or out-of-line."
11418  // Similar behavior is observed with MSVC. An alternative ABI could use
11419  // StrongODR/AvailableExternally to match the function, but none are
11420  // known/supported currently.
11421  if (StaticLocalLinkage == GVA_StrongODR ||
11422  StaticLocalLinkage == GVA_AvailableExternally)
11423  return GVA_DiscardableODR;
11424  return StaticLocalLinkage;
11425  }
11426 
11427  // MSVC treats in-class initialized static data members as definitions.
11428  // By giving them non-strong linkage, out-of-line definitions won't
11429  // cause link errors.
11430  if (Context.isMSStaticDataMemberInlineDefinition(VD))
11431  return GVA_DiscardableODR;
11432 
11433  // Most non-template variables have strong linkage; inline variables are
11434  // linkonce_odr or (occasionally, for compatibility) weak_odr.
11435  GVALinkage StrongLinkage;
11436  switch (Context.getInlineVariableDefinitionKind(VD)) {
11437  case ASTContext::InlineVariableDefinitionKind::None:
11438  StrongLinkage = GVA_StrongExternal;
11439  break;
11440  case ASTContext::InlineVariableDefinitionKind::Weak:
11441  case ASTContext::InlineVariableDefinitionKind::WeakUnknown:
11442  StrongLinkage = GVA_DiscardableODR;
11443  break;
11444  case ASTContext::InlineVariableDefinitionKind::Strong:
11445  StrongLinkage = GVA_StrongODR;
11446  break;
11447  }
11448 
11449  switch (VD->getTemplateSpecializationKind()) {
11450  case TSK_Undeclared:
11451  return StrongLinkage;
11452 
11453  case TSK_ExplicitSpecialization:
11454  return Context.getTargetInfo().getCXXABI().isMicrosoft() &&
11455  VD->isStaticDataMember()
11456  ? GVA_StrongODR
11457  : StrongLinkage;
11458 
11459  case TSK_ExplicitInstantiationDefinition:
11460  return GVA_StrongODR;
11461 
11462  case TSK_ExplicitInstantiationDeclaration:
11463  return GVA_AvailableExternally;
11464 
11465  case TSK_ImplicitInstantiation:
11466  return GVA_DiscardableODR;
11467  }
11468 
11469  llvm_unreachable("Invalid Linkage!");
11470 }
11471 
11472 GVALinkage ASTContext::GetGVALinkageForVariable(const VarDecl *VD) {
11473  return adjustGVALinkageForExternalDefinitionKind(*this, VD,
11474  adjustGVALinkageForAttributes(*this, VD,
11475  basicGVALinkageForVariable(*this, VD)));
11476 }
11477 
11478 bool ASTContext::DeclMustBeEmitted(const Decl *D) {
11479  if (const auto *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(D)) {
11480  if (!VD->isFileVarDecl())
11481  return false;
11482  // Global named register variables (GNU extension) are never emitted.
11483  if (VD->getStorageClass() == SC_Register)
11484  return false;
11485  if (VD->getDescribedVarTemplate() ||
11486  isa<VarTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl>(VD))
11487  return false;
11488  } else if (const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D)) {
11489  // We never need to emit an uninstantiated function template.
11490  if (FD->getTemplatedKind() == FunctionDecl::TK_FunctionTemplate)
11491  return false;
11492  } else if (isa<PragmaCommentDecl>(D))
11493  return true;
11494  else if (isa<PragmaDetectMismatchDecl>(D))
11495  return true;
11496  else if (isa<OMPRequiresDecl>(D))
11497  return true;
11498  else if (isa<OMPThreadPrivateDecl>(D))
11499  return !D->getDeclContext()->isDependentContext();
11500  else if (isa<OMPAllocateDecl>(D))
11501  return !D->getDeclContext()->isDependentContext();
11502  else if (isa<OMPDeclareReductionDecl>(D) || isa<OMPDeclareMapperDecl>(D))
11503  return !D->getDeclContext()->isDependentContext();
11504  else if (isa<ImportDecl>(D))
11505  return true;
11506  else
11507  return false;
11508 
11509  // If this is a member of a class template, we do not need to emit it.
11510  if (D->getDeclContext()->isDependentContext())
11511  return false;
11512 
11513  // Weak references don't produce any output by themselves.
11514  if (D->hasAttr<WeakRefAttr>())
11515  return false;
11516 
11517  if (LangOpts.SYCLIsDevice && !D->hasAttr<OpenCLKernelAttr>() &&
11518  !D->hasAttr<SYCLDeviceAttr>())
11519  return false;
11520 
11521  // Aliases and used decls are required.
11522  if (D->hasAttr<AliasAttr>() || D->hasAttr<UsedAttr>())
11523  return true;
11524 
11525  if (const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D)) {
11526  // Forward declarations aren't required.
11527  if (!FD->doesThisDeclarationHaveABody())
11528  return FD->doesDeclarationForceExternallyVisibleDefinition();
11529 
11530  // Constructors and destructors are required.
11531  if (FD->hasAttr<ConstructorAttr>() || FD->hasAttr<DestructorAttr>())
11532  return true;
11533 
11534  // The key function for a class is required. This rule only comes
11535  // into play when inline functions can be key functions, though.
11536  if (getTargetInfo().getCXXABI().canKeyFunctionBeInline()) {
11537  if (const auto *MD = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(FD)) {
11538  const CXXRecordDecl *RD = MD->getParent();
11539  if (MD->isOutOfLine() && RD->isDynamicClass()) {
11540  const CXXMethodDecl *KeyFunc = getCurrentKeyFunction(RD);
11541  if (KeyFunc && KeyFunc->getCanonicalDecl() == MD->getCanonicalDecl())
11542  return true;
11543  }
11544  }
11545  }
11546 
11547  // Methods explcitly marked with 'sycl_device' attribute (via SYCL_EXTERNAL)
11548  // or `indirectly_callable' attribute must be emitted regardless of number
11549  // of actual uses
11550  if (LangOpts.SYCLIsDevice && isa<CXXMethodDecl>(D)) {
11551  if (auto *A = D->getAttr<SYCLDeviceIndirectlyCallableAttr>())
11552  return !A->isImplicit();
11553  if (auto *A = D->getAttr<SYCLDeviceAttr>())
11554  return !A->isImplicit();
11555  }
11556 
11557  GVALinkage Linkage = GetGVALinkageForFunction(FD);
11558 
11559  // static, static inline, always_inline, and extern inline functions can
11560  // always be deferred. Normal inline functions can be deferred in C99/C++.
11561  // Implicit template instantiations can also be deferred in C++.
11562  return !isDiscardableGVALinkage(Linkage);
11563  }
11564 
11565  const auto *VD = cast<VarDecl>(D);
11566  assert(VD->isFileVarDecl() && "Expected file scoped var");
11567 
11568  // If the decl is marked as `declare target to`, it should be emitted for the
11569  // host and for the device.
11570  if (LangOpts.OpenMP &&
11571  OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr::isDeclareTargetDeclaration(VD))
11572  return true;
11573 
11574  if (VD->isThisDeclarationADefinition() == VarDecl::DeclarationOnly &&
11575  !isMSStaticDataMemberInlineDefinition(VD))
11576  return false;
11577 
11578  // Variables that can be needed in other TUs are required.
11579  auto Linkage = GetGVALinkageForVariable(VD);
11580  if (!isDiscardableGVALinkage(Linkage))
11581  return true;
11582 
11583  // We never need to emit a variable that is available in another TU.
11584  if (Linkage == GVA_AvailableExternally)
11585  return false;
11586 
11587  // Variables that have destruction with side-effects are required.
11588  if (VD->needsDestruction(*this))
11589  return true;
11590 
11591  // Variables that have initialization with side-effects are required.
11592  if (VD->getInit() && VD->getInit()->HasSideEffects(*this) &&
11593  // We can get a value-dependent initializer during error recovery.
11594  (VD->getInit()->isValueDependent() || !VD->evaluateValue()))
11595  return true;
11596 
11597  // Likewise, variables with tuple-like bindings are required if their
11598  // bindings have side-effects.
11599  if (const auto *DD = dyn_cast<DecompositionDecl>(VD))
11600  for (const auto *BD : DD->bindings())
11601  if (const auto *BindingVD = BD->getHoldingVar())
11602  if (DeclMustBeEmitted(BindingVD))
11603  return true;
11604 
11605  return false;
11606 }
11607 
11608 void ASTContext::forEachMultiversionedFunctionVersion(
11609  const FunctionDecl *FD,
11610  llvm::function_ref<void(FunctionDecl *)> Pred) const {
11611  assert(FD->isMultiVersion() && "Only valid for multiversioned functions");
11612  llvm::SmallDenseSet<const FunctionDecl*, 4> SeenDecls;
11613  FD = FD->getMostRecentDecl();
11614  // FIXME: The order of traversal here matters and depends on the order of
11615  // lookup results, which happens to be (mostly) oldest-to-newest, but we
11616  // shouldn't rely on that.
11617  for (auto *CurDecl :
11618  FD->getDeclContext()->getRedeclContext()->lookup(FD->getDeclName())) {
11619  FunctionDecl *CurFD = CurDecl->getAsFunction()->getMostRecentDecl();
11620  if (CurFD && hasSameType(CurFD->getType(), FD->getType()) &&
11621  std::end(SeenDecls) == llvm::find(SeenDecls, CurFD)) {
11622  SeenDecls.insert(CurFD);
11623  Pred(CurFD);
11624  }
11625  }
11626 }
11627 
11628 CallingConv ASTContext::getDefaultCallingConvention(bool IsVariadic,
11629  bool IsCXXMethod,
11630  bool IsBuiltin) const {
11631  // Pass through to the C++ ABI object
11632  if (IsCXXMethod && !LangOpts.SYCLIsDevice)
11633  return ABI->getDefaultMethodCallConv(IsVariadic);
11634 
11635  // Builtins ignore user-specified default calling convention and remain the
11636  // Target's default calling convention.
11637  if (!IsBuiltin) {
11638  switch (LangOpts.getDefaultCallingConv()) {
11639  case LangOptions::DCC_None:
11640  break;
11641  case LangOptions::DCC_CDecl:
11642  return CC_C;
11643  case LangOptions::DCC_FastCall:
11644  if (getTargetInfo().hasFeature("sse2") && !IsVariadic)
11645  return CC_X86FastCall;
11646  break;
11647  case LangOptions::DCC_StdCall:
11648  if (!IsVariadic)
11649  return CC_X86StdCall;
11650  break;
11651  case LangOptions::DCC_VectorCall:
11652  // __vectorcall cannot be applied to variadic functions.
11653  if (!IsVariadic)
11654  return CC_X86VectorCall;
11655  break;
11656  case LangOptions::DCC_RegCall:
11657  // __regcall cannot be applied to variadic functions.
11658  if (!IsVariadic)
11659  return CC_X86RegCall;
11660  break;
11661  }
11662  }
11663  return Target->getDefaultCallingConv();
11664 }

11666 bool ASTContext::isNearlyEmpty(const CXXRecordDecl *RD) const {
11667  // Pass through to the C++ ABI object
11668  return ABI->isNearlyEmpty(RD);
11669 }

11671 VTableContextBase *ASTContext::getVTableContext() {
11672  if (!VTContext.get()) {
11673  auto ABI = Target->getCXXABI();
11674  if (ABI.isMicrosoft())
11675  VTContext.reset(new MicrosoftVTableContext(*this));
11676  else {
11677  auto ComponentLayout = getLangOpts().RelativeCXXABIVTables
11678  ? ItaniumVTableContext::Relative
11679  : ItaniumVTableContext::Pointer;
11680  VTContext.reset(new ItaniumVTableContext(*this, ComponentLayout));
11681  }
11682  }
11683  return VTContext.get();
11684 }

11686 MangleContext *ASTContext::createMangleContext(const TargetInfo *T) {
11687  if (!T)
11688  T = Target;
11689  switch (T->getCXXABI().getKind()) {
11690  case TargetCXXABI::AppleARM64:
11691  case TargetCXXABI::Fuchsia:
11692  case TargetCXXABI::GenericAArch64:
11693  case TargetCXXABI::GenericItanium:
11694  case TargetCXXABI::GenericARM:
11695  case TargetCXXABI::GenericMIPS:
11696  case TargetCXXABI::iOS:
11697  case TargetCXXABI::WebAssembly:
11698  case TargetCXXABI::WatchOS:
11699  case TargetCXXABI::XL:
11700  return ItaniumMangleContext::create(*this, getDiagnostics());
11701  case TargetCXXABI::Microsoft:
11702  return MicrosoftMangleContext::create(*this, getDiagnostics());
11703  }
11704  llvm_unreachable("Unsupported ABI");
11705 }
11706 
11707 MangleContext *ASTContext::createDeviceMangleContext(const TargetInfo &T) {
11708  assert(T.getCXXABI().getKind() != TargetCXXABI::Microsoft &&
11709  "Device mangle context does not support Microsoft mangling.");
11710  switch (T.getCXXABI().getKind()) {
11711  case TargetCXXABI::AppleARM64:
11712  case TargetCXXABI::Fuchsia:
11713  case TargetCXXABI::GenericAArch64:
11714  case TargetCXXABI::GenericItanium:
11715  case TargetCXXABI::GenericARM:
11716  case TargetCXXABI::GenericMIPS:
11717  case TargetCXXABI::iOS:
11718  case TargetCXXABI::WebAssembly:
11719  case TargetCXXABI::WatchOS:
11720  case TargetCXXABI::XL:
11721  return ItaniumMangleContext::create(
11722  *this, getDiagnostics(),
11723  [](ASTContext &, const NamedDecl *ND) -> llvm::Optional<unsigned> {
11724  if (const auto *RD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(ND))
11725  return RD->getDeviceLambdaManglingNumber();
11726  return llvm::None;
11727  });
11728  case TargetCXXABI::Microsoft:
11729  return MicrosoftMangleContext::create(*this, getDiagnostics());
11730  }
11731  llvm_unreachable("Unsupported ABI");
11732 }

11752 /// getIntTypeForBitwidth -
11753 /// sets integer QualTy according to specified details:
11754 /// bitwidth, signed/unsigned.
11755 /// Returns empty type if there is no appropriate target types.
11756 QualType ASTContext::getIntTypeForBitwidth(unsigned DestWidth,
11757  unsigned Signed) const {
11758  TargetInfo::IntType Ty = getTargetInfo().getIntTypeByWidth(DestWidth, Signed);
11759  CanQualType QualTy = getFromTargetType(Ty);
11760  if (!QualTy && DestWidth == 128)
11761  return Signed ? Int128Ty : UnsignedInt128Ty;
11762  return QualTy;
11763 }
11764 
11765 /// getRealTypeForBitwidth -
11766 /// sets floating point QualTy according to specified bitwidth.
11767 /// Returns empty type if there is no appropriate target types.
11768 QualType ASTContext::getRealTypeForBitwidth(unsigned DestWidth,
11769  FloatModeKind ExplicitType) const {
11770  FloatModeKind Ty =
11771  getTargetInfo().getRealTypeByWidth(DestWidth, ExplicitType);
11772  switch (Ty) {
11773  case FloatModeKind::Float:
11774  return FloatTy;
11775  case FloatModeKind::Double:
11776  return DoubleTy;
11777  case FloatModeKind::LongDouble:
11778  return LongDoubleTy;
11779  case FloatModeKind::Float128:
11780  return Float128Ty;
11781  case FloatModeKind::Ibm128:
11782  return Ibm128Ty;
11783  case FloatModeKind::NoFloat:
11784  return {};
11785  }
11786 
11787  llvm_unreachable("Unhandled TargetInfo::RealType value");
11788 }

11877 QualType ASTContext::getStringLiteralArrayType(QualType EltTy,
11878  unsigned Length) const {
11879  // A C++ string literal has a const-qualified element type (C++ 2.13.4p1).
11880  if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus || getLangOpts().ConstStrings)
11881  EltTy = EltTy.withConst();
11882 
11883  EltTy = adjustStringLiteralBaseType(EltTy);
11884 
11885  // Get an array type for the string, according to C99 6.4.5. This includes
11886  // the null terminator character.
11887  return getConstantArrayType(EltTy, llvm::APInt(32, Length + 1), nullptr,
11888  ArrayType::Normal, /*IndexTypeQuals*/ 0);
11889 }

11902 MSGuidDecl *
11903 ASTContext::getMSGuidDecl(MSGuidDecl::Parts Parts) const {
11904  assert(MSGuidTagDecl && "building MS GUID without MS extensions?");
11905 
11906  llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
11907  MSGuidDecl::Profile(ID, Parts);
11908 
11909  void *InsertPos;
11910  if (MSGuidDecl *Existing = MSGuidDecls.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos))
11911  return Existing;
11912 
11913  QualType GUIDType = getMSGuidType().withConst();
11914  MSGuidDecl *New = MSGuidDecl::Create(*this, GUIDType, Parts);
11915  MSGuidDecls.InsertNode(New, InsertPos);
11916  return New;
11917 }

11919 TemplateParamObjectDecl *
11920 ASTContext::getTemplateParamObjectDecl(QualType T, const APValue &V) const {
11921  assert(T->isRecordType() && "template param object of unexpected type");
11922 
11923  // C++ [temp.param]p8:
11924  // [...] a static storage duration object of type 'const T' [...]
11925  T.addConst();
11926 
11927  llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
11928  TemplateParamObjectDecl::Profile(ID, T, V);
11929 
11930  void *InsertPos;
11931  if (TemplateParamObjectDecl *Existing =
11932  TemplateParamObjectDecls.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos))
11933  return Existing;
11934 
11935  TemplateParamObjectDecl *New = TemplateParamObjectDecl::Create(*this, T, V);
11936  TemplateParamObjectDecls.InsertNode(New, InsertPos);
11937  return New;
11938 }
11939 
11940 bool ASTContext::AtomicUsesUnsupportedLibcall(const AtomicExpr *E) const {
11941  const llvm::Triple &T = getTargetInfo().getTriple();
11942  if (!T.isOSDarwin())
11943  return false;
11944 
11945  if (!(T.isiOS() && T.isOSVersionLT(7)) &&
11946  !(T.isMacOSX() && T.isOSVersionLT(10, 9)))
11947  return false;
11948 
11949  QualType AtomicTy = E->getPtr()->getType()->getPointeeType();
11950  CharUnits sizeChars = getTypeSizeInChars(AtomicTy);
11951  uint64_t Size = sizeChars.getQuantity();
11952  CharUnits alignChars = getTypeAlignInChars(AtomicTy);
11953  unsigned Align = alignChars.getQuantity();
11954  unsigned MaxInlineWidthInBits = getTargetInfo().getMaxAtomicInlineWidth();
11955  return (Size != Align || toBits(sizeChars) > MaxInlineWidthInBits);
11956 }
11957 
11958 bool
11959 ASTContext::ObjCMethodsAreEqual(const ObjCMethodDecl *MethodDecl,
11960  const ObjCMethodDecl *MethodImpl) {
11961  // No point trying to match an unavailable/deprecated mothod.
11962  if (MethodDecl->hasAttr<UnavailableAttr>()
11963  || MethodDecl->hasAttr<DeprecatedAttr>())
11964  return false;
11965  if (MethodDecl->getObjCDeclQualifier() !=
11966  MethodImpl->getObjCDeclQualifier())
11967  return false;
11968  if (!hasSameType(MethodDecl->getReturnType(), MethodImpl->getReturnType()))
11969  return false;
11970 
11971  if (MethodDecl->param_size() != MethodImpl->param_size())
11972  return false;
11973 
11974  for (ObjCMethodDecl::param_const_iterator IM = MethodImpl->param_begin(),
11975  IF = MethodDecl->param_begin(), EM = MethodImpl->param_end(),
11976  EF = MethodDecl->param_end();
11977  IM != EM && IF != EF; ++IM, ++IF) {
11978  const ParmVarDecl *DeclVar = (*IF);
11979  const ParmVarDecl *ImplVar = (*IM);
11980  if (ImplVar->getObjCDeclQualifier() != DeclVar->getObjCDeclQualifier())
11981  return false;
11982  if (!hasSameType(DeclVar->getType(), ImplVar->getType()))
11983  return false;
11984  }
11985 
11986  return (MethodDecl->isVariadic() == MethodImpl->isVariadic());
11987 }

11989 uint64_t ASTContext::getTargetNullPointerValue(QualType QT) const {
11990  LangAS AS;
11991  if (QT->getUnqualifiedDesugaredType()->isNullPtrType())
11992  AS = LangAS::Default;
11993  else
11994  AS = QT->getPointeeType().getAddressSpace();
11995 
11996  return getTargetInfo().getNullPointerValue(AS);
11997 }

11999 unsigned ASTContext::getTargetAddressSpace(QualType T) const {
12000  // Return the address space for the type. If the type is a
12001  // function type without an address space qualifier, the
12002  // program address space is used. Otherwise, the target picks
12003  // the best address space based on the type information
12004  return T->isFunctionType() && !T.hasAddressSpace()
12005  ? getTargetInfo().getProgramAddressSpace()
12006  : getTargetAddressSpace(T.getQualifiers());
12007 }

12020 QualType ASTContext::getCorrespondingSaturatedType(QualType Ty) const {
12021  assert(Ty->isFixedPointType());
12022 
12023  if (Ty->isSaturatedFixedPointType()) return Ty;
12024 
12025  switch (Ty->castAs<BuiltinType>()->getKind()) {
12026  default:
12027  llvm_unreachable("Not a fixed point type!");
12028  case BuiltinType::ShortAccum:
12029  return SatShortAccumTy;
12030  case BuiltinType::Accum:
12031  return SatAccumTy;
12032  case BuiltinType::LongAccum:
12033  return SatLongAccumTy;
12034  case BuiltinType::UShortAccum:
12035  return SatUnsignedShortAccumTy;
12036  case BuiltinType::UAccum:
12037  return SatUnsignedAccumTy;
12038  case BuiltinType::ULongAccum:
12039  return SatUnsignedLongAccumTy;
12040  case BuiltinType::ShortFract:
12041  return SatShortFractTy;
12042  case BuiltinType::Fract:
12043  return SatFractTy;
12044  case BuiltinType::LongFract:
12045  return SatLongFractTy;
12046  case BuiltinType::UShortFract:
12047  return SatUnsignedShortFractTy;
12048  case BuiltinType::UFract:
12049  return SatUnsignedFractTy;
12050  case BuiltinType::ULongFract:
12051  return SatUnsignedLongFractTy;

12161 llvm::FixedPointSemantics
12162 ASTContext::getFixedPointSemantics(QualType Ty) const {
12163  assert((Ty->isFixedPointType() || Ty->isIntegerType()) &&
12164  "Can only get the fixed point semantics for a "
12165  "fixed point or integer type.");
12166  if (Ty->isIntegerType())
12167  return llvm::FixedPointSemantics::GetIntegerSemantics(
12168  getIntWidth(Ty), Ty->isSignedIntegerType());
12169 
12170  bool isSigned = Ty->isSignedFixedPointType();
12171  return llvm::FixedPointSemantics(
12172  static_cast<unsigned>(getTypeSize(Ty)), getFixedPointScale(Ty), isSigned,
12173  Ty->isSaturatedFixedPointType(),
12174  !isSigned && getTargetInfo().doUnsignedFixedPointTypesHavePadding());
12175 }

12177 llvm::APFixedPoint ASTContext::getFixedPointMax(QualType Ty) const {
12178  assert(Ty->isFixedPointType());

12180 }

12187 QualType ASTContext::getCorrespondingSignedFixedPointType(QualType Ty) const {
12188  assert(Ty->isUnsignedFixedPointType() &&
12189  "Expected unsigned fixed point type");
12190 
12191  switch (Ty->castAs<BuiltinType>()->getKind()) {
12192  case BuiltinType::UShortAccum:
12193  return ShortAccumTy;
12194  case BuiltinType::UAccum:
12195  return AccumTy;
12196  case BuiltinType::ULongAccum:
12197  return LongAccumTy;
12198  case BuiltinType::SatUShortAccum:
12199  return SatShortAccumTy;
12200  case BuiltinType::SatUAccum:
12201  return SatAccumTy;
12202  case BuiltinType::SatULongAccum:
12203  return SatLongAccumTy;
12204  case BuiltinType::UShortFract:
12205  return ShortFractTy;
12206  case BuiltinType::UFract:
12207  return FractTy;
12208  case BuiltinType::ULongFract:
12209  return LongFractTy;
12210  case BuiltinType::SatUShortFract:
12211  return SatShortFractTy;
12212  case BuiltinType::SatUFract:
12213  return SatFractTy;
12214  case BuiltinType::SatULongFract:
12215  return SatLongFractTy;
12216  default:
12217  llvm_unreachable("Unexpected unsigned fixed point type");
12218  }
12219 }
12220 
12221 ParsedTargetAttr
12222 ASTContext::filterFunctionTargetAttrs(const TargetAttr *TD) const {
12223  assert(TD != nullptr);
12224  ParsedTargetAttr ParsedAttr = TD->parse();
12225 
12226  llvm::erase_if(ParsedAttr.Features, [&](const std::string &Feat) {
12227  return !Target->isValidFeatureName(StringRef{Feat}.substr(1));
12228  });
12229  return ParsedAttr;
12230 }
12231 
12232 void ASTContext::getFunctionFeatureMap(llvm::StringMap<bool> &FeatureMap,
12233  const FunctionDecl *FD) const {
12234  if (FD)
12235  getFunctionFeatureMap(FeatureMap, GlobalDecl().getWithDecl(FD));
12236  else
12237  Target->initFeatureMap(FeatureMap, getDiagnostics(),
12238  Target->getTargetOpts().CPU,
12239  Target->getTargetOpts().Features);
12240 }
12241 
12242 // Fills in the supplied string map with the set of target features for the
12243 // passed in function.
12244 void ASTContext::getFunctionFeatureMap(llvm::StringMap<bool> &FeatureMap,
12245  GlobalDecl GD) const {
12246  StringRef TargetCPU = Target->getTargetOpts().CPU;
12247  const FunctionDecl *FD = GD.getDecl()->getAsFunction();
12248  if (const auto *TD = FD->getAttr<TargetAttr>()) {
12249  ParsedTargetAttr ParsedAttr = filterFunctionTargetAttrs(TD);
12250 
12251  // Make a copy of the features as passed on the command line into the
12252  // beginning of the additional features from the function to override.
12253  ParsedAttr.Features.insert(
12254  ParsedAttr.Features.begin(),
12255  Target->getTargetOpts().FeaturesAsWritten.begin(),
12256  Target->getTargetOpts().FeaturesAsWritten.end());
12257 
12258  if (ParsedAttr.Architecture != "" &&
12259  Target->isValidCPUName(ParsedAttr.Architecture))
12260  TargetCPU = ParsedAttr.Architecture;
12261 
12262  // Now populate the feature map, first with the TargetCPU which is either
12263  // the default or a new one from the target attribute string. Then we'll use
12264  // the passed in features (FeaturesAsWritten) along with the new ones from
12265  // the attribute.
12266  Target->initFeatureMap(FeatureMap, getDiagnostics(), TargetCPU,
12267  ParsedAttr.Features);
12268  } else if (const auto *SD = FD->getAttr<CPUSpecificAttr>()) {
12269  llvm::SmallVector<StringRef, 32> FeaturesTmp;
12270  Target->getCPUSpecificCPUDispatchFeatures(
12271  SD->getCPUName(GD.getMultiVersionIndex())->getName(), FeaturesTmp);
12272  std::vector<std::string> Features(FeaturesTmp.begin(), FeaturesTmp.end());
12273  Features.insert(Features.begin(),
12274  Target->getTargetOpts().FeaturesAsWritten.begin(),
12275  Target->getTargetOpts().FeaturesAsWritten.end());
12276  Target->initFeatureMap(FeatureMap, getDiagnostics(), TargetCPU, Features);
12277  } else if (const auto *TC = FD->getAttr<TargetClonesAttr>()) {
12278  std::vector<std::string> Features;
12279  StringRef VersionStr = TC->getFeatureStr(GD.getMultiVersionIndex());
12280  if (VersionStr.startswith("arch="))
12281  TargetCPU = VersionStr.drop_front(sizeof("arch=") - 1);
12282  else if (VersionStr != "default")
12283  Features.push_back((StringRef{"+"} + VersionStr).str());
12284 
12285  Target->initFeatureMap(FeatureMap, getDiagnostics(), TargetCPU, Features);
12286  } else {
12287  FeatureMap = Target->getTargetOpts().FeatureMap;
12288  }
12289 }
12290 
12291 OMPTraitInfo &ASTContext::getNewOMPTraitInfo() {

12293  return *OMPTraitInfoVector.back();
12294 }

12296 const StreamingDiagnostic &clang::
12297 operator<<(const StreamingDiagnostic &DB,

12300  return DB << Section.Decl;
12301  return DB << "a prior #pragma section";
12302 }
12303 
12304 bool ASTContext::mayExternalizeStaticVar(const Decl *D) const {
12305  bool IsStaticVar =
12306  isa<VarDecl>(D) && cast<VarDecl>(D)->getStorageClass() == SC_Static;
12307  bool IsExplicitDeviceVar = (D->hasAttr<CUDADeviceAttr>() &&
12308  !D->getAttr<CUDADeviceAttr>()->isImplicit()) ||
12309  (D->hasAttr<CUDAConstantAttr>() &&
12310  !D->getAttr<CUDAConstantAttr>()->isImplicit());
12311  // CUDA/HIP: static managed variables need to be externalized since it is
12312  // a declaration in IR, therefore cannot have internal linkage.
12313  return IsStaticVar &&
12314  (D->hasAttr<HIPManagedAttr>() || IsExplicitDeviceVar);
12315 }
12316 
12317 bool ASTContext::shouldExternalizeStaticVar(const Decl *D) const {
12318  return mayExternalizeStaticVar(D) &&
12319  (D->hasAttr<HIPManagedAttr>() ||
12320  CUDADeviceVarODRUsedByHost.count(cast<VarDecl>(D)));
12321 }
12322 
12323 StringRef ASTContext::getCUIDHash() const {
12324  if (!CUIDHash.empty())
12325  return CUIDHash;
12326  if (LangOpts.CUID.empty())
12327  return StringRef();
12328  CUIDHash = llvm::utohexstr(llvm::MD5Hash(LangOpts.CUID), /*LowerCase=*/true);
12329  return CUIDHash;
12330 }
